{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_1IUhkQu6cagduIAqQjFaFSRI","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tname: product-analyzer\n3\tdescription: у╗Ўт«џС║ДтЊЂтљЇтњїт«ўуйЉ URL,С║ДтЄ║тљФСИЅСИфт╝║тѕХуФаУіѓ(С║ДтЊЂжђ╗УЙЉ/UIUX/т«ўуйЉТЈЈУ┐░)уџёСИГТќЄ Markdown С║ДтЊЂтѕєТъљТіЦтЉіСИјжЁЇтЦЌТѕфтЏЙТќЄС╗Хтц╣сђѓС╝ўтЁѕжЕ▒тіеТАїжЮбуФ»;ТАїжЮбуФ»СИЇтЈ»ућеТЌХУЄфтіежЎЇу║Д web-onlyсђѓУДдтЈЉТќ╣т╝Ј:scripts/analyze_product.py У░Ѓуће,Тѕќт»╣У»ЮСИГ\"тѕєТъљ/ТІєУДБ/У»ёТхІ/У░Ѓуаћ У┐ЎСИфС║ДтЊЂ https://...\"у▒╗У»иТ▒ѓСИћтїЁтљФ URLсђѓ\n4\t---\n5\t\n6\t# product-analyzer\n7\t\n8\tТіі\"тѕєТъљСИђСИфТќ░С║ДтЊЂ\"У┐ЎС╗ХС║ІтЏ║тїќТѕљСИђТЮАтЈ»жЄЇтцЇТхЂТ░┤у║┐сђѓТ»ЈТгАУиЉжЃйС║ДтЄ║СИђС╗йу╗ЊТъёуе│т«џуџёТіЦтЉі + СИђу╗ётИдтЉйтљЇУДётѕЎуџёТѕфтЏЙ,Тќ╣СЙ┐т»╣тцќТЈљС║цсђЂтйњТАБсђЂУиеС║ДтЊЂТефтљЉТ»ћУЙЃсђѓ\n9\t\n10\t## тиЦСйюТеАт╝Ј\n11\t\n12\t- **т«їТЋ┤ТеАт╝Ј (full)**:ТіЊт«ўуйЉ Рєњ ТЅЙтЄ║тйЊтЅЇСИ╗Тю║УЃйућеуџёт«ЅУБЁтїЁ Рєњ УБЁтЦйжЕ▒тіетЎе(`scripts/install_cua_driver.py`)Рєњ тљ»тіеС║ДтЊЂ Рєњ уће **cua-driver** ТЊЇСйюСИ╗УдЂуЋїжЮб Рєњ ТЅ╣жЄЈТѕфтЏЙ Рєњ ТЋ┤тљѕтєЎТіЦтЉісђѓ**С╗Ё `runtime=host` тЇЋС╗╗тіА**Ух░ТГцУи»тЙёсђѓ\n13\t- **Т▓Ўу«▒т«їТЋ┤ТеАт╝Ј (sandbox-full)**:**С╗ЁТЅ╣жЄЈ** (`runtime=sandbox-local` / `sandbox-cloud`)сђѓуће Cua Sandbox SDK тюеТ▓ЎуЏњтєЁт«їТѕљтѕєТъљ;`metadata.mode` СИ║ `sandbox-full`сђѓтЇЋС╗╗тіА**СИЇтЙЌ**Сй┐ућесђѓ\n14\t- **Android ТеАт╝Ј (android)**:**С╗ЁТ▓ЎуЏњТЅ╣жЄЈ**СИћ `android.enabled=true` **СИћ Android Т▓ЎуЏњТѕљтіЪтљ»тіе**ТЌХуџётбът╝║жА╣сђѓТюфтљ»ућеТѕќТ▓ЎуЏњТюфУхиТЌХ**тЈфТЊЇСйюуйЉжАх**(Firefox),С╗јт«ўуйЉУјитЈќС║ДтЊЂС┐АТЂ»,УДЂ [Android Тюфтљ»ућеТѕќТюфтљ»тіе](#android-Тюфтљ»ућеТѕќТюфтљ»тіе)сђѓ\n15\t- **уйЉжАхТеАт╝Ј (web-only)**:С╗ЁтЪ║С║јт«ўуйЉС┐АТЂ» + ТхЈУДѕтЎеТѕфтЏЙсђѓС╗ЁтюеТАїжЮбжЕ▒тіеСИЇтЈ»УЙЙТЌХтљ»уће Рђћ УДЂСИІТќЄ\"Уиет╣│тЈ░СИјжЎЇу║Д\"\n16\t\n17\t## У┐љУАїТЌХтѕєТхЂ(у╝ќТјњтЎетЦЉу║д,т┐ЁУ»╗)\n18\t\n19\tPython у╝ќТјњтЎежђџУ┐Є prompt жЄїуџё `runtime` СИј `metadata.json` тї║тѕєУи»тЙёсђѓ**СИЇУдЂУЄфУАїТћ╣ућеТ▓ЎуЏњТѕќТћ╣уће cua-driverсђѓ**\n20\t\n21\t| тЁЦтЈБ | `runtime` | жЕ▒тіеТќ╣т╝Ј | удЂТГб |\n22\t|------|-----------|----------|------|\n23\t| **тЇЋС╗╗тіА**:УЈютЇЋ 1сђЂСйЇуй«тЈѓТЋ░сђЂ`python scripts/analyze_product.py \"тљЇ\" \"URL\"` | **`host`** | ТюгТю║ **cua-driver** + уѕХ shell `curl`(тЈ»Ух░С╗Буљє) | `import cua`сђЂ`Sandbox.ephemeral`сђЂDocker/Lume/QEMU Т▓ЎуЏњсђЂУ»╗сђїSandbox У┐љУАїтљѕу║дсђЇтйЊТЊЇСйюТЅІтєї |\n24\t| **ТЅ╣жЄЈ**: `--batch queue.json` | **`sandbox-local`** Тѕќ **`sandbox-cloud`** | **жђљТГЦ**ТјДтѕХТ▓ЎуЏњ(УДЂсђїТ▓ЎуЏњТјДтѕХСИЅжўХТ«хсђЇ);Тюгтю░уће `sandbox_ctl`,С║ЉуФ»уће Cua MCP | cua-driverсђЂhost ТхЈУДѕтЎе/GUIсђЂТЋ┤Т«х `asyncio` тѕєТъљУёџТюг |\n25\t\n26\t**тѕцт«џ**:prompt жЄї `runtime:host` Рєњ тЈфУх░ [Host тЇЋС╗╗тіА](#host-тЇЋС╗╗тіА-runtimehost)сђѓ`runtime:sandbox-local` / `sandbox-cloud` Рєњ тЈфУх░ [Sandbox У┐љУАїтљѕу║д](#sandbox-У┐љУАїтљѕу║д)сђѓ`batch.parallel:true` С╗ЁТЅ╣жЄЈтЄ║уј░сђѓ\n27\t\n28\t## УЙЊтЁЦ\n29\t\n30\tућ▒У░ЃућеТќ╣(УёџТюгТѕќт»╣У»Ю)ТЈљСЙЏ:\n31\t- `product_name` Рђћ т┐ЁтАФ,т▒Ћуц║ућетјЪТќЄ(тЁЂУ«ИСИГТќЄ / тцДт░ЈтєЎТииТјњ)\n32\t- `url` Рђћ т┐ЁтАФ,С║ДтЊЂт«ўуйЉ https URL\n33\t- `download_url` Рђћ тЈ»жђЅ,уЏ┤ТјЦТїЄтљЉтйЊтЅЇСИ╗Тю║УЃйућеуџёт«ЅУБЁтїЁ(.dmg / .exe / .deb уГЅ)сђѓ**С╝ўтЁѕу║ДТюђжФў**,ТюЅт«Ѓт░▒Уи│У┐Є\"тюет«ўуйЉТЅЙСИІУййжЊЙТјЦ\"ТГЦжфц\n34\t- `output_dir` Рђћ У░ЃућеТќ╣ти▓у╗Јт╗║тЦйуџёу╗Ют»╣Уи»тЙё,тйбтдѓ `<repo>/reports/<slug>-YYYY-MM-DD[-N]/`,Тюг skill ТііТЅђТюЅС║ДуЅЕтєЎУ┐Џтј╗\n35\t- `runtime` Рђћ `host`сђЂ`sandbox-local` Тѕќ `sandbox-cloud`сђѓ`host` Сй┐ућетйЊтЅЇСИ╗Тю║ + cua-driver;`sandbox-local` / `sandbox-cloud` т┐ЁжА╗Сй┐уће Cua Sandbox SDK,СИћСИЇтЙЌТЊЇСйю host GUI\n36\t- `sandbox.image` Рђћ `auto` / `linux` / `macos` / `windows`,С╗Ё sandbox runtime ТюЅТЋѕ\n37\t- `sandbox.local` Рђћ `true` СИ║Тюгтю░ Docker/Lume/QEMU(ТЅ╣жЄЈж╗ўУ«ц);`false` СИ║ Cua Cloud(С╗ЁтйЊУ░ЃућеТќ╣ТўЙт╝Ј `--sandbox cloud` ТЌХ,жюђ `CUA_API_KEY` Т│етЁЦ env,**СИЇУдЂ**тєЎтЁЦ metadata.json)\n38\t- `android.enabled` Рђћ Тў»тљдТБђТхІт╣Хт░ЮУ»Ћ Android APK Уи»тЙё\n39\t- `batch.parallel` Рђћ Тў»тљдСИ║ТЅ╣жЄЈжўЪтѕЌСИГуџёт╣ХУАї worker(`true` ТЌХт┐ЁУ»╗СИІТќЄсђїТЅ╣жЄЈт╣ХУАїсђЇ)\n40\t\n41\tу╝ќТјњтЎеУ┐ўтЈ»УЃйжђџУ┐Є**уј»тбЃтЈўжЄЈ**Т│етЁЦ(СЙЏСйаУ»╗ skill ТЌХт»╣уЁД,тІ┐тєЎтЁЦ metadata):`ANALYZER_LINUX_CONTAINER_IMAGE`сђЂ`ANALYZER_LINUX_DOCKER_PLATFORM`сђЂ`ANALYZER_PYTHON_VERSION_MIN`сђЂ`ANALYZER_CONDA_ENV`сђЂ`ANALYZER_BATCH_PARALLEL`сђЂ`CUA_API_KEY`(С╗ЁС║ЉуФ»)сђѓ\n42\t\n43\t## УЙЊтЄ║тИЃт▒ђ\n44\t\n45\t```\n46\t<output_dir>/\n47\t  report.md                     # ТіЦтЉіСИ╗СйЊ\n48\t  metadata.json                 # Тю║тЎетЈ»У»╗тЁЃТЋ░ТЇ«\n49\t  downloads/                    # СИІУййуџёт«ЅУБЁтїЁ / APK\n50\t  screenshots/\n51\t    01_web_homepage.png\n52\t    02_web_pricing.png         # у╝ќтЈиУДЂСИІ\n53\t    05_app_main.png\n54\t    ...\n55\t```\n56\t\n57\t`metadata.json` уџёТюђу╗ѕтйбТђЂ(Python УёџТюгтєЎС║єжЏЈтйб,Тюг skill тюеу╗ЊТЮЪтЅЇУАЦжйљ):\n58\t```json\n59\t{\n60\t  \"product_name\": \"ProductiveKitty\",\n61\t  \"url\": \"https://productivekitty.masterwordai.com\",\n62\t  \"download_url\": null,\n63\t  \"host_os\": \"darwin\",\n64\t  \"host_arch\": \"arm64\",\n65\t  \"runtime\": \"host\",\n66\t  \"sandbox\": {\"image\": null, \"local\": true, \"mode\": \"local\", \"name\": null, \"api_url\": null},\n67\t  \"android\": {\n68\t    \"enabled\": false,\n69\t    \"apk_url\": null,\n70\t    \"apk_file\": null,\n71\t    \"package_name\": null,\n72\t    \"mode\": null\n73\t  },\n74\t  \"started_at\": \"2026-05-18T03:30:00+08:00\",\n75\t  \"finished_at\": \"2026-05-18T03:55:00+08:00\",\n76\t  \"mode\": \"full\",\n77\t  \"screenshots\": [\n78\t    {\"file\": \"screenshots/01_web_homepage.png\", \"view\": \"web-homepage\", \"caption\": \"т«ўуйЉждќжАх\"},\n79\t    ...\n80\t  ],\n81\t  \"warnings\": []\n82\t}\n83\t```\n84\t\n85\t## ТѕфтЏЙтЉйтљЇ\n86\t\n87\t`NN_<source>_<view>.png`:\n88\t- `NN` Рђћ СИцСйЇжЏХтАФтЁЁуџётЇЋУ░Ѓу╝ќтЈисђѓ**тЁЂУ«ИУи│тЈи**:web Т«хСИђУѕг 01-04,app Т«х 05+ Ухи;УІЦСИГжђћТќ░тбъС╣ЪтЈ»С╗ЦТІ┐ 09сђЂ10\n89\t- `source Рѕѕ {web, app, android}` Рђћ `web` УАеуц║ТхЈУДѕтЎетєЁТѕфтЏЙ,`app` УАеуц║ТАїжЮбт║ћућеуфЌтЈБТѕфтЏЙ,`android` УАеуц║ Android Т▓Ўу«▒тєЁТѕфтЏЙ\n90\t- `view` Рђћ уЪГ kebab-case,У»ГС╣Ѕтїќ:`homepage / pricing / faq / main / settings / new-task / focus-mode / report-detail` уГЅ\n91\t\n92\tТ»Јт╝аТѕфтЏЙжЃйт┐ЁжА╗тюе `report.md` жЄїС╗ЦуЏИт»╣Уи»тЙё(`screenshots/NN_*.png`)тЄ║уј░,СИћтюе**жЎётйЋ A ТѕфтЏЙу┤бт╝Ћ**жЄїТюЅСИђУАїУ»┤ТўјсђѓТ▓Ат╝ЋућеУ┐ЄуџёТѕфтЏЙтѕаТјЅ,СИЇУдЂуЋЎт╝ЃтЏЙсђѓ\n93\t\n94\t## Canonical loop(7 ТГЦ,тЏ║т«џжА║т║Ј)\n95\t\n96\tУ░ЃућеТќ╣У┐ЏтЁЦТЌХ,`output_dir` ти▓т╗║тЦйсђЂ`metadata.json` жЏЈтйбти▓тєЎсђѓУ┐Ў skill ТјЦу«Атљју╗Гсђѓ\n97\t\n98\t**СИцТЮАжЊЂтЙІ(С╝ўтЁѕу║ДжФўС║јС╗╗СйЋТГЦжфцу╗єУіѓ)**:\n99\t\n100\t1. **ТЅЙСИІУййжЊЙТјЦ = уюЪт«ъТЊЇСйюТхЈУДѕтЎе**,СИЇТў»тЈфУиЉ curl + grepсђѓ`curl + grep` тЈфТў»т┐ФжђЪу║┐у┤б,**СИЇТў»тѕцт«џ web-only уџёСЙЮТЇ«**сђѓ`grep` Т▓АтЄ║у╗ЊТъюТЌХ**т┐ЁжА╗**у╗Ду╗ГТЅЊт╝ђТхЈУДѕтЎе,уюЪт«ъуѓ╣тЄ╗т»╝Уѕф Рђћ host уће cua-driver;sandbox уће **ж╝аТаЄ/жћ«уЏўжђљТГЦ**(`screenshot` Рєњ `click`/`scroll` Рєњ `type`/`key`),**удЂТГб**уће `step shell` + `wget/curl` С╗БТЏ┐уѓ╣уйЉжАхсђѓ\n101\t\n102\t2. **т«їТЋ┤ТеАт╝ЈСИІ,ТАїжЮбт║ћућеТў»т┐ЁтЂџжА╣,СИЇУЃйтЏаСИ║уйЉжАхтЦйујЕт░▒уюЂуЋЦ**:ТюЅт«ЅУБЁтїЁт░▒**т┐ЁжА╗**УБЁсђЂтљ»тіесђЂуће cua-driver Тііт«бТѕиуФ»СИ╗УдЂтіЪУЃйУх░СИђжЂЇсђѓуйЉжАхтЈ»С╗ЦтљїТЌХТи▒тЁЦТјбу┤б(тцџТїќСИђС║Џт«џС╗исђЂТќЄТАБсђЂтЇџт«бжЃйТ▓АжЌ«жбў),Сйє web Т«хтЂџтЙЌтцџРЅа app Т«хтЈ»С╗ЦтЂџтЙЌт░Љсђѓapp Т«хТў» ┬Д1 ТіЦтЉіуџёСИ╗УдЂу┤аТЮљТЮЦТ║љ,**С╗╗СйЋ\"т║ћућеТѕЉуюІС║єт«ўуйЉт░▒тцДТдѓуЪЦжЂЊС║є\"Тѕќ\"т║ћућетљ»тіетцфж║╗уЃдтЁѕУи│У┐Є\"уџётЂиТЄњжЃйСИЇУАї**сђѓтЈфТюЅ step 3 тЁежЃетц▒У┤ЦсђЂуА«т«ъСИІСИЇтѕ░т«ЅУБЁтїЁ,ТЅЇУ┐ЏтЁЦ web-only ТеАт╝Ј,ТііуйЉжАхтйЊСИ╗Тѕўтю║\n103\t\n104\t- `runtime=host` ТЌХ:тЈфУ»╗ [Host тЇЋС╗╗тіА](#host-тЇЋС╗╗тіА-runtimehost),**СИЇУдЂ**У»╗сђїSandbox У┐љУАїтљѕу║дсђЇсђѓ\n105\t- `runtime` СИ║ `sandbox-local` Тѕќ `sandbox-cloud` ТЌХ:т┐ЁжА╗тЁѕУ»╗ [Sandbox У┐љУАїтљѕу║д](#sandbox-У┐љУАїтљѕу║д),тєЇТЅДУАї canonical loopсђѓ\n106\t\n107\t### 7 ТГЦУ»ду╗є\n108\t\n109\t1. **TodoWrite т╗║ 7 СИф todos**:`ТіЊтЈќт«ўуйЉ` Рєњ `т«џСйЇСИІУййжЊЙТјЦ` Рєњ `т«ЅУБЁ/тљ»тіет║ћуће` Рєњ `жЕ▒тіеуЏ«ТаЄ(т║ћуће + тЈ»жђЅуйЉжАх)` Рєњ `ТЅ╣жЄЈТѕфтЏЙ` Рєњ `ТЋ┤тљѕТіЦтЉі` Рєњ `УАЦжйљ metadata.json`сђѓТ»ЈТГЦт╝ђтДІтЅЇ `in_progress`,т«їТѕљУйг `completed`\n110\t\n111\t2. **ТіЊтЈќт«ўуйЉтјЪтДІС┐АТЂ»(у║┐у┤б + тЁЦжЌеСйЊжфї)** Рђћ\n112\t   - **host**:уѕХ shell `curl -fsSL`(тЈ»Ух░С╗Буљє)+ Python тЅЦ HTML;уће **cua-driver** ТЅЊт╝ђТхЈУДѕтЎеТѕфждќжАх `01_web_homepage.png`сђѓ\n113\t   - **sandbox**(**ж╝аТаЄС╝ўтЁѕ**,УДЂСИІУіѓ):\n114\t     1. `sandbox_ctl bootstrap \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" --open-browser --url '<т«ўуйЉ>'`(Тѕќ `step open-url`)\n115\t     2. `step screenshot` Рєњ `01_web_homepage.png`\n116\t     3. уће **click / scroll / type / key** ТхЈУДѕ(тЁ│ cookie т╝╣уфЌсђЂуѓ╣т»╝Уѕф),Т»ЈТГЦтЅЇтљјТѕфтЏЙ\n117\t     - **удЂТГб**уће `step shell -c 'curl/wget ...'` ТіЊт«ўуйЉтйЊСИ╗Уи»тЙё;shell С╗ЁтЁЂУ«ИСИІТќЄсђїСЙІтцќсђЇсђѓ\n118\t   - тЈ»жА║тИдТхЈУДѕт«џС╗и/ТќЄТАБжАх Рђћ СИЇУЃйТЏ┐С╗БТАїжЮбуФ»СйЊжфїсђѓ\n119\t\n120\t3. **т«џСйЇСИІУййжЊЙТјЦ(тѕєСИцт▒ѓ:жЮЎТђЂ grep + уюЪт«ъТхЈУДѕ)** Рђћ\n121\t   С╝ўтЁѕућеУ░ЃућеТќ╣С╝атЁЦуџё `download_url`сђѓтљдтѕЎ:\n122\t\n123\t   **3.1 жЮЎТђЂу║┐у┤б(тЈ»жђЅ,sandbox СИІ**СИЇтЙЌ**ТЏ┐С╗Буѓ╣тЄ╗)**:\n124\t   - host тЈ»тюети▓СИІУйй HTML СИі grep т«ЅУБЁтїЁ URLсђѓ\n125\t   - sandbox:**СИЇУдЂ**СИ║ТЅЙжЊЙТјЦУђї `wget` ТЋ┤уФЎ;С╗Ц **3.2 ж╝аТаЄТхЈУДѕ** СИ║тЄє,УѓЅую╝+ТѕфтЏЙУ«░тйЋСИІУййтЁЦтЈБсђѓ\n126\t\n127\t   **3.2 ТхЈУДѕтЎет«ъТЊЇ(т┐ЁжА╗тЂџ,СИЇтЈ»Уи│У┐Є)**:\n128\t   - host: cua-driver уѓ╣тЄ╗т»╝Уѕфсђѓ\n129\t   - sandbox: **`sandbox_ctl step screenshot` / `click` / `scroll` / `type` / `key`** Ух░т«їт«ўуйЉ(УДЂсђїТ▓ЎуЏњтєЁж╝аТаЄС╝ўтЁѕсђЇ):\n130\t   - ТЅЊт╝ђТхЈУДѕтЎе,т«џСйЇтѕ░т«ўуйЉ,**уюЪт«ъуѓ╣тЄ╗**т»╝УѕфТаЈжЄїТЅђТюЅуюІУхиТЮЦуЏИтЁ│уџётЁЦтЈБ:`Download`/`СИІУйй`/`Get the App`/`Install`/`Pricing`/`Get Started`/`Try Free`/`С║ДтЊЂ`уГЅ\n131\t   - УІЦ `android.enabled=true` СИћУ«АтѕњТІЅУхи Android Т▓ЎуЏњ,жбЮтцќуѓ╣тЄ╗/ТБђТЪЦ `Android` / `APK` / `Mobile` / `Get it on Android` / `Google Play` тЁЦтЈБ\n132\t   - УІЦ `android.enabled=false` Тѕќ Android Т▓ЎуЏњТюфтљ»тіе:тЈфтюе **Firefox уйЉжАх**жЄї hunt(тљФ Play жЊЙТјЦТќЄтГЌУ»ЂТЇ«),**СИЇ**СИІУйй/т«ЅУБЁ APK\n133\t   - Т»ЈСИфтђЎжђЅжАхжЃйТѕфтЏЙтГўТАБ(`screenshots/02_web_<view>.png` тйбт╝Ј)\n134\t   - Т╗џтѕ░т║ЋжЃе,уюІ footer ТюЅТ▓АТюЅ `Mac` / `Windows` / `Linux` / `Android` уџёт░ЈтЏЙТаЄТїЅжњ«\n135\t   - уѓ╣тЄ╗т╣│тЈ░тѕЄТЇбтЎе(тЙѕтцџуФЎуѓ╣С╝џтЁѕТўЙуц║У«┐т«б OS ТјеУЇљ)сђЂтЁ│ТјЅуЎ╗тйЋт╝╣уфЌсђЂтЁ│ТјЅ cookie Тефт╣Ё,у╗Ду╗ГТЅЙ\n136\t   - С╗╗СйЋ a11y ТаЉСИ║уЕ║ / Electron canvas уџёжАхжЮбТїЅ [cua-driver SKILL](../cua-driver/SKILL.md) уџё escalation жўХТб»тЇЄу║Дтѕ░ vision\n137\t\n138\t   **3.3 тЉйСИГтљјжђЅТюђтї╣жЁЇуџёт«ЅУБЁтїЁ**:\n139\t   - `darwin/arm64` С╝ўтЁѕ `*arm64*.dmg`сђЂ`*aarch64*.dmg`,тљдтѕЎ `darwin/x86_64` уће `*x64*.dmg`сђЂ`*intel*.dmg`сђЂСИЇтИдТъХТъёТаЄуџё `.dmg`\n140\t   - `linux/x86_64` С╝ўтЁѕ `*x86_64*.AppImage`/`.deb`/`.tar.gz`\n141\t   - `windows/x86_64` жђЅ `*.exe` / `*.msi` / `Setup-*.exe`\n142\t   - Android APK тЈфТјЦтЈЌт«ўуйЉуЏ┤жЊЙТѕќт«ўТќ╣ release assetсђѓGoogle Play тЈфУ«░тйЋУ»ЂТЇ«,СИЇу╗ЋуЎ╗тйЋсђЂСИЇТіЊуггСИЅТќ╣жЋютЃЈсђЂСИЇС╗јжЮът«ўТќ╣ APK жЋютЃЈуФЎСИІУйй\n143\t   - ТЅЙтѕ░ APK ТЌХтєЎтЁЦ `metadata.android.apk_url`;СИІУййтѕ░ `<output_dir>/downloads/`,тєЎтЁЦ `metadata.android.apk_file`\n144\t\n145\t   **3.4 тЁежЃетц▒У┤ЦТЅЇТаЄ web-only**,т╣Хтюе `metadata.warnings[]` тєЎТўј:\n146\t   - жЮЎТђЂ grep У»ЋУ┐ЄтЊфС║Џ\n147\t   - ТхЈУДѕтЎет«ъжЎЁУ«┐жЌ«/уѓ╣тЄ╗У┐ЄтЊфС║ЏжАхжЮб(тѕЌтЄ║жАхжЮб URL,У»ЂТўјтЂџС║єуюЪт«ъ hunt)\n148\t   - Тюђу╗ѕу╗ЊУ«║(тдѓ\"С║ДтЊЂС╗ЁТюЅ Web уЅѕ,ТЌаТАїжЮбуФ»т«ЅУБЁтїЁ\")\n149\t\n150\t4. **т«ЅУБЁ/тљ»тіет║ћуће(С╗ЁтйЊ step 3 тЉйСИГ)** Рђћ\n151\t   - host runtime:уће `scripts/install_cua_driver.py` уА«С┐ЮТАїжЮбжЕ▒тіетЎети▓УБЁ(жбёТБђУ┐Є,Сйє sanity-check СИђТгА `which cua-driver`)сђѓСИІУййС║ДтЊЂт«ЅУБЁтїЁтѕ░ `<output_dir>/downloads/`,ТїЅт╣│тЈ░ућет»╣т║ћТќ╣т╝Јт«ЅУБЁ(macOS:`hdiutil attach` + `cp -R` + `xattr -d com.apple.quarantine`;Linux:`dpkg -i` Тѕќ `chmod +x` AppImage;Windows:`start /wait` MSI)сђѓ**СИЦТа╝жЂхтЙф [cua-driver SKILL](../cua-driver/SKILL.md) уџё no-foreground тЦЉу║д**\n152\t   - sandbox-local / sandbox-cloud runtime:Т▓ЎуЏњти▓тюе **bootstrap** жўХТ«хтѕЏт╗║сђѓ**т«ЅУБЁтїЁ**тЈ»тюети▓ТюЅуЏ┤жЊЙТЌХуће **СИђТгА** `step shell -c 'wget -O ...'` СИІУййтѕ░ `downloads/`(СЙІтцќ);**тљ»тіет║ћућесђЂуѓ╣уЋїжЮб**СИђтЙІ **mouse/keyboard**(`click`/`type`/`scroll`/`screenshot`)сђѓ\n153\t   - Android APK:**С╗ЁтйЊ** `android.enabled=true` **СИћ** Android Т▓ЎуЏњти▓т░▒у╗фТЌХ:УІЦ `metadata.android.apk_url` ти▓тАФ,тєЇтѕЏт╗║ Android sandbox т╣Х `adb install` уГЅсђѓтљдтѕЎУи│У┐Є,Тћ╣Ух░ [Android Тюфтљ»ућеТѕќТюфтљ»тіе](#android-Тюфтљ»ућеТѕќТюфтљ»тіе)\n154\t\n155\t5. **жЕ▒тіеуЏ«ТаЄ** Рђћ\n156\t\n157\t   **5.A т«їТЋ┤ТеАт╝Ј(step 3 тЉйСИГ):ТАїжЮбт║ћућет┐ЁтЂџ,т«ўуйЉтЈ»жђЅТи▒Тїќ** Рђћ\n158\t   - **ТАїжЮбуФ»т┐ЁтЂџ**:тљ»тіеС║ДтЊЂ,**СИ╗УдЂтіЪУЃйТїеСИфУх░СИђжЂЇ**сђѓТ»ЈТЅЊт╝ђСИђСИфТќ░уЋїжЮбт░▒ТѕфтЏЙсђѓhost уће cua-driver;sandbox уће **ж╝аТаЄС╝ўтЁѕ**жђљТГЦуѓ╣(app тЏЙТаЄсђЂУЈютЇЋсђЂТїЅжњ«),**удЂТГб**тЈфжЮа shell тљ»тіетљјСИЇтєЇуѓ╣уЋїжЮбсђѓapp Т«хТѕфтЏЙУЄ│т░Љ 4-8 т╝а,**У┐ЎТў» ┬Д1 ТіЦтЉіуџёСИ╗УдЂу┤аТЮљТЮЦТ║љ**\n159\t   - **т«ўуйЉтЈ»жђЅТи▒Тїќ**:тюеС┐ЮУ»ЂТАїжЮбуФ»СйЊжфїт«їТЋ┤уџётЅЇТЈљСИІ,тЈ»С╗Цу╗Ду╗ГуюІт«џС╗и / ТќЄТАБ / тЇџт«б / FAQ уГЅ,УАЦтЁЁ ┬Д3 т«ўуйЉТЈЈУ┐░уџёу┤аТЮљсђѓweb Т«хТѕфтЏЙТЋ░жЄЈТ▓АТюЅСИіжЎљ Рђћ Сйє**у╗Ют»╣СИЇУЃйућеуйЉжАхТѕфтЏЙТЏ┐С╗Бт║ћућеТѕфтЏЙ**,С╣ЪСИЇУЃйтЏаСИ║уйЉжАхтєЁт«╣тцџт░▒у╝ЕТ░┤т║ћућеСйЊжфї\n160\t\n161\t   **5.B уйЉжАхТеАт╝Ј(step 3 тЁежЃетц▒У┤Ц,жЎЇу║Д web-only):тюеТхЈУДѕтЎежЄїт«їТЋ┤СйЊжфї** Рђћ У┐ЎТЌХуйЉжАхт░▒Тў»С║ДтЊЂТюгСйЊ,ућетйЊтЅЇ runtime уџёТхЈУДѕтЎеТЊЇСйюУЃйтіЏжђљжАхТи▒тЁЦ:\n162\t   - ждќжАх(Т╗џтѕ░т║Ћ,тљё section тљёТѕфСИђт╝а)\n163\t   - СИ╗тіЪУЃйжАх / Т╝ћуц║жАх(УЃйС║цС║њуџёжЃетѕєжЃйУ»ЋСИђСИІ:УЙЊтЁЦсђЂТЈљС║цсђЂТњГТћЙсђЂтѕЄ tab)\n164\t   - т«џС╗и / Pricing(тљёТАБСйЇжЃйуѓ╣т╝ђ)\n165\t   - ТќЄТАБ / тИ«тіЕ / Changelog\n166\t   - FAQ / тЇџт«бтц┤уЅѕ / тЁ│С║ј\n167\t   - уЎ╗тйЋтЁЦтЈБ(тЈфуюІСИЇТЊЇСйюУ┤дтЈи)\n168\t   - тЏйжЎЁтїќ:ТюЅ `EN/СИГТќЄ/...` тѕЄТЇбтЎет░▒тѕЄСИђжЂЇтљёуюІСИђт╝а\n169\t   - жћЎУ»»ТђЂ:ТЋЁТёЈУЙЊтЁЦжћЎуџёсђЂуѓ╣СИЇУ»Цуѓ╣уџё,уюІС║цС║њтЈЇждѕ\n170\t   - web Т«хУЄ│т░Љ 6-10 т╝атЏЙ\n171\t\n172\t   СИцуДЇТеАт╝ЈжЃйУдЂС┐ЮУ»Ђ ┬Д1 ТіЦтЉіуФаУіѓТюЅУХ│тцЪтцџуџё\"уЋїжЮб\"тЈ»тєЎсђѓ\n173\t\n174\t   **5.C Android тбът╝║Уи»тЙё(С╗Ё `android.enabled=true` СИћ Android Т▓ЎуЏњти▓тљ»тіе;ТЅЙтѕ░ APK ТЌХУ┐йтіа)** Рђћ\n175\t   - тюе Android sandbox СИГтљ»тіет║ћуће,ТѕфтЏЙС┐ЮтГўСИ║ `screenshots/NN_android_<view>.png`\n176\t   - УЄ│т░ЉУдєуЏќтљ»тіежАхсђЂСИ╗уЋїжЮбсђЂТЮЃжЎљт╝╣уфЌсђЂуЎ╗тйЋтбЎсђЂУ«Йуй«/тЁ│С║јсђЂжћЎУ»»ТђЂСИГтЈ»УЙЙуџёжЃетѕє\n177\t   - СИЇтѕЏт╗║У┤дтЈисђЂСИЇу╗ЋУ┐ЄуЎ╗тйЋсђЂСИЇТјѕС║ѕжФўтЇ▒ТЮЃжЎљ;ТЮЃжЎљт╝╣уфЌтЈфУ«░тйЋж╗ўУ«цТќЄТАѕтњїтЈ»УДЂжђЅжА╣\n178\t   - УІЦ APK т«ЅУБЁтц▒У┤ЦсђЂтљ»тіежЌфжђђсђЂAndroid Т▓ЎуЏњ**Тюфтљ»тіе**Тѕќ runtime у╝║тц▒:тєЎтЁЦ `metadata.android.mode = \"failed\"`(Тѕќ `skipped`),`metadata.warnings[]` У»┤ТўјтјЪтЏа,**Тћ╣тЈфТЊЇСйюуйЉжАх**т«їТѕљтЅЕСйЎтѕєТъљ(УДЂ [Android Тюфтљ»ућеТѕќТюфтљ»тіе](#android-Тюфтљ»ућеТѕќТюфтљ»тіе)),ТіЦтЉітЈфт╝Ћућети▓ТюЅУ»ЂТЇ«\n179\t\n180\t6. **ТЅ╣жЄЈТѕфтЏЙ** Рђћ ТЋ┤уљє screenshots/,тѕатєЌСйЎсђЂС┐ЮуЋЎС╗БУАеТђДуџёсђЂуА«С┐ЮтЉйтљЇУ┐ъу╗Г(тЁЂУ«ИУи│тЈи)\n181\t\n182\t7. **ТЋ┤тљѕТіЦтЉі** Рђћ ТІиУ┤Ю [REPORT_TEMPLATE.md](REPORT_TEMPLATE.md) тѕ░ `<output_dir>/report.md`,жђљУіѓтАФтєЎсђѓтЈ»жђЅуФаУіѓ(т«џС╗и / уЏ«ТаЄућеТѕи / тљїу▒╗т»╣Т»ћ / С╝ўтіБті┐)**тЈфтюеТюЅУ»ЂТЇ«ТЌХС┐ЮуЋЎ,тљдтѕЎТЋ┤Т«хтѕажЎц**сђѓТЅђТюЅ\"У»ёС╗и\"тъІжЎѕУ┐░т┐ЁжА╗тЈ»УбФТѕфтЏЙТѕќт«ўуйЉтјЪТќЄУ»Ђт«ъ\n183\t\n184\tТ»ЈТГЦу╗ЊТЮЪ TodoWrite ТаЄ `completed`,СИІСИђТГЦТаЄ `in_progress`,уёХтљјт╝ђтДІСИІСИђТГЦсђѓ\n185\t\n186\t## Host тЇЋС╗╗тіА (`runtime=host`)\n187\t\n188\tтйЊ prompt / `metadata.json` жЄї **`runtime` СИ║ `host`** ТЌХ(ж╗ўУ«цтЇЋС╗╗тіАУи»тЙё):\n189\t\n190\t1. **удЂТГбТ▓ЎуЏњ**:СИЇтЙЌ `from cua import Sandbox`сђЂСИЇтЙЌ `Sandbox.ephemeral`сђЂСИЇтЙЌТІЅ Docker/Lume Т▓ЎуЏњсђѓтЇ│Сй┐ТюгТю║ти▓УБЁ Docker/conda,С╣Ъ**СИЇУдЂ**Тћ╣ућеТ▓ЎуЏњт«їТѕљтѕєТъљсђѓ\n191\t2. **ТАїжЮбСИјТхЈУДѕтЎе**:СИђтЙІ [cua-driver SKILL](../cua-driver/SKILL.md)(`launch_app`сђЂ`get_window_state`сђЂ`element_index` уѓ╣тЄ╗сђЂТѕфтЏЙ),СИЦт«ѕ **no-foreground**сђѓ\n192\t3. **т«ўуйЉ curl**:тЈ»тюе **host уѕХ shell** ТЅДУАї(тЈ»Ух░ућеТѕиС╗Буљє),ућеС║ј HTML у║┐у┤б;уюЪт«ъуѓ╣тЄ╗т»╝УѕфС╗ЇУх░ cua-driver ТхЈУДѕтЎесђѓ\n193\t4. **т«ЅУБЁтїЁ**:СИІУййтѕ░ `<output_dir>/downloads/`,тюе **host** т«ЅУБЁ(macOS/Linux/Windows тИИУДёТќ╣т╝Ј),уће cua-driver жЕ▒тіети▓т«ЅУБЁт║ћућесђѓ\n194\t5. **`metadata.mode`**:ТѕљтіЪТЌХтєЎ `full`,жЎЇу║ДтєЎ `web-only` Рђћ **СИЇУдЂ**тєЎ `sandbox-full`сђѓ\n195\t\n196\t## Sandbox У┐љУАїтљѕу║д\n197\t\n198\t**С╗ЁтйЊ** `runtime Рѕѕ {sandbox-local, sandbox-cloud}`(ТЅ╣жЄЈ `--batch`)ТЌХ,ТюгУіѓТЅЇТў»ТЮЃтеЂТ▓ЎуЏњУ»┤Тўјсђѓ`runtime=host` ТЌХ**Уи│У┐ЄТюгУіѓ**сђѓ\n199\t\n200\t### Т▓ЎуЏњТјДтѕХСИЅжўХТ«х(СИј host cua-driver жђљТГЦт»╣жйљ)\n201\t\n202\t| жўХТ«х | тЂџС╗ђС╣ѕ | удЂТГб |\n203\t|------|--------|------|\n204\t| **1. bootstrap(СИђТгА)** | тѕЏт╗║Т▓ЎуЏњсђЂтєЎ `<output_dir>/sandbox.json`сђЂтЈ»жђЅтљ»тіеТхЈУДѕтЎе | тюе bootstrap жЄї curl тЁеуФЎсђЂУБЁтїЁсђЂтєЎ `report.md` |\n205\t| **2. step loop(Т»ЈТГЦ)** | **screenshot Рєњ уюІтЏЙ Рєњ click/scroll/type/key Рєњ тєЇ screenshot** | уће shell ТхЈУДѕуйЉжАх;тЇЋСИф `asyncio.run()` тѕєТъљУёџТюг |\n206\t| **3. teardown(СИђТгА)** | жћђТ»ЂТ▓ЎуЏњ;у╝ќТјњтЎеС╣ЪтЈ»УЃйУЄфтіе teardown | Т│ёТ╝Ј Docker т«╣тЎе / Cloud VM |\n207\t\n208\t**observeРђЊact жЊЂтЙІ**:Т»ЈТгА GUI ТЊЇСйютЅЇтљјтљёСИђт╝аТѕфтЏЙУ┐Џ `screenshots/`;Уи»тЙётєЎУ┐ЏтйЊУй«Тјеуљє,тєЇтє│т«џСИІСИђТГЦтЮљТаЄсђѓ\n209\t\n210\t### Т▓ЎуЏњтєЁж╝аТаЄС╝ўтЁѕ(sandbox-local / sandbox-cloud)\n211\t\n212\tТ▓ЎуЏњТ▓АТюЅ host уџё AX ТаЉ,**тЮљТаЄу║Дж╝аТаЄ + жћ«уЏў**Тў»тћ»СИђтЈ»жЮауџё GUI Уи»тЙёсђѓж╗ўУ«цТЊЇСйюТаѕ(ТїЅжбЉујЄ):\n213\t\n214\t| С╝ўтЁѕу║Д | `sandbox_ctl` / MCP | ућежђћ |\n215\t|--------|---------------------|------|\n216\t| 1 | `step screenshot` | Т»ЈТГЦтЅЇтљјтЈќУ»Ђ |\n217\t| 2 | `step click` / `move` | уѓ╣ТїЅжњ«сђЂжЊЙТјЦсђЂтЁ│жЌГт╝╣уфЌ |\n218\t| 3 | `step scroll` | Т╗џУй«у┐╗жАх |\n219\t| 4 | `step type` / `step key` | УЙЊтЁЦТќЄтГЌ;жћ«тљЇућет░ЈтєЎ pynput тљЇ(`enter`/`esc`/`ctrl+l`,тІ┐уће `Return`/`Escape`/`Meta`) |\n220\t| 5 | `step open-url` / `bootstrap --url` | ТЅЊт╝ђт«ўуйЉ(жћ«уЏўУ┐Џтю░тЮђТаЈ,жЮъ wget) |\n221\t| ТюФСйЇ | `step shell -c '...'` | **С╗Ё**УДЂСИІТќ╣СЙІтцќ |\n222\t\n223\t**`step shell` тЈфтЁЂУ«ИУ┐ЎС║Џтю║ТЎ»**(тЁХСйЎСИђтЙІж╝аТаЄТхЂ):\n224\t\n225\t1. **bootstrap ТЌХтљ»тіе Firefox СИђТгА**(Linux `cua-xfce` тЈфТюЅ Firefox;УёџТюгтєЁжЃети▓тЂџ;СйаСИЇУдЂТЅІтєЎ `chromium` ТѕќжЋ┐ shell жЊЙ)\n226\t2. **ти▓ТюЅуЏ┤жЊЙ**ТЌХ `wget -O <output_dir>/downloads/...` СИІУййт«ЅУБЁтїЁ/APK(СИІт«їтљјС╗Їућеж╝аТаЄт«ЅУБЁ/ТЅЊт╝ђ)\n227\t3. `dpkg -i` / `chmod +x` уГЅ**у║»т«ЅУБЁтЉйС╗ц**(ТЌа GUI ТЌХ)\n228\t4. У»╗ `/proc`сђЂ`uname` уГЅ**СИЇТЏ┐С╗БуЋїжЮбСйЊжфї**уџёТјбТхІ\n229\t\n230\t**удЂТГб**:уће `curl|wget|python3` ТіЊт«ўуйЉ HTML тйЊ step 2/3 СИ╗Уи»тЙё;уће shell тљ»тіеТхЈУДѕтЎетљјСИЇтєЇ `click` уѓ╣уЋїжЮбсђѓ\n231\t\n232\tтЁИтъІт╝ђт▒ђ:\n233\t\n234\t```bash\n235\tpython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py bootstrap \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" --open-browser --url \"$URL\"\n236\tpython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step screenshot \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" --out screenshots/01_web_homepage.png\n237\tpython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step key \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" esc          # тЁ│ Firefox у┐╗У»Љ/cookie т╝╣уфЌ;тЈ»У┐ъТїЅСИцТгА\n238\tpython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step click \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" 640 120    # уц║СЙІ:тЁ│ cookie(т╝╣уфЌС╗ЇтюетѕЎтєЇ click)\n239\tpython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step scroll \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" 512 400 --scroll-y -8\n240\tpython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step screenshot \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" --out screenshots/02_web_after_scroll.png\n241\t```\n242\t\n243\tтЮљТаЄТЮЦУЄф**СИіСИђт╝аТѕфтЏЙ**уџёуЏ«ТхІ;тЈ»тЁѕ `step screen-size` уЪЦтѕєУЙеујЄ(жђџтИИ 1024├Ќ768)сђѓ\n244\t\n245\t#### `sandbox_ctl` Рєћ Cua SDK / computer-server тЦЉу║д\n246\t\n247\tТЅ╣жЄЈ worker жђџУ┐Є `sandbox_ctl` У░Ѓуће [Cua Sandbox SDK](https://cua.ai/docs/cua/reference/sandbox-sdk)(`Sandbox.connect` Рєњ `mouse`/`keyboard`/`screen`/`shell`)сђѓ**SDK ТќЄТАБуц║СЙІСИј Docker тєЁ computer-server(pynput) уџёжћ«тљЇ/Т╗џУй«У»ГС╣ЅСИЇт«їтЁеСИђУЄ┤** Рђћ СИІтѕЌУДётѕЎти▓тюе `scripts/product_analyzer/sandbox_ctl.py` жЄїтЂџтйњСИђтїќ/workaround;Claude ТїЅ CLI ућеТ│ЋтЇ│тЈ»,СИЇт┐ЁуЏ┤ТјЦ `import cua` тЈЉтЉйС╗цсђѓ\n248\t\n249\t**У┐ъТјЦ**: bootstrap тєЎтЁЦ `<output_dir>/sandbox.json` уџё `api_url`;тљју╗Г `step` уће `Sandbox.connect(..., http_url=api_url)` уЏ┤У┐ъ computer-server(Тюгтю░/С║ЉуФ»тЮЄжђѓуће)сђѓ\n250\t\n251\t**жћ«уЏў(`step key`)** Рђћ тєЁжЃеТўат░ётѕ░ pynput `Key.*` тљЇ;тИИућетєЎТ│Ћ:\n252\t\n253\t| ТёЈтЏЙ | ТГБуА« CLI | тІ┐уће(С╝џ Remote error) |\n254\t|------|----------|------------------------|\n255\t| Esc тЁ│т╝╣уфЌ/УЈютЇЋ | `esc` Тѕќ `escape`(тйњСИђтїќСИ║ `esc`) | `Escape` |\n256\t| тЏъУйд | `enter` | `Return` |\n257\t| у╗ётљѕжћ« | `ctrl+l`сђЂ`ctrl+alt+t` | `Control+L`сђЂ`Meta+Рђд` |\n258\t| Super/Win | `cmd` / `super`(тйњСИђтїќСИ║ `cmd`) | `meta` |\n259\t| у┐╗жАхжћ« | `page_down` / `page_up` | `PageDown`сђЂ`pgdn` |\n260\t| тѕажЎц | `delete` | `del` тЈ»,`Del` тІ┐ |\n261\t\n262\tтЇЋжћ«Ух░ `press_key`,у╗ётљѕжћ«Ух░ `hotkey`(СИј SDK `Keyboard.keypress` СИђУЄ┤)сђѓ\n263\t\n264\t**Т╗џУй«(`step scroll`)** Рђћ SDK `Mouse.scroll(x,y,scroll_x,scroll_y)` у╗Ј HTTP тѕ░ Linux handler ТЌХС╝џТіі `x/y` У»»тйЊТ╗џУй«тбъжЄЈт╣ХСИбт╝Ѓ `scroll_x/scroll_y`(СИіТИИ bug)сђѓ`sandbox_ctl` ти▓ workaround:**тЁѕ `move` тѕ░ `(x,y)`,тєЇ `scroll_down`/`scroll_up`(ТїЅ `--scroll-y` угдтЈи)**сђѓућеТ│ЋСИЇтЈў:\n265\t\n266\t```bash\n267\tpython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step scroll \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" 512 400 --scroll-y -8\n268\t```\n269\t\n270\t- Т╗џУй«тЅЇуА«С┐Юуёдуѓ╣тюежАхжЮбтєЁт«╣тї║(тЁѕ `click` ТГБТќЄТѕќ `esc` тЁ│т╝╣уфЌ);**ТАїжЮбтЏътйњТЌХ scroll т║ћтюе right-click С╣ІтЅЇ**,жЂ┐тЁЇтЈ│жћ«УЈютЇЋТїАСйЈТ╗џтіесђѓ\n271\t- УІЦТѕфтЏЙС╗ЇТЌаТ╗џтіетЈўтїќ:жЎЇу║Д `step key page_down`(тЈ»У┐ъТїЅ 2РђЊ3 ТгА)тєЇ screenshotсђѓ\n272\t\n273\t**тЁХт«Ѓ step СИј SDK т»╣жйљТЃЁтєх**:\n274\t\n275\t| step | SDK | У»┤Тўј |\n276\t|------|-----|------|\n277\t| `screenshot` | `sb.screenshot()` | РюЊ |\n278\t| `screen-size` | `sb.screen.size()` | РюЊ |\n279\t| `move` / `click` | `mouse.move` / `click` / `right_click` / `double_click` | РюЊ |\n280\t| `type` | `keyboard.type` | РюЊ |\n281\t| `shell` | `shell.run` | С╗Ёт«ЅУБЁ/ТјбТхІ,СИЇТЏ┐С╗БТхЈУДѕ |\n282\t| `open-url` | `keyboard` т»╝Уѕф | тѕ╗ТёЈСИЇућеТхЈУДѕтЎе MCP;`ctrl+l` Рєњ type URL Рєњ `enter` |\n283\t\n284\tжфїУ»ЂУёџТюг:`python -m tests.sandbox.sandbox_ctl_smoke`(browser + ТАїжЮбжћ«ж╝атЏътйњ;ТѕфтЏЙтюе `tmp/sandbox-ctl-smoke/screenshots/`)сђѓ\n285\t\n286\t#### Linux ТАїжЮб (`trycua/cua-xfce`)\n287\t\n288\t- жЋютЃЈ**тЈфжбёУБЁ Firefox**,Т▓АТюЅ Chromiumсђѓ`bootstrap --open-browser` / `step open-url` С╝џућ▒ `sandbox_ctl` ТјбТхІ `DISPLAY`(У»╗ `/tmp/.X11-unix`,тИИУДЂ **`:1`**,тІ┐тєЎТГ╗ `:0`)т╣Хтљ»тіе Firefox,тєЇуће `ctrl+l` Рєњ УЙЊтЁЦ URL Рєњ `enter`сђѓ\n289\t- **`bootstrap` С╝џУЄфтіетЁ│жЌГ XFCE С╝Љуюа/т▒ЈС┐Ю**(`xset`сђЂ`xfce4-power-manager`сђЂ`screensaver`);Claude **СИЇУдЂ**тєЇТЅІтіеУиЉућхТ║љу«АуљєтЉйС╗ц,жЎцжЮъТѕфтЏЙС╗Їж╗Љт▒Јсђѓ\n290\t- **удЂТГб**Тіі `chromium Рђд`сђЂ`apt install chromium` тйЊСИ╗Уи»тЙё;С╝џтц▒У┤ЦТѕќТхфУ┤╣ТЌХжЌ┤сђѓ\n291\t- УІЦ bootstrap тљјтЈфТюЅуЕ║уЎйт░ЈуфЌ/жЮбТЮ┐:тЁѕ `step screenshot`,тєЇ **click** С╗╗тіАТаЈ Firefox тЏЙТаЄ,Тѕќ `step open-url \"$URL\"`(Firefox ти▓УиЉтѕЎтіа `--no-launch`)сђѓ\n292\t- т«ўуйЉт»╝УѕфсђЂCookieсђЂСИІУйй hunt тЮЄтюе **Firefox уфЌтЈБтєЁ**ућеж╝аТаЄ + жћ«уЏўт«їТѕљсђѓ\n293\t\n294\t#### тЈЇТеАт╝Ј(ТўјуА«удЂТГб)\n295\t\n296\t- тєЎСИђСИф `analyze_*.py` / `run_analysis.py`,тюежЄїУЙ╣ `async with Sandbox.ephemeral` УиЉт«їтЁежЃетѕєТъљсђѓ\n297\t- bootstrap УёџТюгжЄїтїЁтљФ step 3РђЊ7 уџёСИџтіАжђ╗УЙЉсђѓ\n298\t- уће host уѕХ shell `curl` С╗БТЏ┐Т▓ЎуЏњтєЁУ»ЂТЇ«(`ANALYZER_BATCH_PARALLEL=1` ТЌХ)сђѓ\n299\t\n300\t#### Тюгтю░ (`sandbox-local`) Рђћ С╝ўтЁѕ `sandbox_ctl`\n301\t\n302\tу╝ќТјњтЎеТЈљСЙЏУќё CLI(conda уј»тбЃ `python`,тІ┐ућеу│╗у╗Ъ 3.9):\n303\t\n304\t```bash\n305\tconda activate computer-use-py312   # Тѕќ $ANALYZER_CONDA_ENV\n306\tREPO=...                            # С╗Њт║ЊТа╣уЏ«тйЋ\n307\t\n308\t# 1) bootstrap + ућежћ«уЏўТЅЊт╝ђт«ўуйЉ(жЮъ wget)\n309\tpython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py bootstrap \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" --open-browser --url \"$URL\"\n310\t\n311\t# 2) ж╝аТаЄС╝ўтЁѕ loop Рђћ Т»ЈТГЦСИђТЮА;тЁѕуюІтЏЙтєЇт«џтЮљТаЄ\n312\tpython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step screenshot \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" --out screenshots/01_web_homepage.png\n313\tpython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step key \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" esc            # тЁ│т╝╣уфЌ\n314\tpython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step click \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" 512 380\n315\tpython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step scroll \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" 512 400 --scroll-y -6\n316\tpython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step screenshot \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" --out screenshots/02_web_pricing.png\n317\t# С╗ЁтйЊТюЅуЏ┤жЊЙСИІУййт«ЅУБЁтїЁТЌХ:\n318\t# python scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step shell \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" -c 'wget -q -O ...'\n319\t\n320\t# 3) teardown\n321\tpython \"$REPO/scripts/sandbox_ctl.py\" teardown \"$OUTPUT_DIR\"\n322\t```\n323\t\n324\t`<output_dir>/sandbox.json` тЦЉу║д( bootstrap тєЎтЁЦ,тІ┐ТЅІТћ╣):\n325\t\n326\t```json\n327\t{\n328\t  \"name\": \"analyzer-babbel-2026-05-19\",\n329\t  \"provider\": \"docker\",\n330\t  \"api_url\": \"http://127.0.0.1:PORT\",\n331\t  \"image\": \"trycua/cua-xfce:latest\",\n332\t  \"platform\": \"linux/amd64\",\n333\t  \"local\": true\n334\t}\n335\t```\n336\t\n337\t- Сй┐уће **`Sandbox.create(..., ephemeral=False, name=...)`**,С╗ЦСЙ┐ `~/.cua/sandboxes/` ТюЅуіХТђЂ;**СИЇУдЂ**уће `Sandbox.ephemeral` тЂџ batch СИ╗Т▓ЎуЏњсђѓ\n338\t- **тцЄжђЅ**:`cua do switch docker <sandbox.json.name>` тљј `cua do screenshot` / `click`(СИј `sandbox_ctl` С║їжђЅСИђ;**С╝ўтЁѕ `sandbox_ctl`**,СИЇСЙЮУхќ Claude У«░ port)сђѓ\n339\t- `sandbox_ctl status \"$OUTPUT_DIR\"` Тјњжџюсђѓ\n340\t- **Т▓ЎуЏњтєЁТЌа curl** ТЌХ:т«ўуйЉС╗Їуће **ж╝аТаЄТхЈУДѕ**;`wget` тЈфућеС║ј**ти▓ТюЅ URL**уџёт«ЅУБЁтїЁСИІУйй,СИЇућеС║јТіЊждќжАх HTMLсђѓ\n341\t- **`step shell` тц▒У┤ЦТѕќ Bash уюІСИЇтѕ░УЙЊтЄ║**:У»╗ `$OUTPUT_DIR/.sandbox_ctl_last_shell.json`;СИЇУдЂУЄфтєЎ `/tmp/sb_run.py` ТЏ┐С╗Б(жЎцжЮъ `sandbox_ctl` ТюгУ║ФТіЦжћЎ)сђѓ\n342\t\n343\t#### С║ЉуФ» (`sandbox-cloud`) Рђћ С╝ўтЁѕ Cua MCP\n344\t\n345\tу╝ќТјњтЎеС╝џСИ║ worker Т│етЁЦ `claude --mcp-config`( `cua serve-mcp` )сђѓжђљТГЦСй┐уће:\n346\t\n347\t- `computer_screenshot` / `computer_click` / `computer_type` / `computer_shell` уГЅ\n348\t- **удЂТГб**уће host Bash ТЊЇСйюТ▓ЎуЏњ GUI\n349\t- MCP У┐ћтЏъуџёТѕфтЏЙУІЦТюфУЄфтіеУљйуЏў,**т┐ЁжА╗** `Write` тѕ░ `<output_dir>/screenshots/NN_*.png` тєЇУ»╗тЏЙтѕєТъљ\n350\t- С╗ЇтЈ»уће `sandbox_ctl bootstrap` + `step`(cloud) Сйю MCP СИЇтЈ»ућеТЌХуџёжЎЇу║Д\n351\t\n352\t**СИЇУдЂ**Сй┐уће `ComputerAgent(tools=[sb])` тхїтЦЌ agent Рђћ СИјтйЊтЅЇ `claude --print` ТхЂТ░┤у║┐жЄЇтцЇсђѓ\n353\t\n354\t### Тђ╗тјЪтѕЎ\n355\t\n356\t1. **ТЊЇСйюу│╗у╗Ъу║ДтиЦСйютЈфтюеТ▓ЎуЏњтєЁ**сђѓ**удЂТГб** cua-driverсђЂhost `open`/`osascript`сђЂТюгТю║ТхЈУДѕтЎе/ТАїжЮб GUIсђѓ\n357\t2. **host С╗Ё**:У░Ѓуће `sandbox_ctl` / MCP / У»╗тєЎ `<output_dir>` С║ДуЅЕсђѓ\n358\t3. **Т»ЈСИфС║ДтЊЂуІгуФІ sandbox**;удЂТГбтцЇућетЁХт«Ѓ `reports/` С╗╗тіАуџёУ┐ъТјЦсђѓ\n359\t\n360\t### Host СЙД Python / CLI\n361\t\n362\t- Cua Sandbox SDK **С╗ЁТћ»ТїЂ Python 3.12 Тѕќ 3.13**;`sandbox_ctl` СИј `import cua` т┐ЁжА╗уће conda уј»тбЃ(У»╗ `ANALYZER_CONDA_ENV`,ж╗ўУ«ц `computer-use-py312`)сђѓ\n363\t- ТЅ╣жЄЈжбёТБђУдЂТ▒ѓ `cua` CLI тюе PATH(`cua --version`)сђѓ\n364\t- Т▓ЎуЏњ**тєЁ** shell ућет«╣тЎетєЁ `python3`(тЅЦ HTML уГЅ);СИј host SDK уЅѕТюгТЌатЁ│сђѓ\n365\t\n366\t### ТЅ╣жЄЈт╣ХУАї(`batch.parallel=true` Тѕќ `ANALYZER_BATCH_PARALLEL=1`)\n367\t\n368\t- уІгуФІ worker;т«ўуйЉСИј GUI У»ЂТЇ«т┐ЁжА╗ТЮЦУЄфТ▓ЎуЏњсђѓ\n369\t- жЎцУ»╗тєЎтйЊтЅЇ `<output_dir>` тцќ,СИЇтЙЌТіі host тйЊтѕєТъљуј»тбЃсђѓ\n370\t\n371\t### жЋютЃЈ\n372\t\n373\t| `sandbox.image` | Тюгтю░ | У»┤Тўј |\n374\t|-----------------|------|------|\n375\t| `linux` | `trycua/cua-xfce:latest` + `linux/amd64` | `sandbox_ctl bootstrap` ж╗ўУ«ц |\n376\t| `macos` | Lume | bootstrap ТїЅ image жђЅУ┐љУАїТЌХ(УІЦТюфт«ъуј░тѕЎ warnings) |\n377\t| `windows` | QEMU Docker | тљїСИі |\n378\t| `auto` | С╝ўтЁѕ linux т«╣тЎетЂџуйЉжАх | |\n379\t\n380\t- У»╗ `ANALYZER_LINUX_CONTAINER_IMAGE` / `ANALYZER_LINUX_DOCKER_PLATFORM`сђѓ\n381\t- С║ЉуФ»:ућ▒ `CUA_API_KEY` Т│етЁЦ;**тІ┐тєЎтЁЦ metadata**сђѓ\n382\t\n383\t### SDK ТЋ┤УёџТюгуц║СЙІ(smoke/CI СИЊуће,жЮъ batch agent ж╗ўУ«ц)\n384\t\n385\t[`tests/sandbox/linux_smoke.py`](../../tests/sandbox/linux_smoke.py) уће `Sandbox.ephemeral` жфїУ»ЂжЊЙУи» Рђћ **СИЇУдЂ**уЁДТіётѕ░С║ДтЊЂтѕєТъљ Bash жЄїсђѓ\n386\t\n387\t### Android APK(тЈ»жђЅ)\n388\t\n389\t- С╗Ё `android.enabled=true` **СИћ** Android Т▓ЎуЏњТѕљтіЪтљ»тіеТЌХ;**уІгуФІ** Android sandbox(`sandbox_ctl` Тѕќ SDK),ТѕфтЏЙ `NN_android_*.png`сђѓ\n390\t- жЋютЃЈ **`trycua/cua-qemu-android:latest`**сђѓ\n391\t\n392\t### Android Тюфтљ»ућеТѕќТюфтљ»тіе\n393\t\n394\tТ╗АУХ│**С╗╗СИђ**ТЮАС╗ХТЌХ,**удЂТГб**тѕЏт╗║/У┐ъТјЦ Android Т▓ЎуЏњ(ТЌа `Image.android()`сђЂТЌа `cua-qemu-android`сђЂТЌа `adb install`):\n395\t\n396\t- prompt / `metadata.android.enabled` СИ║ **`false`**(ТЅ╣жЄЈТюфтіа `--android`,Тѕќ `--no-android`)\n397\t- Android жЋютЃЈТюфТІЅтЈќсђЂ`Sandbox.create` тц▒У┤ЦсђЂadb/QEMU СИЇтЈ»уће\n398\t- ти▓т░ЮУ»Ћтљ»тіе Android Т▓ЎуЏњСйєУХЁТЌХТѕќтц▒У┤Ц\n399\t\n400\tТГцТЌХ**т┐ЁжА╗**:\n401\t\n402\t1. **тЈф**тюеуј░ТюЅ **Linux ТАїжЮбТ▓ЎуЏњ + Firefox** тєЁТхЈУДѕт«ўуйЉ,уће `screenshot` Рєњ `click`/`scroll`/`type`/`key` УјитЈќС║ДтЊЂС┐АТЂ»(т«џСйЇсђЂтіЪУЃйсђЂт«џС╗исђЂUI/UXсђЂт«ўуйЉТќЄТАѕ)сђѓ\n403\t2. С╗Ц `screenshots/NN_web_*.png` СИ║СИ╗УдЂу┤аТЮљ,ТїЅСИіТќЄ **5.B уйЉжАхТеАт╝Ј** уџётіЏт║дУх░т«ўуйЉтљётЁЦтЈБ(ждќжАхсђЂт«џС╗исђЂтіЪУЃйсђЂFAQ уГЅ)сђѓ\n404\t3. тЈ»тюеуйЉжАхСИіУ«░тйЋ Google Play / APK жЊЙТјЦтѕ░ `metadata.warnings[]`,**СИЇ**СИІУййсђЂСИЇУБЁ APKсђѓ\n405\t4. У«Йуй« `metadata.android.mode = \"skipped\"`,`warnings[]` тєЎТИЁтдѓ `\"android: sandbox not started; web-only product path\"`сђѓ\n406\t5. **СИЇУдЂ**тЏаТГцТііТЋ┤тЇЋ `metadata.mode` Тћ╣Тѕљ `web-only` Рђћ жЎцжЮъ [Уиет╣│тЈ░СИјжЎЇу║Д](#Уиет╣│тЈ░СИјжЎЇу║Д) жЄїТАїжЮбт«ЅУБЁтїЁ hunt С╣Ъти▓тц▒У┤ЦсђѓТ▓ЎуЏњтєЁсђїтЈфтЂџуйЉжАхсђЇРЅа тЁет▒ђ web-only жЎЇу║Дсђѓ\n407\t\n408\t### Т▓ЎуЏњтєЁ GUI / уйЉжАх\n409\t\n410\t- С╗Ц **ж╝аТаЄС╝ўтЁѕ**УіѓСИ║тЄє;Т»ЈТГЦ `step screenshot` УљйуЏўсђѓ\n411\t- тцЇТЮѓ SPA / уЎ╗тйЋтбЎ:У«░тЁЦ `warnings[]`,тІ┐у╗ЋУ┐ЄуЎ╗тйЋсђѓ\n412\t\n413\t## ТіЦтЉіТеАТЮ┐УдЂТ▒ѓ\n414\t\n415\tтЈѓУДЂ [REPORT_TEMPLATE.md](REPORT_TEMPLATE.md)сђѓУдЂуѓ╣:\n416\t\n417\t- **т┐ЁТюЅуФаУіѓ(жА║т║ЈСИЇУЃйтЈў)**:`Тђ╗т«џСйЇ` Рєњ `уЋїжЮбТИЁтЇЋ` Рєњ `тљёуЋїжЮбтіЪУЃйСИјУ»ёС╗и` Рєњ `UI/UX` Рєњ `т«ўуйЉТЈЈУ┐░` Рєњ `жЎётйЋ A ТѕфтЏЙу┤бт╝Ћ`\n418\t- **тЈ»жђЅуФаУіѓ**(`т«џС╗и / уЏ«ТаЄућеТѕи / тљїу▒╗т»╣Т»ћ / С╝ўтіБті┐т░Ју╗Њ`):ТюЅУ»ЂТЇ«ТЅЇтєЎ,ТЌатѕЎТЋ┤Т«хтѕа,**СИЇУдЂуЋЎ\"С┐АТЂ»СИЇУХ│\"тЇаСйЇ**\n419\t- **Т»ЈСИфУ»ёС╗ит┐ЁжА╗тЈ»У»ЂС╝ф**:СИЇтєЎ\"ТхЂуЋЁ\"сђЂ\"уЙјУДѓ\",тєЎ\"тљ»тіетѕ░ждќт▒Ју║д 0.8s,ТЌатіаУййтіеућ╗\"Тѕќ\"СИ╗ CTA ућеу┤ФУЅ▓тАФтЁЁТїЅжњ«СйЇС║јждќт▒ЈтЈ│СИІ,СИјУЃїТЎ»т»╣Т»ћт║дТ╗АУХ│ WCAG AA\"\n420\t- **т«ўуйЉтјЪТќЄућет╝ЋтЈит╝Ћуће**(СИЇУдЂТёЈУ»Љ),УіѓТаЄжбўТЌЂТаЄ\"тјЪТќЄжћџ:ждќжАх H1\"С╣Іу▒╗уџёСйЇуй«С┐АТЂ»\n421\t\n422\t## Уиет╣│тЈ░СИјжЎЇу║Д\n423\t\n424\thost runtime уџёТАїжЮбжЕ▒тіетљјуФ» OS уЪЕжўхућ▒ `scripts/install_cua_driver.py` тє│т«џ:\n425\t- macOS arm64 / x86_64 Рєњ Swift `cua-driver`\n426\t- Linux x86_64 Рєњ `cua-driver-rs`\n427\t- Windows x86_64 Рєњ `cua-driver-rs` (PowerShell т«ЅУБЁ)\n428\t- Linux aarch64 Рєњ ТЌажбёу╝ќУ»Љ Рєњ УЄфтіе web-only\n429\t\n430\tsandbox-local runtime уџёТАїжЮб/Android уЪЕжўхућ▒ Cua Sandbox SDK тњїТюгтю░У┐љУАїТЌХтє│т«џ:\n431\t- Linux sandbox Рєњ Docker\n432\t- macOS sandbox Рєњ Lume\n433\t- Windows sandbox Рєњ QEMU\n434\t- Android sandbox Рєњ Android SDK(emulator + platform-tools)Тѕќ QEMU\n435\t\n436\tsandbox-cloud runtime ућ▒ Cua Cloud ТЅўу«А VM/т«╣тЎе;`sandbox.image` жђЅТІЕ linux / macos / windowsсђѓСИЇжюђУдЂТюгТю║ Docker/Lume жбёТБђ,СйєжюђУдЂТюЅТЋѕуџё `CUA_API_KEY`(ти▓ућ▒ orchestrator Т│етЁЦ,тІ┐тєЎтЁЦ metadata)сђѓ\n437\t\n438\tжЎЇу║Дтѕ░ `mode: \"web-only\"` уџёУДдтЈЉТЮАС╗Х,тЈфТюЅУ┐ЎСИЅуДЇ:\n439\t1. С║ДтЊЂт«ўуйЉТ▓АтЄ║тйЊтЅЇСИ╗Тю║ OS уџёт«ЅУБЁтїЁ(тдѓ ProductiveKitty Т▓А Linux уЅѕ,УђїСйатюе Linux СИ╗Тю║СИі)\n440\t2. тйЊтЅЇСИ╗Тю║т╣│тЈ░Т▓АТюЅ cua-driver жбёу╝ќУ»Љ(Linux aarch64)\n441\t3. т║ћућет«ЅУБЁ/тљ»тіетц▒У┤Ц / тЈЇтцЇжЌфжђђ\n442\t\n443\tжЎЇу║ДТЌХ:\n444\t- `metadata.json.mode = \"web-only\"`\n445\t- batch sandbox ТѕљтіЪжЕ▒тіеТАїжЮбуФ»ТЌХ `metadata.json.mode = \"sandbox-full\"`;ТЅЙтѕ░т╣ХТѕљтіЪСйЊжфї APK ТЌХ `metadata.android.mode = \"android\"`\n446\t- тюе `metadata.json.warnings[]` тіаСИђТЮАтйбтдѓ `\"web-only: no macos package found at <url>\"`\n447\t- ТіЦтЉітц┤уџётЁЃС┐АТЂ»УАе\"ТеАт╝Ј\"тѕЌтАФ `web-only`,т╣ХтюеУАеСИІућеСИђтЈЦУ»ЮУ»┤ТўјжЎЇу║ДтјЪтЏа\n448\t- ТіЦтЉітЁХС╗ќжЃетѕєуЁДтИИтєЎ,тЈфТў» ┬Д1 С╗ЁтЪ║С║јт«ўуйЉ + ТхЈУДѕтЎеТѕфтЏЙ,жЋ┐т║дтЈ»УЃйТ»ћ full ТеАт╝ЈуЪГ\n449\t\n450\t## тц▒У┤ЦтцёуљєСИјтЇЄу║Д\n451\t\n452\t- **AX ТаЉСИ║уЕ║ / Electron canvas / WebView2 т║ћуће** Рєњ ТїЅ [cua-driver SKILL](../cua-driver/SKILL.md) уџё escalation СИђУіѓтцёуљє(ТБђТхІ webviewсђЂт┐ЁУдЂТЌХ vision тЁют║Ћ)сђѓТюг skill СИЇтцЇУ┐░У┐ЎС║ЏУДётѕЎ\n453\t- **т║ћућетљ»тіежЌфжђђ** Рєњ Тѕфт▒Јт┤ЕТ║Ѓт»╣У»ЮТАє,У«░тйЋу│╗у╗ЪТЌЦт┐ЌУи»тЙё(macOS:`~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`,Linux:`journalctl --user-unit`),`┬Д1.3` ТаЄ\"У»ЦуЋїжЮбтЏат┤ЕТ║ЃТюфУЃйжЄЄжЏє\",жЎЇу║Дтѕ░т░йжЄЈтцџуџётЈ»УЙЙуЋїжЮб\n454\t- **уЎ╗тйЋтбЎ** Рєњ СИЇу╗ЋУ┐ЄсђЂСИЇтѕЏт╗║У┤дтЈисђѓУЃйжЄЄжЏєуџё:ждќжАхсђЂт«џС╗исђЂТќЄТАБсђЂтЇџт«бсђЂChangelog;`metadata.json.warnings[]` тіа `\"login-required: feature pages not analyzed\"`,ТіЦтЉітц┤Т│еТўј\"ТюфуЎ╗тйЋТђЂтѕєТъљ\"\n455\t- **тЇЋТГЦ 30s УХЁТЌХ** Рђћ Уи│У┐ЄУ»ЦТГЦ,`metadata.json.warnings[]` У«░тйЋ,у╗Ду╗ГСИІСИђТГЦ;СИЇУдЂТЌажЎљуГЅ\n456\t- **СИІУйй/т«ЅУБЁТЮЃжЎљтЈЌжў╗**(/Applications СИЇтЈ»тєЎсђЂSIP тЇАтюе quarantine уГЅ)Рєњ У«░тйЋтјЪтЏа,жЎЇу║Д web-only\n457\t\n458\t## жБјТа╝т«ѕтѕЎ\n459\t\n460\t- **ТіЦтЉітЁеуеІСИГТќЄ**(у«ђСйЊ)\n461\t- **СИЇтцИт╝а**:СИЇуће\"т«їуЙј\"сђЂ\"ТЃіУЅ│\"сђЂ\"жбаУдє\"сђѓС║Іт«ъжЎѕУ┐░ + СИђСИцтЈЦУ»ёС╗ит░▒тцЪ\n462\t- **СИЇтњїуеђТ│Ц**:С║ДтЊЂТюЅжЌ«жбўт░▒тєЎ,СйєУдЂУљйтѕ░тЁиСйЊу╗єУіѓ,СИЇУдЂТ│ЏТ│ЏТЅ╣У»ё\n463\t- **тЈ»У»ЂС╝ф**:Т»ЈСИфУ»ёС╗иТїЄтљЉТѕфтЏЙТѕќт«ўуйЉтјЪТќЄсђѓУ»╗УђЁТЅФСИђую╝УЃй follow back to evidence\n464\t\n465\t## СИј cua-driver / Cua Sandbox SDK уџётЁ│у│╗\n466\t\n467\tТюг skill У┤ЪУ┤Б\"тѕєТъљС╗ђС╣ѕсђЂС║ДтЄ║С╗ђС╣ѕ\"сђѓhost runtime СИІ,ТЅђТюЅ\"тдѓСйЋжЕ▒тіеТАїжЮбуФ»\"уџётЁиСйЊУДётѕЎ(snapshot СИЇтЈўжЄЈсђЂno-foreground тЦЉу║дсђЂтЮљТаЄу│╗сђЂescalation жўХТб»сђЂт╣│тЈ░ти«т╝ѓ)жЃйтюе [.claude/skills/cua-driver/SKILL.md](../cua-driver/SKILL.md)сђѓ**СИЇУдЂтюеУ┐ЎжЄїтцЇУ┐░,тЈфтюетиЦСйюСИГжЂхт«ѕ**сђѓ\n468\t\n469\tsandbox-local / sandbox-cloud runtime СИІ,Т▓ЎуЏњТЊЇСйюУДётѕЎС╗Ц**Тюг skillсђїSandbox У┐љУАїтљѕу║дсђЇ**СИ║тЄє(СИЇтюе prompt жЄїжЄЇтцЇ)сђѓhost runtime СИІТАїжЮбжЕ▒тіеС╗ЇС╗Ц [cua-driver SKILL](../cua-driver/SKILL.md) СИ║тЄєсђѓ\n470\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9ae2b347-5aa4-4079-9d46-d9fc7aba3cef","uuid":"852ede3a-4f54-4645-a08c-ae2535b8eb06","timestamp":"2026-05-21T20:28:38.197Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/zhiwei/projects/computer-use/.claude/skills/product-analyzer/SKILL.md","content":"---\nname: product-analyzer\ndescription: у╗Ўт«џС║ДтЊЂтљЇтњїт«ўуйЉ URL,С║ДтЄ║тљФСИЅСИфт╝║тѕХуФаУіѓ(С║ДтЊЂжђ╗УЙЉ/UIUX/т«ўуйЉТЈЈУ┐░)уџёСИГТќЄ Markdown С║ДтЊЂтѕєТъљТіЦтЉіСИјжЁЇтЦЌТѕфтЏЙТќЄС╗Хтц╣сђѓС╝ўтЁѕжЕ▒тіеТАїжЮбуФ»;ТАїжЮбуФ»СИЇтЈ»ућеТЌХУЄфтіежЎЇу║Д web-onlyсђѓУДдтЈЉТќ╣т╝Ј:scripts/analyze_product.py У░Ѓуће,Тѕќт»╣У»ЮСИГ\"тѕєТъљ/ТІєУДБ/У»ёТхІ/У░Ѓуаћ У┐ЎСИфС║ДтЊЂ https://...\"у▒╗У»иТ▒ѓСИћтїЁтљФ URLсђѓ\n---\n\n# product-analyzer\n\nТіі\"тѕєТъљСИђСИфТќ░С║ДтЊЂ\"У┐ЎС╗ХС║ІтЏ║тїќТѕљСИђТЮАтЈ»жЄЇтцЇТхЂТ░┤у║┐сђѓТ»ЈТгАУиЉжЃйС║ДтЄ║СИђС╗йу╗ЊТъёуе│т«џуџёТіЦтЉі + СИђу╗ётИдтЉйтљЇУДётѕЎуџёТѕфтЏЙ,Тќ╣СЙ┐т»╣тцќТЈљС║цсђЂтйњТАБсђЂУиеС║ДтЊЂТефтљЉТ»ћУЙЃсђѓ\n\n## тиЦСйюТеАт╝Ј\n\n- **т«їТЋ┤ТеАт╝Ј (full)**:ТіЊт«ўуйЉ Рєњ ТЅЙтЄ║тйЊтЅЇСИ╗Тю║УЃйућеуџёт«ЅУБЁтїЁ Рєњ УБЁтЦйжЕ▒тіетЎе(`scripts/install_cua_driver.py`)Рєњ тљ»тіеС║ДтЊЂ Рєњ уће **cua-driver** ТЊЇСйюСИ╗УдЂуЋїжЮб Рєњ ТЅ╣жЄЈТѕфтЏЙ Рєњ ТЋ┤тљѕтєЎТіЦтЉісђѓ**С╗Ё `runtime=host` тЇЋС╗╗тіА**Ух░ТГцУи»тЙёсђѓ\n- **Т▓Ўу«▒т«їТЋ┤ТеАт╝Ј (sandbox-full)**:**С╗ЁТЅ╣жЄЈ** (`runtime=sandbox-local` / `sandbox-cloud`)сђѓуће Cua Sandbox SDK тюеТ▓ЎуЏњтєЁт«їТѕљтѕєТъљ;`metadata.mode` СИ║ `sandbox-full`сђѓтЇЋС╗╗тіА**СИЇтЙЌ**Сй┐ућесђѓ\n- **Android ТеАт╝Ј (android)**:**С╗ЁТ▓ЎуЏњТЅ╣жЄЈ**СИћ `android.enabled=true` **СИћ Android Т▓ЎуЏњТѕљтіЪтљ»тіе**ТЌХуџётбът╝║жА╣сђѓТюфтљ»ућеТѕќТ▓ЎуЏњТюфУхиТЌХ**тЈфТЊЇСйюуйЉжАх**(Firefox),С╗јт«ўуйЉУјитЈќС║ДтЊЂС┐АТЂ»,УДЂ [Android Тюфтљ»ућеТѕќТюфтљ»тіе](#android-Тюфтљ»ућеТѕќТюфтљ»тіе)сђѓ\n- **уйЉжАхТеАт╝Ј (web-only)**:С╗ЁтЪ║С║јт«ўуйЉС┐АТЂ» + ТхЈУДѕтЎеТѕфтЏЙсђѓС╗ЁтюеТАїжЮбжЕ▒тіеСИЇтЈ»УЙЙТЌХтљ»уће Рђћ УДЂСИІТќЄ\"Уиет╣│тЈ░СИјжЎЇу║Д\"\n\n## У┐љУАїТЌХтѕєТхЂ(у╝ќТјњтЎетЦЉу║д,т┐ЁУ»╗)\n\nPython у╝ќТјњтЎежђџУ┐Є prompt жЄїуџё `runtime` СИј `metadata.json` тї║тѕєУи»тЙёсђѓ**СИЇУдЂУЄфУАїТћ╣ућеТ▓ЎуЏњТѕќТћ╣уће cua-driverсђѓ**\n\n| тЁЦтЈБ | `runtime` | жЕ▒тіеТќ╣т╝Ј | удЂТГб |\n|------|-----------|----------|------|\n| **тЇЋС╗╗тіА**:УЈютЇЋ 1сђЂСйЇуй«тЈѓТЋ░сђЂ`python scripts/analyze_product.py \"тљЇ\" \"URL\"` | **`host`** | ТюгТю║ **cua-driver** + уѕХ shell `curl`(тЈ»Ух░С╗Буљє) | `import cua`сђЂ`Sandbox.ephemeral`сђЂDocker/Lume/QEMU Т▓ЎуЏњсђЂУ»╗сђїSandbox У┐љУАїтљѕу║дсђЇтйЊТЊЇСйюТЅІтєї |\n| **ТЅ╣жЄЈ**: `--batch queue.json` | **`sandbox-local`** Тѕќ **`sandbox-cloud`** | **жђљТГЦ**ТјДтѕХТ▓ЎуЏњ(УДЂсђїТ▓ЎуЏњТјДтѕХСИЅжўХТ«хсђЇ);Тюгтю░уће `sandbox_ctl`,С║ЉуФ»уће Cua MCP | cua-driverсђЂhost ТхЈУДѕтЎе/GUIсђЂТЋ┤Т«х `asyncio` тѕєТъљУёџТюг |\n\n**тѕцт«џ**:prompt жЄї `runtime:host` Рєњ тЈфУх░ [Host тЇЋС╗╗тіА](#host-тЇЋС╗╗тіА-runtimehost)сђѓ`runtime:sandbox-local` / `sandbox-cloud` Рєњ тЈфУх░ [Sandbox У┐љУАїтљѕу║д](#sandbox-У┐љУАїтљѕу║д)сђѓ`batch.parallel:true` С╗ЁТЅ╣жЄЈтЄ║уј░сђѓ\n\n## УЙЊтЁЦ\n\nућ▒У░ЃућеТќ╣(УёџТюгТѕќт»╣У»Ю)ТЈљСЙЏ:\n- `product_name` Рђћ т┐ЁтАФ,т▒Ћуц║ућетјЪТќЄ(тЁЂУ«ИСИГТќЄ / тцДт░ЈтєЎТииТјњ)\n- `url` Рђћ т┐ЁтАФ,С║ДтЊЂт«ўуйЉ https URL\n- `download_url` Рђћ тЈ»жђЅ,уЏ┤ТјЦТїЄтљЉтйЊтЅЇСИ╗Тю║УЃйућеуџёт«ЅУБЁтїЁ(.dmg / .exe / .deb уГЅ)сђѓ**С╝ўтЁѕу║ДТюђжФў**,ТюЅт«Ѓт░▒Уи│У┐Є\"тюет«ўуйЉТЅЙСИІУййжЊЙТјЦ\"ТГЦжфц\n- `output_dir` Рђћ У░ЃућеТќ╣ти▓у╗Јт╗║тЦйуџёу╗Ют»╣Уи»тЙё,тйбтдѓ `<repo>/reports/<slug>-YYYY-MM-DD[-N]/`,Тюг skill ТііТЅђТюЅС║ДуЅЕтєЎУ┐Џтј╗\n- `runtime` Рђћ `host`сђЂ`sandbox-local` Тѕќ `sandbox-cloud`сђѓ`host` Сй┐ућетйЊтЅЇСИ╗Тю║ + cua-driver;`sandbox-local` / `sandbox-cloud` т┐ЁжА╗Сй┐уће Cua Sandbox SDK,СИћСИЇтЙЌТЊЇСйю host GUI\n- `sandbox.image` Рђћ `auto` / `linux` / `macos` / `windows`,С╗Ё sandbox runtime ТюЅТЋѕ\n- `sandbox.local` Рђћ `true` СИ║Тюгтю░ Docker/Lume/QEMU(ТЅ╣жЄЈж╗ўУ«ц);`false` СИ║ Cua Cloud(С╗ЁтйЊУ░ЃућеТќ╣ТўЙт╝Ј `--sandbox cloud` ТЌХ,жюђ `CUA_API_KEY` Т│етЁЦ env,**СИЇУдЂ**тєЎтЁЦ metadata.json)\n- `android.enabled` Рђћ Тў»тљдТБђТхІт╣Хт░ЮУ»Ћ Android APK Уи»тЙё\n- `batch.parallel` Рђћ Тў»тљдСИ║ТЅ╣жЄЈжўЪтѕЌСИГуџёт╣ХУАї worker(`true` ТЌХт┐ЁУ»╗СИІТќЄсђїТЅ╣жЄЈт╣ХУАїсђЇ)\n\nу╝ќТјњтЎеУ┐ўтЈ»УЃйжђџУ┐Є**уј»тбЃтЈўжЄЈ**Т│етЁЦ(СЙЏСйаУ»╗ skill ТЌХт»╣уЁД,тІ┐тєЎтЁЦ metadata):`ANALYZER_LINUX_CONTAINER_IMAGE`сђЂ`ANALYZER_LINUX_DOCKER_PLATFORM`сђЂ`ANALYZER_PYTHON_VERSION_MIN`сђЂ`ANALYZER_CONDA_ENV`сђЂ`ANALYZER_BATCH_PARALLEL`сђЂ`CUA_API_KEY`(С╗ЁС║ЉуФ»)сђѓ\n\n## УЙЊтЄ║тИЃт▒ђ\n\n```\n<output_dir>/\n  report.md                     # ТіЦтЉіСИ╗СйЊ\n  metadata.json                 # Тю║тЎетЈ»У»╗тЁЃТЋ░ТЇ«\n  downloads/                    # СИІУййуџёт«ЅУБЁтїЁ / APK\n  screenshots/\n    01_web_homepage.png\n    02_web_pricing.png         # у╝ќтЈиУДЂСИІ\n    05_app_main.png\n    ...\n```\n\n`metadata.json` уџёТюђу╗ѕтйбТђЂ(Python УёџТюгтєЎС║єжЏЈтйб,Тюг skill тюеу╗ЊТЮЪтЅЇУАЦжйљ):\n```json\n{\n  \"product_name\": \"ProductiveKitty\",\n  \"url\": \"https://productivekitty.masterwordai.com\",\n  \"download_url\": null,\n  \"host_os\": \"darwin\",\n  \"host_arch\": \"arm64\",\n  \"runtime\": \"host\",\n  \"sandbox\": {\"image\": null, \"local\": true, \"mode\": \"local\", \"name\": null, \"api_url\": null},\n  \"android\": {\n    \"enabled\": false,\n    \"apk_url\": null,\n    \"apk_file\": null,\n    \"package_name\": null,\n    \"mode\": null\n  },\n  \"started_at\": \"2026-05-18T03:30:00+08:00\",\n  \"finished_at\": \"2026-05-18T03:55:00+08:00\",\n  \"mode\": \"full\",\n  \"screenshots\": [\n    {\"file\": \"screenshots/01_web_homepage.png\", \"view\": \"web-homepage\", \"caption\": \"т«ўуйЉждќжАх\"},\n    ...\n  ],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## ТѕфтЏЙтЉйтљЇ\n\n`NN_<source>_<view>.png`:\n- `NN` Рђћ СИцСйЇжЏХтАФтЁЁуџётЇЋУ░Ѓу╝ќтЈисђѓ**тЁЂУ«ИУи│тЈи**:web Т«хСИђУѕг 01-04,app Т«х 05+ Ухи;УІЦСИГжђћТќ░тбъС╣ЪтЈ»С╗ЦТІ┐ 09сђЂ10\n- `source Рѕѕ {web, app, android}` Рђћ `web` УАеуц║ТхЈУДѕтЎетєЁТѕфтЏЙ,`app` УАеуц║ТАїжЮбт║ћућеуфЌтЈБТѕфтЏЙ,`android` УАеуц║ Android Т▓Ўу«▒тєЁТѕфтЏЙ\n- `view` Рђћ уЪГ kebab-case,У»ГС╣Ѕтїќ:`homepage / pricing / faq / main / settings / new-task / focus-mode / report-detail` уГЅ\n\nТ»Јт╝аТѕфтЏЙжЃйт┐ЁжА╗тюе `report.md` жЄїС╗ЦуЏИт»╣Уи»тЙё(`screenshots/NN_*.png`)тЄ║уј░,СИћтюе**жЎётйЋ A ТѕфтЏЙу┤бт╝Ћ**жЄїТюЅСИђУАїУ»┤ТўјсђѓТ▓Ат╝ЋућеУ┐ЄуџёТѕфтЏЙтѕаТјЅ,СИЇУдЂуЋЎт╝ЃтЏЙсђѓ\n\n## Canonical loop(7 ТГЦ,тЏ║т«џжА║т║Ј)\n\nУ░ЃућеТќ╣У┐ЏтЁЦТЌХ,`output_dir` ти▓т╗║тЦйсђЂ`metadata.json` жЏЈтйбти▓тєЎсђѓУ┐Ў skill ТјЦу«Атљју╗Гсђѓ\n\n**СИцТЮАжЊЂтЙІ(С╝ўтЁѕу║ДжФўС║јС╗╗СйЋТГЦжфцу╗єУіѓ)**:\n\n1. **ТЅЙСИІУййжЊЙТјЦ = уюЪт«ъТЊЇСйюТхЈУДѕтЎе**,СИЇТў»тЈфУиЉ curl + grepсђѓ`curl + grep` тЈфТў»т┐ФжђЪу║┐у┤б,**СИЇТў»тѕцт«џ web-only уџёСЙЮТЇ«**сђѓ`grep` Т▓АтЄ║у╗ЊТъюТЌХ**т┐ЁжА╗**у╗Ду╗ГТЅЊт╝ђТхЈУДѕтЎе,уюЪт«ъуѓ╣тЄ╗т»╝Уѕф Рђћ host уће cua-driver;sandbox уће **ж╝аТаЄ/жћ«уЏўжђљТГЦ**(`screenshot` Рєњ `click`/`scroll` Рєњ `type`/`key`),**удЂТГб**уће `step shell` + `wget/curl` С╗БТЏ┐уѓ╣уйЉжАхсђѓ\n\n2. **т«їТЋ┤ТеАт╝ЈСИІ,ТАїжЮбт║ћућеТў»т┐ЁтЂџжА╣,СИЇУЃйтЏаСИ║уйЉжАхтЦйујЕт░▒уюЂуЋЦ**:ТюЅт«ЅУБЁтїЁт░▒**т┐ЁжА╗**УБЁсђЂтљ»тіесђЂуће cua-driver Тііт«бТѕиуФ»СИ╗УдЂтіЪУЃйУх░СИђжЂЇсђѓуйЉжАхтЈ»С╗ЦтљїТЌХТи▒тЁЦТјбу┤б(тцџТїќСИђС║Џт«џС╗исђЂТќЄТАБсђЂтЇџт«бжЃйТ▓АжЌ«жбў),Сйє web Т«хтЂџтЙЌтцџРЅа app Т«хтЈ»С╗ЦтЂџтЙЌт░Љсђѓapp Т«хТў» ┬Д1 ТіЦтЉіуџёСИ╗УдЂу┤аТЮљТЮЦТ║љ,**С╗╗СйЋ\"т║ћућеТѕЉуюІС║єт«ўуйЉт░▒тцДТдѓуЪЦжЂЊС║є\"Тѕќ\"т║ћућетљ»тіетцфж║╗уЃдтЁѕУи│У┐Є\"уџётЂиТЄњжЃйСИЇУАї**сђѓтЈфТюЅ step 3 тЁежЃетц▒У┤ЦсђЂуА«т«ъСИІСИЇтѕ░т«ЅУБЁтїЁ,ТЅЇУ┐ЏтЁЦ web-only ТеАт╝Ј,ТііуйЉжАхтйЊСИ╗Тѕўтю║\n\n- `runtime=host` ТЌХ:тЈфУ»╗ [Host тЇЋС╗╗тіА](#host-тЇЋС╗╗тіА-runtimehost),**СИЇУдЂ**У»╗сђїSandbox У┐љУАїтљѕу║дсђЇсђѓ\n- `runtime` СИ║ `sandbox-local` Тѕќ `sandbox-cloud` ТЌХ:т┐ЁжА╗тЁѕУ»╗ [Sandbox У┐љУАїтљѕу║д](#sandbox-У┐љУАїтљѕу║д),тєЇТЅДУАї canonical loopсђѓ\n\n### 7 ТГЦУ»ду╗є\n\n1. **TodoWrite т╗║ 7 СИф todos**:`ТіЊтЈќт«ўуйЉ` Рєњ `т«џСйЇСИІУййжЊЙТјЦ` Рєњ `т«ЅУБЁ/тљ»тіет║ћуће` Рєњ `жЕ▒тіеуЏ«ТаЄ(т║ћуће + тЈ»жђЅуйЉжАх)` Рєњ `ТЅ╣жЄЈТѕфтЏЙ` Рєњ `ТЋ┤тљѕТіЦтЉі` Рєњ `УАЦжйљ metadata.json`сђѓТ»ЈТГЦт╝ђтДІтЅЇ `in_progress`,т«їТѕљУйг `completed`\n\n2. **ТіЊтЈќт«ўуйЉтјЪтДІС┐АТЂ»(у║┐у┤б + тЁЦжЌеСйЊжфї)** Рђћ\n   - **host**:уѕХ shell `curl -fsSL`(тЈ»Ух░С╗Буљє)+ Python тЅЦ HTML;уће **cua-driver** ТЅЊт╝ђТхЈУДѕтЎеТѕфждќжАх `01_web_homepage.png`сђѓ\n   - **sandbox**(**ж╝аТаЄС╝ўтЁѕ**,УДЂСИІУіѓ):\n     1. `sandbox_ctl bootstrap \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" --open-browser --url '<т«ўуйЉ>'`(Тѕќ `step open-url`)\n     2. `step screenshot` Рєњ `01_web_homepage.png`\n     3. уће **click / scroll / type / key** ТхЈУДѕ(тЁ│ cookie т╝╣уфЌсђЂуѓ╣т»╝Уѕф),Т»ЈТГЦтЅЇтљјТѕфтЏЙ\n     - **удЂТГб**уће `step shell -c 'curl/wget ...'` ТіЊт«ўуйЉтйЊСИ╗Уи»тЙё;shell С╗ЁтЁЂУ«ИСИІТќЄсђїСЙІтцќсђЇсђѓ\n   - тЈ»жА║тИдТхЈУДѕт«џС╗и/ТќЄТАБжАх Рђћ СИЇУЃйТЏ┐С╗БТАїжЮбуФ»СйЊжфїсђѓ\n\n3. **т«џСйЇСИІУййжЊЙТјЦ(тѕєСИцт▒ѓ:жЮЎТђЂ grep + уюЪт«ъТхЈУДѕ)** Рђћ\n   С╝ўтЁѕућеУ░ЃућеТќ╣С╝атЁЦуџё `download_url`сђѓтљдтѕЎ:\n\n   **3.1 жЮЎТђЂу║┐у┤б(тЈ»жђЅ,sandbox СИІ**СИЇтЙЌ**ТЏ┐С╗Буѓ╣тЄ╗)**:\n   - host тЈ»тюети▓СИІУйй HTML СИі grep т«ЅУБЁтїЁ URLсђѓ\n   - sandbox:**СИЇУдЂ**СИ║ТЅЙжЊЙТјЦУђї `wget` ТЋ┤уФЎ;С╗Ц **3.2 ж╝аТаЄТхЈУДѕ** СИ║тЄє,УѓЅую╝+ТѕфтЏЙУ«░тйЋСИІУййтЁЦтЈБсђѓ\n\n   **3.2 ТхЈУДѕтЎет«ъТЊЇ(т┐ЁжА╗тЂџ,СИЇтЈ»Уи│У┐Є)**:\n   - host: cua-driver уѓ╣тЄ╗т»╝Уѕфсђѓ\n   - sandbox: **`sandbox_ctl step screenshot` / `click` / `scroll` / `type` / `key`** Ух░т«їт«ўуйЉ(УДЂсђїТ▓ЎуЏњтєЁж╝аТаЄС╝ўтЁѕсђЇ):\n   - ТЅЊт╝ђТхЈУДѕтЎе,т«џСйЇтѕ░т«ўуйЉ,**уюЪт«ъуѓ╣тЄ╗**т»╝УѕфТаЈжЄїТЅђТюЅуюІУхиТЮЦуЏИтЁ│уџётЁЦтЈБ:`Download`/`СИІУйй`/`Get the App`/`Install`/`Pricing`/`Get Started`/`Try Free`/`С║ДтЊЂ`уГЅ\n   - УІЦ `android.enabled=true` СИћУ«АтѕњТІЅУхи Android Т▓ЎуЏњ,жбЮтцќуѓ╣тЄ╗/ТБђТЪЦ `Android` / `APK` / `Mobile` / `Get it on Android` / `Google Play` тЁЦтЈБ\n   - УІЦ `android.enabled=false` Тѕќ Android Т▓ЎуЏњТюфтљ»тіе:тЈфтюе **Firefox уйЉжАх**жЄї hunt(тљФ Play жЊЙТјЦТќЄтГЌУ»ЂТЇ«),**СИЇ**СИІУйй/т«ЅУБЁ APK\n   - Т»ЈСИфтђЎжђЅжАхжЃйТѕфтЏЙтГўТАБ(`screenshots/02_web_<view>.png` тйбт╝Ј)\n   - Т╗џтѕ░т║ЋжЃе,уюІ footer ТюЅТ▓АТюЅ `Mac` / `Windows` / `Linux` / `Android` уџёт░ЈтЏЙТаЄТїЅжњ«\n   - уѓ╣тЄ╗т╣│тЈ░тѕЄТЇбтЎе(тЙѕтцџуФЎуѓ╣С╝џтЁѕТўЙуц║У«┐т«б OS ТјеУЇљ)сђЂтЁ│ТјЅуЎ╗тйЋт╝╣уфЌсђЂтЁ│ТјЅ cookie Тефт╣Ё,у╗Ду╗ГТЅЙ\n   - С╗╗СйЋ a11y ТаЉСИ║уЕ║ / Electron canvas уџёжАхжЮбТїЅ [cua-driver SKILL](../cua-driver/SKILL.md) уџё escalation жўХТб»тЇЄу║Дтѕ░ vision\n\n   **3.3 тЉйСИГтљјжђЅТюђтї╣жЁЇуџёт«ЅУБЁтїЁ**:\n   - `darwin/arm64` С╝ўтЁѕ `*arm64*.dmg`сђЂ`*aarch64*.dmg`,тљдтѕЎ `darwin/x86_64` уће `*x64*.dmg`сђЂ`*intel*.dmg`сђЂСИЇтИдТъХТъёТаЄуџё `.dmg`\n   - `linux/x86_64` С╝ўтЁѕ `*x86_64*.AppImage`/`.deb`/`.tar.gz`\n   - `windows/x86_64` жђЅ `*.exe` / `*.msi` / `Setup-*.exe`\n   - Android APK тЈфТјЦтЈЌт«ўуйЉуЏ┤жЊЙТѕќт«ўТќ╣ release assetсђѓGoogle Play тЈфУ«░тйЋУ»ЂТЇ«,СИЇу╗ЋуЎ╗тйЋсђЂСИЇТіЊуггСИЅТќ╣жЋютЃЈсђЂСИЇС╗јжЮът«ўТќ╣ APK жЋютЃЈуФЎСИІУйй\n   - ТЅЙтѕ░ APK ТЌХтєЎтЁЦ `metadata.android.apk_url`;СИІУййтѕ░ `<output_dir>/downloads/`,тєЎтЁЦ `metadata.android.apk_file`\n\n   **3.4 тЁежЃетц▒У┤ЦТЅЇТаЄ web-only**,т╣Хтюе `metadata.warnings[]` тєЎТўј:\n   - жЮЎТђЂ grep У»ЋУ┐ЄтЊфС║Џ\n   - ТхЈУДѕтЎет«ъжЎЁУ«┐жЌ«/уѓ╣тЄ╗У┐ЄтЊфС║ЏжАхжЮб(тѕЌтЄ║жАхжЮб URL,У»ЂТўјтЂџС║єуюЪт«ъ hunt)\n   - Тюђу╗ѕу╗ЊУ«║(тдѓ\"С║ДтЊЂС╗ЁТюЅ Web уЅѕ,ТЌаТАїжЮбуФ»т«ЅУБЁтїЁ\")\n\n4. **т«ЅУБЁ/тљ»тіет║ћуће(С╗ЁтйЊ step 3 тЉйСИГ)** Рђћ\n   - host runtime:уће `scripts/install_cua_driver.py` уА«С┐ЮТАїжЮбжЕ▒тіетЎети▓УБЁ(жбёТБђУ┐Є,Сйє sanity-check СИђТгА `which cua-driver`)сђѓСИІУййС║ДтЊЂт«ЅУБЁтїЁтѕ░ `<output_dir>/downloads/`,ТїЅт╣│тЈ░ућет»╣т║ћТќ╣т╝Јт«ЅУБЁ(macOS:`hdiutil attach` + `cp -R` + `xattr -d com.apple.quarantine`;Linux:`dpkg -i` Тѕќ `chmod +x` AppImage;Windows:`start /wait` MSI)сђѓ**СИЦТа╝жЂхтЙф [cua-driver SKILL](../cua-driver/SKILL.md) уџё no-foreground тЦЉу║д**\n   - sandbox-local / sandbox-cloud runtime:Т▓ЎуЏњти▓тюе **bootstrap** жўХТ«хтѕЏт╗║сђѓ**т«ЅУБЁтїЁ**тЈ»тюети▓ТюЅуЏ┤жЊЙТЌХуће **СИђТгА** `step shell -c 'wget -O ...'` СИІУййтѕ░ `downloads/`(СЙІтцќ);**тљ»тіет║ћућесђЂуѓ╣уЋїжЮб**СИђтЙІ **mouse/keyboard**(`click`/`type`/`scroll`/`screenshot`)сђѓ\n   - Android APK:**С╗ЁтйЊ** `android.enabled=true` **СИћ** Android Т▓ЎуЏњти▓т░▒у╗фТЌХ:УІЦ `metadata.android.apk_url` ти▓тАФ,тєЇтѕЏт╗║ Android sandbox т╣Х `adb install` уГЅсђѓтљдтѕЎУи│У┐Є,Тћ╣Ух░ [Android Тюфтљ»ућеТѕќТюфтљ»тіе](#android-Тюфтљ»ућеТѕќТюфтљ»тіе)\n\n5. **жЕ▒тіеуЏ«ТаЄ** Рђћ\n\n   **5.A т«їТЋ┤ТеАт╝Ј(step 3 тЉйСИГ):ТАїжЮбт║ћућет┐ЁтЂџ,т«ўуйЉтЈ»жђЅТи▒Тїќ** Рђћ\n   - **ТАїжЮбуФ»т┐ЁтЂџ**:тљ»тіеС║ДтЊЂ,**СИ╗УдЂтіЪУЃйТїеСИфУх░СИђжЂЇ**сђѓТ»ЈТЅЊт╝ђСИђСИфТќ░уЋїжЮбт░▒ТѕфтЏЙсђѓhost уће cua-driver;sandbox уће **ж╝аТаЄС╝ўтЁѕ**жђљТГЦуѓ╣(app тЏЙТаЄсђЂУЈютЇЋсђЂТїЅжњ«),**удЂТГб**тЈфжЮа shell тљ»тіетљјСИЇтєЇуѓ╣уЋїжЮбсђѓapp Т«хТѕфтЏЙУЄ│т░Љ 4-8 т╝а,**У┐ЎТў» ┬Д1 ТіЦтЉіуџёСИ╗УдЂу┤аТЮљТЮЦТ║љ**\n   - **т«ўуйЉтЈ»жђЅТи▒Тїќ**:тюеС┐ЮУ»ЂТАїжЮбуФ»СйЊжфїт«їТЋ┤уџётЅЇТЈљСИІ,тЈ»С╗Цу╗Ду╗ГуюІт«џС╗и / ТќЄТАБ / тЇџт«б / FAQ уГЅ,УАЦтЁЁ ┬Д3 т«ўуйЉТЈЈУ┐░уџёу┤аТЮљсђѓweb Т«хТѕфтЏЙТЋ░жЄЈТ▓АТюЅСИіжЎљ Рђћ Сйє**у╗Ют»╣СИЇУЃйућеуйЉжАхТѕфтЏЙТЏ┐С╗Бт║ћућеТѕфтЏЙ**,С╣ЪСИЇУЃйтЏаСИ║уйЉжАхтєЁт«╣тцџт░▒у╝ЕТ░┤т║ћућеСйЊжфї\n\n   **5.B уйЉжАхТеАт╝Ј(step 3 тЁежЃетц▒У┤Ц,жЎЇу║Д web-only):тюеТхЈУДѕтЎежЄїт«їТЋ┤СйЊжфї** Рђћ У┐ЎТЌХуйЉжАхт░▒Тў»С║ДтЊЂТюгСйЊ,ућетйЊтЅЇ runtime уџёТхЈУДѕтЎеТЊЇСйюУЃйтіЏжђљжАхТи▒тЁЦ:\n   - ждќжАх(Т╗џтѕ░т║Ћ,тљё section тљёТѕфСИђт╝а)\n   - СИ╗тіЪУЃйжАх / Т╝ћуц║жАх(УЃйС║цС║њуџёжЃетѕєжЃйУ»ЋСИђСИІ:УЙЊтЁЦсђЂТЈљС║цсђЂТњГТћЙсђЂтѕЄ tab)\n   - т«џС╗и / Pricing(тљёТАБСйЇжЃйуѓ╣т╝ђ)\n   - ТќЄТАБ / тИ«тіЕ / Changelog\n   - FAQ / тЇџт«бтц┤уЅѕ / тЁ│С║ј\n   - уЎ╗тйЋтЁЦтЈБ(тЈфуюІСИЇТЊЇСйюУ┤дтЈи)\n   - тЏйжЎЁтїќ:ТюЅ `EN/СИГТќЄ/...` тѕЄТЇбтЎет░▒тѕЄСИђжЂЇтљёуюІСИђт╝а\n   - жћЎУ»»ТђЂ:ТЋЁТёЈУЙЊтЁЦжћЎуџёсђЂуѓ╣СИЇУ»Цуѓ╣уџё,уюІС║цС║њтЈЇждѕ\n   - web Т«хУЄ│т░Љ 6-10 т╝атЏЙ\n\n   СИцуДЇТеАт╝ЈжЃйУдЂС┐ЮУ»Ђ ┬Д1 ТіЦтЉіуФаУіѓТюЅУХ│тцЪтцџуџё\"уЋїжЮб\"тЈ»тєЎсђѓ\n\n   **5.C Android тбът╝║Уи»тЙё(С╗Ё `android.enabled=true` СИћ Android Т▓ЎуЏњти▓тљ»тіе;ТЅЙтѕ░ APK ТЌХУ┐йтіа)** Рђћ\n   - тюе Android sandbox СИГтљ»тіет║ћуће,ТѕфтЏЙС┐ЮтГўСИ║ `screenshots/NN_android_<view>.png`\n   - УЄ│т░ЉУдєуЏќтљ»тіежАхсђЂСИ╗уЋїжЮбсђЂТЮЃжЎљт╝╣уфЌсђЂуЎ╗тйЋтбЎсђЂУ«Йуй«/тЁ│С║јсђЂжћЎУ»»ТђЂСИГтЈ»УЙЙуџёжЃетѕє\n   - СИЇтѕЏт╗║У┤дтЈисђЂСИЇу╗ЋУ┐ЄуЎ╗тйЋсђЂСИЇТјѕС║ѕжФўтЇ▒ТЮЃжЎљ;ТЮЃжЎљт╝╣уфЌтЈфУ«░тйЋж╗ўУ«цТќЄТАѕтњїтЈ»УДЂжђЅжА╣\n   - УІЦ APK т«ЅУБЁтц▒У┤ЦсђЂтљ»тіежЌфжђђсђЂAndroid Т▓ЎуЏњ**Тюфтљ»тіе**Тѕќ runtime у╝║тц▒:тєЎтЁЦ `metadata.android.mode = \"failed\"`(Тѕќ `skipped`),`metadata.warnings[]` У»┤ТўјтјЪтЏа,**Тћ╣тЈфТЊЇСйюуйЉжАх**т«їТѕљтЅЕСйЎтѕєТъљ(УДЂ [Android Тюфтљ»ућеТѕќТюфтљ»тіе](#android-Тюфтљ»ућеТѕќТюфтљ»тіе)),ТіЦтЉітЈфт╝Ћућети▓ТюЅУ»ЂТЇ«\n\n6. **ТЅ╣жЄЈТѕфтЏЙ** Рђћ ТЋ┤уљє screenshots/,тѕатєЌСйЎсђЂС┐ЮуЋЎС╗БУАеТђДуџёсђЂуА«С┐ЮтЉйтљЇУ┐ъу╗Г(тЁЂУ«ИУи│тЈи)\n\n7. **ТЋ┤тљѕТіЦтЉі** Рђћ ТІиУ┤Ю [REPORT_TEMPLATE.md](REPORT_TEMPLATE.md) тѕ░ `<output_dir>/report.md`,жђљУіѓтАФтєЎсђѓтЈ»жђЅуФаУіѓ(т«џС╗и / уЏ«ТаЄућеТѕи / тљїу▒╗т»╣Т»ћ / С╝ўтіБті┐)**тЈфтюеТюЅУ»ЂТЇ«ТЌХС┐ЮуЋЎ,тљдтѕЎТЋ┤Т«хтѕажЎц**сђѓТЅђТюЅ\"У»ёС╗и\"тъІжЎѕУ┐░т┐ЁжА╗тЈ»УбФТѕфтЏЙТѕќт«ўуйЉтјЪТќЄУ»Ђт«ъ\n\nТ»ЈТГЦу╗ЊТЮЪ TodoWrite ТаЄ `completed`,СИІСИђТГЦТаЄ `in_progress`,уёХтљјт╝ђтДІСИІСИђТГЦсђѓ\n\n## Host тЇЋС╗╗тіА (`runtime=host`)\n\nтйЊ prompt / `metadata.json` жЄї **`runtime` СИ║ `host`** ТЌХ(ж╗ўУ«цтЇЋС╗╗тіАУи»тЙё):\n\n1. **удЂТГбТ▓ЎуЏњ**:СИЇтЙЌ `from cua import Sandbox`сђЂСИЇтЙЌ `Sandbox.ephemeral`сђЂСИЇтЙЌТІЅ Docker/Lume Т▓ЎуЏњсђѓтЇ│Сй┐ТюгТю║ти▓УБЁ Docker/conda,С╣Ъ**СИЇУдЂ**Тћ╣ућеТ▓ЎуЏњт«їТѕљтѕєТъљсђѓ\n2. **ТАїжЮбСИјТхЈУДѕтЎе**:СИђтЙІ [cua-driver SKILL](../cua-driver/SKILL.md)(`launch_app`сђЂ`get_window_state`сђЂ`element_index` уѓ╣тЄ╗сђЂТѕфтЏЙ),СИЦт«ѕ **no-foreground**сђѓ\n3. **т«ўуйЉ curl**:тЈ»тюе **host уѕХ shell** ТЅДУАї(тЈ»Ух░ућеТѕиС╗Буљє),ућеС║ј HTML у║┐у┤б;уюЪт«ъуѓ╣тЄ╗т»╝УѕфС╗ЇУх░ cua-driver ТхЈУДѕтЎесђѓ\n4. **т«ЅУБЁтїЁ**:СИІУййтѕ░ `<output_dir>/downloads/`,тюе **host** т«ЅУБЁ(macOS/Linux/Windows тИИУДёТќ╣т╝Ј),уће cua-driver жЕ▒тіети▓т«ЅУБЁт║ћућесђѓ\n5. **`metadata.mode`**:ТѕљтіЪТЌХтєЎ `full`,жЎЇу║ДтєЎ `web-only` Рђћ **СИЇУдЂ**тєЎ `sandbox-full`сђѓ\n\n## Sandbox У┐љУАїтљѕу║д\n\n**С╗ЁтйЊ** `runtime Рѕѕ {sandbox-local, sandbox-cloud}`(ТЅ╣жЄЈ `--batch`)ТЌХ,ТюгУіѓТЅЇТў»ТЮЃтеЂТ▓ЎуЏњУ»┤Тўјсђѓ`runtime=host` ТЌХ**Уи│У┐ЄТюгУіѓ**сђѓ\n\n### Т▓ЎуЏњТјДтѕХСИЅжўХТ«х(СИј host cua-driver жђљТГЦт»╣жйљ)\n\n| жўХТ«х | тЂџС╗ђС╣ѕ | удЂТГб |\n|------|--------|------|\n| **1. bootstrap(СИђТгА)** | тѕЏт╗║Т▓ЎуЏњсђЂтєЎ `<output_dir>/sandbox.json`сђЂтЈ»жђЅтљ»тіеТхЈУДѕтЎе | тюе bootstrap жЄї curl тЁеуФЎсђЂУБЁтїЁсђЂтєЎ `report.md` |\n| **2. step loop(Т»ЈТГЦ)** | **screenshot Рєњ уюІтЏЙ Рєњ click/scroll/type/key Рєњ тєЇ screenshot** | уће shell ТхЈУДѕуйЉжАх;тЇЋСИф `asyncio.run()` тѕєТъљУёџТюг |\n| **3. teardown(СИђТгА)** | жћђТ»ЂТ▓ЎуЏњ;у╝ќТјњтЎеС╣ЪтЈ»УЃйУЄфтіе teardown | Т│ёТ╝Ј Docker т«╣тЎе / Cloud VM |\n\n**observeРђЊact жЊЂтЙІ**:Т»ЈТгА GUI ТЊЇСйютЅЇтљјтљёСИђт╝аТѕфтЏЙУ┐Џ `screenshots/`;Уи»тЙётєЎУ┐ЏтйЊУй«Тјеуљє,тєЇтє│т«џСИІСИђТГЦтЮљТаЄсђѓ\n\n### Т▓ЎуЏњтєЁж╝аТаЄС╝ўтЁѕ(sandbox-local / sandbox-cloud)\n\nТ▓ЎуЏњТ▓АТюЅ host уџё AX ТаЉ,**тЮљТаЄу║Дж╝аТаЄ + жћ«уЏў**Тў»тћ»СИђтЈ»жЮауџё GUI Уи»тЙёсђѓж╗ўУ«цТЊЇСйюТаѕ(ТїЅжбЉујЄ):\n\n| С╝ўтЁѕу║Д | `sandbox_ctl` / MCP | ућежђћ |\n|--------|---------------------|------|\n| 1 | `step screenshot` | Т»ЈТГЦтЅЇтљјтЈќУ»Ђ |\n| 2 | `step click` / `move` | уѓ╣ТїЅжњ«сђЂжЊЙТјЦсђЂтЁ│жЌГт╝╣уфЌ |\n| 3 | `step scroll` | Т╗џУй«у┐╗жАх |\n| 4 | `step type` / `step key` | УЙЊтЁЦТќЄтГЌ;жћ«тљЇућет░ЈтєЎ pynput тљЇ(`enter`/`esc`/`ctrl+l`,тІ┐уће `Return`/`Escape`/`Meta`) |\n| 5 | `step open-url` / `bootstrap --url` | ТЅЊт╝ђт«ўуйЉ(жћ«уЏўУ┐Џтю░тЮђТаЈ,жЮъ wget) |\n| ТюФСйЇ | `step shell -c '...'` | **С╗Ё**УДЂСИІТќ╣СЙІтцќ |\n\n**`step shell` тЈфтЁЂУ«ИУ┐ЎС║Џтю║ТЎ»**(тЁХСйЎСИђтЙІж╝аТаЄТхЂ):\n\n1. **bootstrap ТЌХтљ»тіе Firefox СИђТгА**(Linux `cua-xfce` тЈфТюЅ Firefox;УёџТюгтєЁжЃети▓тЂџ;СйаСИЇУдЂТЅІтєЎ `chromium` ТѕќжЋ┐ shell жЊЙ)\n2. **ти▓ТюЅуЏ┤жЊЙ**ТЌХ `wget -O <output_dir>/downloads/...` СИІУййт«ЅУБЁтїЁ/APK(СИІт«їтљјС╗Їућеж╝аТаЄт«ЅУБЁ/ТЅЊт╝ђ)\n3. `dpkg -i` / `chmod +x` уГЅ**у║»т«ЅУБЁтЉйС╗ц**(ТЌа GUI ТЌХ)\n4. У»╗ `/proc`сђЂ`uname` уГЅ**СИЇТЏ┐С╗БуЋїжЮбСйЊжфї**уџёТјбТхІ\n\n**удЂТГб**:уће `curl|wget|python3` ТіЊт«ўуйЉ HTML тйЊ step 2/3 СИ╗Уи»тЙё;уће shell тљ»тіеТхЈУДѕтЎетљјСИЇтєЇ `click` уѓ╣уЋїжЮбсђѓ\n\nтЁИтъІт╝ђт▒ђ:\n\n```bash\npython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py bootstrap \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" --open-browser --url \"$URL\"\npython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step screenshot \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" --out screenshots/01_web_homepage.png\npython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step key \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" esc          # тЁ│ Firefox у┐╗У»Љ/cookie т╝╣уфЌ;тЈ»У┐ъТїЅСИцТгА\npython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step click \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" 640 120    # уц║СЙІ:тЁ│ cookie(т╝╣уфЌС╗ЇтюетѕЎтєЇ click)\npython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step scroll \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" 512 400 --scroll-y -8\npython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step screenshot \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" --out screenshots/02_web_after_scroll.png\n```\n\nтЮљТаЄТЮЦУЄф**СИіСИђт╝аТѕфтЏЙ**уџёуЏ«ТхІ;тЈ»тЁѕ `step screen-size` уЪЦтѕєУЙеујЄ(жђџтИИ 1024├Ќ768)сђѓ\n\n#### `sandbox_ctl` Рєћ Cua SDK / computer-server тЦЉу║д\n\nТЅ╣жЄЈ worker жђџУ┐Є `sandbox_ctl` У░Ѓуће [Cua Sandbox SDK](https://cua.ai/docs/cua/reference/sandbox-sdk)(`Sandbox.connect` Рєњ `mouse`/`keyboard`/`screen`/`shell`)сђѓ**SDK ТќЄТАБуц║СЙІСИј Docker тєЁ computer-server(pynput) уџёжћ«тљЇ/Т╗џУй«У»ГС╣ЅСИЇт«їтЁеСИђУЄ┤** Рђћ СИІтѕЌУДётѕЎти▓тюе `scripts/product_analyzer/sandbox_ctl.py` жЄїтЂџтйњСИђтїќ/workaround;Claude ТїЅ CLI ућеТ│ЋтЇ│тЈ»,СИЇт┐ЁуЏ┤ТјЦ `import cua` тЈЉтЉйС╗цсђѓ\n\n**У┐ъТјЦ**: bootstrap тєЎтЁЦ `<output_dir>/sandbox.json` уџё `api_url`;тљју╗Г `step` уће `Sandbox.connect(..., http_url=api_url)` уЏ┤У┐ъ computer-server(Тюгтю░/С║ЉуФ»тЮЄжђѓуће)сђѓ\n\n**жћ«уЏў(`step key`)** Рђћ тєЁжЃеТўат░ётѕ░ pynput `Key.*` тљЇ;тИИућетєЎТ│Ћ:\n\n| ТёЈтЏЙ | ТГБуА« CLI | тІ┐уће(С╝џ Remote error) |\n|------|----------|------------------------|\n| Esc тЁ│т╝╣уфЌ/УЈютЇЋ | `esc` Тѕќ `escape`(тйњСИђтїќСИ║ `esc`) | `Escape` |\n| тЏъУйд | `enter` | `Return` |\n| у╗ётљѕжћ« | `ctrl+l`сђЂ`ctrl+alt+t` | `Control+L`сђЂ`Meta+Рђд` |\n| Super/Win | `cmd` / `super`(тйњСИђтїќСИ║ `cmd`) | `meta` |\n| у┐╗жАхжћ« | `page_down` / `page_up` | `PageDown`сђЂ`pgdn` |\n| тѕажЎц | `delete` | `del` тЈ»,`Del` тІ┐ |\n\nтЇЋжћ«Ух░ `press_key`,у╗ётљѕжћ«Ух░ `hotkey`(СИј SDK `Keyboard.keypress` СИђУЄ┤)сђѓ\n\n**Т╗џУй«(`step scroll`)** Рђћ SDK `Mouse.scroll(x,y,scroll_x,scroll_y)` у╗Ј HTTP тѕ░ Linux handler ТЌХС╝џТіі `x/y` У»»тйЊТ╗џУй«тбъжЄЈт╣ХСИбт╝Ѓ `scroll_x/scroll_y`(СИіТИИ bug)сђѓ`sandbox_ctl` ти▓ workaround:**тЁѕ `move` тѕ░ `(x,y)`,тєЇ `scroll_down`/`scroll_up`(ТїЅ `--scroll-y` угдтЈи)**сђѓућеТ│ЋСИЇтЈў:\n\n```bash\npython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step scroll \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" 512 400 --scroll-y -8\n```\n\n- Т╗џУй«тЅЇуА«С┐Юуёдуѓ╣тюежАхжЮбтєЁт«╣тї║(тЁѕ `click` ТГБТќЄТѕќ `esc` тЁ│т╝╣уфЌ);**ТАїжЮбтЏътйњТЌХ scroll т║ћтюе right-click С╣ІтЅЇ**,жЂ┐тЁЇтЈ│жћ«УЈютЇЋТїАСйЈТ╗џтіесђѓ\n- УІЦТѕфтЏЙС╗ЇТЌаТ╗џтіетЈўтїќ:жЎЇу║Д `step key page_down`(тЈ»У┐ъТїЅ 2РђЊ3 ТгА)тєЇ screenshotсђѓ\n\n**тЁХт«Ѓ step СИј SDK т»╣жйљТЃЁтєх**:\n\n| step | SDK | У»┤Тўј |\n|------|-----|------|\n| `screenshot` | `sb.screenshot()` | РюЊ |\n| `screen-size` | `sb.screen.size()` | РюЊ |\n| `move` / `click` | `mouse.move` / `click` / `right_click` / `double_click` | РюЊ |\n| `type` | `keyboard.type` | РюЊ |\n| `shell` | `shell.run` | С╗Ёт«ЅУБЁ/ТјбТхІ,СИЇТЏ┐С╗БТхЈУДѕ |\n| `open-url` | `keyboard` т»╝Уѕф | тѕ╗ТёЈСИЇућеТхЈУДѕтЎе MCP;`ctrl+l` Рєњ type URL Рєњ `enter` |\n\nжфїУ»ЂУёџТюг:`python -m tests.sandbox.sandbox_ctl_smoke`(browser + ТАїжЮбжћ«ж╝атЏътйњ;ТѕфтЏЙтюе `tmp/sandbox-ctl-smoke/screenshots/`)сђѓ\n\n#### Linux ТАїжЮб (`trycua/cua-xfce`)\n\n- жЋютЃЈ**тЈфжбёУБЁ Firefox**,Т▓АТюЅ Chromiumсђѓ`bootstrap --open-browser` / `step open-url` С╝џућ▒ `sandbox_ctl` ТјбТхІ `DISPLAY`(У»╗ `/tmp/.X11-unix`,тИИУДЂ **`:1`**,тІ┐тєЎТГ╗ `:0`)т╣Хтљ»тіе Firefox,тєЇуће `ctrl+l` Рєњ УЙЊтЁЦ URL Рєњ `enter`сђѓ\n- **`bootstrap` С╝џУЄфтіетЁ│жЌГ XFCE С╝Љуюа/т▒ЈС┐Ю**(`xset`сђЂ`xfce4-power-manager`сђЂ`screensaver`);Claude **СИЇУдЂ**тєЇТЅІтіеУиЉућхТ║љу«АуљєтЉйС╗ц,жЎцжЮъТѕфтЏЙС╗Їж╗Љт▒Јсђѓ\n- **удЂТГб**Тіі `chromium Рђд`сђЂ`apt install chromium` тйЊСИ╗Уи»тЙё;С╝џтц▒У┤ЦТѕќТхфУ┤╣ТЌХжЌ┤сђѓ\n- УІЦ bootstrap тљјтЈфТюЅуЕ║уЎйт░ЈуфЌ/жЮбТЮ┐:тЁѕ `step screenshot`,тєЇ **click** С╗╗тіАТаЈ Firefox тЏЙТаЄ,Тѕќ `step open-url \"$URL\"`(Firefox ти▓УиЉтѕЎтіа `--no-launch`)сђѓ\n- т«ўуйЉт»╝УѕфсђЂCookieсђЂСИІУйй hunt тЮЄтюе **Firefox уфЌтЈБтєЁ**ућеж╝аТаЄ + жћ«уЏўт«їТѕљсђѓ\n\n#### тЈЇТеАт╝Ј(ТўјуА«удЂТГб)\n\n- тєЎСИђСИф `analyze_*.py` / `run_analysis.py`,тюежЄїУЙ╣ `async with Sandbox.ephemeral` УиЉт«їтЁежЃетѕєТъљсђѓ\n- bootstrap УёџТюгжЄїтїЁтљФ step 3РђЊ7 уџёСИџтіАжђ╗УЙЉсђѓ\n- уће host уѕХ shell `curl` С╗БТЏ┐Т▓ЎуЏњтєЁУ»ЂТЇ«(`ANALYZER_BATCH_PARALLEL=1` ТЌХ)сђѓ\n\n#### Тюгтю░ (`sandbox-local`) Рђћ С╝ўтЁѕ `sandbox_ctl`\n\nу╝ќТјњтЎеТЈљСЙЏУќё CLI(conda уј»тбЃ `python`,тІ┐ућеу│╗у╗Ъ 3.9):\n\n```bash\nconda activate computer-use-py312   # Тѕќ $ANALYZER_CONDA_ENV\nREPO=...                            # С╗Њт║ЊТа╣уЏ«тйЋ\n\n# 1) bootstrap + ућежћ«уЏўТЅЊт╝ђт«ўуйЉ(жЮъ wget)\npython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py bootstrap \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" --open-browser --url \"$URL\"\n\n# 2) ж╝аТаЄС╝ўтЁѕ loop Рђћ Т»ЈТГЦСИђТЮА;тЁѕуюІтЏЙтєЇт«џтЮљТаЄ\npython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step screenshot \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" --out screenshots/01_web_homepage.png\npython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step key \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" esc            # тЁ│т╝╣уфЌ\npython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step click \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" 512 380\npython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step scroll \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" 512 400 --scroll-y -6\npython scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step screenshot \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" --out screenshots/02_web_pricing.png\n# С╗ЁтйЊТюЅуЏ┤жЊЙСИІУййт«ЅУБЁтїЁТЌХ:\n# python scripts/sandbox_ctl.py step shell \"$OUTPUT_DIR\" -c 'wget -q -O ...'\n\n# 3) teardown\npython \"$REPO/scripts/sandbox_ctl.py\" teardown \"$OUTPUT_DIR\"\n```\n\n`<output_dir>/sandbox.json` тЦЉу║д( bootstrap тєЎтЁЦ,тІ┐ТЅІТћ╣):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"analyzer-babbel-2026-05-19\",\n  \"provider\": \"docker\",\n  \"api_url\": \"http://127.0.0.1:PORT\",\n  \"image\": \"trycua/cua-xfce:latest\",\n  \"platform\": \"linux/amd64\",\n  \"local\": true\n}\n```\n\n- Сй┐уће **`Sandbox.create(..., ephemeral=False, name=...)`**,С╗ЦСЙ┐ `~/.cua/sandboxes/` ТюЅуіХТђЂ;**СИЇУдЂ**уће `Sandbox.ephemeral` тЂџ batch СИ╗Т▓ЎуЏњсђѓ\n- **тцЄжђЅ**:`cua do switch docker <sandbox.json.name>` тљј `cua do screenshot` / `click`(СИј `sandbox_ctl` С║їжђЅСИђ;**С╝ўтЁѕ `sandbox_ctl`**,СИЇСЙЮУхќ Claude У«░ port)сђѓ\n- `sandbox_ctl status \"$OUTPUT_DIR\"` Тјњжџюсђѓ\n- **Т▓ЎуЏњтєЁТЌа curl** ТЌХ:т«ўуйЉС╗Їуће **ж╝аТаЄТхЈУДѕ**;`wget` тЈфућеС║ј**ти▓ТюЅ URL**уџёт«ЅУБЁтїЁСИІУйй,СИЇућеС║јТіЊждќжАх HTMLсђѓ\n- **`step shell` тц▒У┤ЦТѕќ Bash уюІСИЇтѕ░УЙЊтЄ║**:У»╗ `$OUTPUT_DIR/.sandbox_ctl_last_shell.json`;СИЇУдЂУЄфтєЎ `/tmp/sb_run.py` ТЏ┐С╗Б(жЎцжЮъ `sandbox_ctl` ТюгУ║ФТіЦжћЎ)сђѓ\n\n#### С║ЉуФ» (`sandbox-cloud`) Рђћ С╝ўтЁѕ Cua MCP\n\nу╝ќТјњтЎеС╝џСИ║ worker Т│етЁЦ `claude --mcp-config`( `cua serve-mcp` )сђѓжђљТГЦСй┐уће:\n\n- `computer_screenshot` / `computer_click` / `computer_type` / `computer_shell` уГЅ\n- **удЂТГб**уће host Bash ТЊЇСйюТ▓ЎуЏњ GUI\n- MCP У┐ћтЏъуџёТѕфтЏЙУІЦТюфУЄфтіеУљйуЏў,**т┐ЁжА╗** `Write` тѕ░ `<output_dir>/screenshots/NN_*.png` тєЇУ»╗тЏЙтѕєТъљ\n- С╗ЇтЈ»уће `sandbox_ctl bootstrap` + `step`(cloud) Сйю MCP СИЇтЈ»ућеТЌХуџёжЎЇу║Д\n\n**СИЇУдЂ**Сй┐уће `ComputerAgent(tools=[sb])` тхїтЦЌ agent Рђћ СИјтйЊтЅЇ `claude --print` ТхЂТ░┤у║┐жЄЇтцЇсђѓ\n\n### Тђ╗тјЪтѕЎ\n\n1. **ТЊЇСйюу│╗у╗Ъу║ДтиЦСйютЈфтюеТ▓ЎуЏњтєЁ**сђѓ**удЂТГб** cua-driverсђЂhost `open`/`osascript`сђЂТюгТю║ТхЈУДѕтЎе/ТАїжЮб GUIсђѓ\n2. **host С╗Ё**:У░Ѓуће `sandbox_ctl` / MCP / У»╗тєЎ `<output_dir>` С║ДуЅЕсђѓ\n3. **Т»ЈСИфС║ДтЊЂуІгуФІ sandbox**;удЂТГбтцЇућетЁХт«Ѓ `reports/` С╗╗тіАуџёУ┐ъТјЦсђѓ\n\n### Host СЙД Python / CLI\n\n- Cua Sandbox SDK **С╗ЁТћ»ТїЂ Python 3.12 Тѕќ 3.13**;`sandbox_ctl` СИј `import cua` т┐ЁжА╗уће conda уј»тбЃ(У»╗ `ANALYZER_CONDA_ENV`,ж╗ўУ«ц `computer-use-py312`)сђѓ\n- ТЅ╣жЄЈжбёТБђУдЂТ▒ѓ `cua` CLI тюе PATH(`cua --version`)сђѓ\n- Т▓ЎуЏњ**тєЁ** shell ућет«╣тЎетєЁ `python3`(тЅЦ HTML уГЅ);СИј host SDK уЅѕТюгТЌатЁ│сђѓ\n\n### ТЅ╣жЄЈт╣ХУАї(`batch.parallel=true` Тѕќ `ANALYZER_BATCH_PARALLEL=1`)\n\n- уІгуФІ worker;т«ўуйЉСИј GUI У»ЂТЇ«т┐ЁжА╗ТЮЦУЄфТ▓ЎуЏњсђѓ\n- жЎцУ»╗тєЎтйЊтЅЇ `<output_dir>` тцќ,СИЇтЙЌТіі host тйЊтѕєТъљуј»тбЃсђѓ\n\n### жЋютЃЈ\n\n| `sandbox.image` | Тюгтю░ | У»┤Тўј |\n|-----------------|------|------|\n| `linux` | `trycua/cua-xfce:latest` + `linux/amd64` | `sandbox_ctl bootstrap` ж╗ўУ«ц |\n| `macos` | Lume | bootstrap ТїЅ image жђЅУ┐љУАїТЌХ(УІЦТюфт«ъуј░тѕЎ warnings) |\n| `windows` | QEMU Docker | тљїСИі |\n| `auto` | С╝ўтЁѕ linux т«╣тЎетЂџуйЉжАх | |\n\n- У»╗ `ANALYZER_LINUX_CONTAINER_IMAGE` / `ANALYZER_LINUX_DOCKER_PLATFORM`сђѓ\n- С║ЉуФ»:ућ▒ `CUA_API_KEY` Т│етЁЦ;**тІ┐тєЎтЁЦ metadata**сђѓ\n\n### SDK ТЋ┤УёџТюгуц║СЙІ(smoke/CI СИЊуће,жЮъ batch agent ж╗ўУ«ц)\n\n[`tests/sandbox/linux_smoke.py`](../../tests/sandbox/linux_smoke.py) уће `Sandbox.ephemeral` жфїУ»ЂжЊЙУи» Рђћ **СИЇУдЂ**уЁДТіётѕ░С║ДтЊЂтѕєТъљ Bash жЄїсђѓ\n\n### Android APK(тЈ»жђЅ)\n\n- С╗Ё `android.enabled=true` **СИћ** Android Т▓ЎуЏњТѕљтіЪтљ»тіеТЌХ;**уІгуФІ** Android sandbox(`sandbox_ctl` Тѕќ SDK),ТѕфтЏЙ `NN_android_*.png`сђѓ\n- жЋютЃЈ **`trycua/cua-qemu-android:latest`**сђѓ\n\n### Android Тюфтљ»ућеТѕќТюфтљ»тіе\n\nТ╗АУХ│**С╗╗СИђ**ТЮАС╗ХТЌХ,**удЂТГб**тѕЏт╗║/У┐ъТјЦ Android Т▓ЎуЏњ(ТЌа `Image.android()`сђЂТЌа `cua-qemu-android`сђЂТЌа `adb install`):\n\n- prompt / `metadata.android.enabled` СИ║ **`false`**(ТЅ╣жЄЈТюфтіа `--android`,Тѕќ `--no-android`)\n- Android жЋютЃЈТюфТІЅтЈќсђЂ`Sandbox.create` тц▒У┤ЦсђЂadb/QEMU СИЇтЈ»уће\n- ти▓т░ЮУ»Ћтљ»тіе Android Т▓ЎуЏњСйєУХЁТЌХТѕќтц▒У┤Ц\n\nТГцТЌХ**т┐ЁжА╗**:\n\n1. **тЈф**тюеуј░ТюЅ **Linux ТАїжЮбТ▓ЎуЏњ + Firefox** тєЁТхЈУДѕт«ўуйЉ,уће `screenshot` Рєњ `click`/`scroll`/`type`/`key` УјитЈќС║ДтЊЂС┐АТЂ»(т«џСйЇсђЂтіЪУЃйсђЂт«џС╗исђЂUI/UXсђЂт«ўуйЉТќЄТАѕ)сђѓ\n2. С╗Ц `screenshots/NN_web_*.png` СИ║СИ╗УдЂу┤аТЮљ,ТїЅСИіТќЄ **5.B уйЉжАхТеАт╝Ј** уџётіЏт║дУх░т«ўуйЉтљётЁЦтЈБ(ждќжАхсђЂт«џС╗исђЂтіЪУЃйсђЂFAQ уГЅ)сђѓ\n3. тЈ»тюеуйЉжАхСИіУ«░тйЋ Google Play / APK жЊЙТјЦтѕ░ `metadata.warnings[]`,**СИЇ**СИІУййсђЂСИЇУБЁ APKсђѓ\n4. У«Йуй« `metadata.android.mode = \"skipped\"`,`warnings[]` тєЎТИЁтдѓ `\"android: sandbox not started; web-only product path\"`сђѓ\n5. **СИЇУдЂ**тЏаТГцТііТЋ┤тЇЋ `metadata.mode` Тћ╣Тѕљ `web-only` Рђћ жЎцжЮъ [Уиет╣│тЈ░СИјжЎЇу║Д](#Уиет╣│тЈ░СИјжЎЇу║Д) жЄїТАїжЮбт«ЅУБЁтїЁ hunt С╣Ъти▓тц▒У┤ЦсђѓТ▓ЎуЏњтєЁсђїтЈфтЂџуйЉжАхсђЇРЅа тЁет▒ђ web-only жЎЇу║Дсђѓ\n\n### Т▓ЎуЏњтєЁ GUI / уйЉжАх\n\n- С╗Ц **ж╝аТаЄС╝ўтЁѕ**УіѓСИ║тЄє;Т»ЈТГЦ `step screenshot` УљйуЏўсђѓ\n- тцЇТЮѓ SPA / уЎ╗тйЋтбЎ:У«░тЁЦ `warnings[]`,тІ┐у╗ЋУ┐ЄуЎ╗тйЋсђѓ\n\n## ТіЦтЉіТеАТЮ┐УдЂТ▒ѓ\n\nтЈѓУДЂ [REPORT_TEMPLATE.md](REPORT_TEMPLATE.md)сђѓУдЂуѓ╣:\n\n- **т┐ЁТюЅуФаУіѓ(жА║т║ЈСИЇУЃйтЈў)**:`Тђ╗т«џСйЇ` Рєњ `уЋїжЮбТИЁтЇЋ` Рєњ `тљёуЋїжЮбтіЪУЃйСИјУ»ёС╗и` Рєњ `UI/UX` Рєњ `т«ўуйЉТЈЈУ┐░` Рєњ `жЎётйЋ A ТѕфтЏЙу┤бт╝Ћ`\n- **тЈ»жђЅуФаУіѓ**(`т«џС╗и / уЏ«ТаЄућеТѕи / тљїу▒╗т»╣Т»ћ / С╝ўтіБті┐т░Ју╗Њ`):ТюЅУ»ЂТЇ«ТЅЇтєЎ,ТЌатѕЎТЋ┤Т«хтѕа,**СИЇУдЂуЋЎ\"С┐АТЂ»СИЇУХ│\"тЇаСйЇ**\n- **Т»ЈСИфУ»ёС╗ит┐ЁжА╗тЈ»У»ЂС╝ф**:СИЇтєЎ\"ТхЂуЋЁ\"сђЂ\"уЙјУДѓ\",тєЎ\"тљ»тіетѕ░ждќт▒Ју║д 0.8s,ТЌатіаУййтіеућ╗\"Тѕќ\"СИ╗ CTA ућеу┤ФУЅ▓тАФтЁЁТїЅжњ«СйЇС║јждќт▒ЈтЈ│СИІ,СИјУЃїТЎ»т»╣Т»ћт║дТ╗АУХ│ WCAG AA\"\n- **т«ўуйЉтјЪТќЄућет╝ЋтЈит╝Ћуће**(СИЇУдЂТёЈУ»Љ),УіѓТаЄжбўТЌЂТаЄ\"тјЪТќЄжћџ:ждќжАх H1\"С╣Іу▒╗уџёСйЇуй«С┐АТЂ»\n\n## Уиет╣│тЈ░СИјжЎЇу║Д\n\nhost runtime уџёТАїжЮбжЕ▒тіетљјуФ» OS уЪЕжўхућ▒ `scripts/install_cua_driver.py` тє│т«џ:\n- macOS arm64 / x86_64 Рєњ Swift `cua-driver`\n- Linux x86_64 Рєњ `cua-driver-rs`\n- Windows x86_64 Рєњ `cua-driver-rs` (PowerShell т«ЅУБЁ)\n- Linux aarch64 Рєњ ТЌажбёу╝ќУ»Љ Рєњ УЄфтіе web-only\n\nsandbox-local runtime уџёТАїжЮб/Android уЪЕжўхућ▒ Cua Sandbox SDK тњїТюгтю░У┐љУАїТЌХтє│т«џ:\n- Linux sandbox Рєњ Docker\n- macOS sandbox Рєњ Lume\n- Windows sandbox Рєњ QEMU\n- Android sandbox Рєњ Android SDK(emulator + platform-tools)Тѕќ QEMU\n\nsandbox-cloud runtime ућ▒ Cua Cloud ТЅўу«А VM/т«╣тЎе;`sandbox.image` жђЅТІЕ linux / macos / windowsсђѓСИЇжюђУдЂТюгТю║ Docker/Lume жбёТБђ,СйєжюђУдЂТюЅТЋѕуџё `CUA_API_KEY`(ти▓ућ▒ orchestrator Т│етЁЦ,тІ┐тєЎтЁЦ metadata)сђѓ\n\nжЎЇу║Дтѕ░ `mode: \"web-only\"` уџёУДдтЈЉТЮАС╗Х,тЈфТюЅУ┐ЎСИЅуДЇ:\n1. С║ДтЊЂт«ўуйЉТ▓АтЄ║тйЊтЅЇСИ╗Тю║ OS уџёт«ЅУБЁтїЁ(тдѓ ProductiveKitty Т▓А Linux уЅѕ,УђїСйатюе Linux СИ╗Тю║СИі)\n2. тйЊтЅЇСИ╗Тю║т╣│тЈ░Т▓АТюЅ cua-driver жбёу╝ќУ»Љ(Linux aarch64)\n3. т║ћућет«ЅУБЁ/тљ»тіетц▒У┤Ц / тЈЇтцЇжЌфжђђ\n\nжЎЇу║ДТЌХ:\n- `metadata.json.mode = \"web-only\"`\n- batch sandbox ТѕљтіЪжЕ▒тіеТАїжЮбуФ»ТЌХ `metadata.json.mode = \"sandbox-full\"`;ТЅЙтѕ░т╣ХТѕљтіЪСйЊжфї APK ТЌХ `metadata.android.mode = \"android\"`\n- тюе `metadata.json.warnings[]` тіаСИђТЮАтйбтдѓ `\"web-only: no macos package found at <url>\"`\n- ТіЦтЉітц┤уџётЁЃС┐АТЂ»УАе\"ТеАт╝Ј\"тѕЌтАФ `web-only`,т╣ХтюеУАеСИІућеСИђтЈЦУ»ЮУ»┤ТўјжЎЇу║ДтјЪтЏа\n- ТіЦтЉітЁХС╗ќжЃетѕєуЁДтИИтєЎ,тЈфТў» ┬Д1 С╗ЁтЪ║С║јт«ўуйЉ + ТхЈУДѕтЎеТѕфтЏЙ,жЋ┐т║дтЈ»УЃйТ»ћ full ТеАт╝ЈуЪГ\n\n## тц▒У┤ЦтцёуљєСИјтЇЄу║Д\n\n- **AX ТаЉСИ║уЕ║ / Electron canvas / WebView2 т║ћуће** Рєњ ТїЅ [cua-driver SKILL](../cua-driver/SKILL.md) уџё escalation СИђУіѓтцёуљє(ТБђТхІ webviewсђЂт┐ЁУдЂТЌХ vision тЁют║Ћ)сђѓТюг skill СИЇтцЇУ┐░У┐ЎС║ЏУДётѕЎ\n- **т║ћућетљ»тіежЌфжђђ** Рєњ Тѕфт▒Јт┤ЕТ║Ѓт»╣У»ЮТАє,У«░тйЋу│╗у╗ЪТЌЦт┐ЌУи»тЙё(macOS:`~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`,Linux:`journalctl --user-unit`),`┬Д1.3` ТаЄ\"У»ЦуЋїжЮбтЏат┤ЕТ║ЃТюфУЃйжЄЄжЏє\",жЎЇу║Дтѕ░т░йжЄЈтцџуџётЈ»УЙЙуЋїжЮб\n- **уЎ╗тйЋтбЎ** Рєњ СИЇу╗ЋУ┐ЄсђЂСИЇтѕЏт╗║У┤дтЈисђѓУЃйжЄЄжЏєуџё:ждќжАхсђЂт«џС╗исђЂТќЄТАБсђЂтЇџт«бсђЂChangelog;`metadata.json.warnings[]` тіа `\"login-required: feature pages not analyzed\"`,ТіЦтЉітц┤Т│еТўј\"ТюфуЎ╗тйЋТђЂтѕєТъљ\"\n- **тЇЋТГЦ 30s УХЁТЌХ** Рђћ Уи│У┐ЄУ»ЦТГЦ,`metadata.json.warnings[]` У«░тйЋ,у╗Ду╗ГСИІСИђТГЦ;СИЇУдЂТЌажЎљуГЅ\n- **СИІУйй/т«ЅУБЁТЮЃжЎљтЈЌжў╗**(/Applications СИЇтЈ»тєЎсђЂSIP тЇАтюе quarantine уГЅ)Рєњ У«░тйЋтјЪтЏа,жЎЇу║Д web-only\n\n## жБјТа╝т«ѕтѕЎ\n\n- **ТіЦтЉітЁеуеІСИГТќЄ**(у«ђСйЊ)\n- **СИЇтцИт╝а**:СИЇуће\"т«їуЙј\"сђЂ\"ТЃіУЅ│\"сђЂ\"жбаУдє\"сђѓС║Іт«ъжЎѕУ┐░ + СИђСИцтЈЦУ»ёС╗ит░▒тцЪ\n- **СИЇтњїуеђТ│Ц**:С║ДтЊЂТюЅжЌ«жбўт░▒тєЎ,СйєУдЂУљйтѕ░тЁиСйЊу╗єУіѓ,СИЇУдЂТ│ЏТ│ЏТЅ╣У»ё\n- **тЈ»У»ЂС╝ф**:Т»ЈСИфУ»ёС╗иТїЄтљЉТѕфтЏЙТѕќт«ўуйЉтјЪТќЄсђѓУ»╗УђЁТЅФСИђую╝УЃй follow back to evidence\n\n## СИј cua-driver / Cua Sandbox SDK уџётЁ│у│╗\n\nТюг skill У┤ЪУ┤Б\"тѕєТъљС╗ђС╣ѕсђЂС║ДтЄ║С╗ђС╣ѕ\"сђѓhost runtime СИІ,ТЅђТюЅ\"тдѓСйЋжЕ▒тіеТАїжЮбуФ»\"уџётЁиСйЊУДётѕЎ(snapshot СИЇтЈўжЄЈсђЂno-foreground тЦЉу║дсђЂтЮљТаЄу│╗сђЂescalation жўХТб»сђЂт╣│тЈ░ти«т╝ѓ)жЃйтюе [.claude/skills/cua-driver/SKILL.md](../cua-driver/SKILL.md)сђѓ**СИЇУдЂтюеУ┐ЎжЄїтцЇУ┐░,тЈфтюетиЦСйюСИГжЂхт«ѕ**сђѓ\n\nsandbox-local / sandbox-cloud runtime СИІ,Т▓ЎуЏњТЊЇСйюУДётѕЎС╗Ц**Тюг skillсђїSandbox У┐љУАїтљѕу║дсђЇ**СИ║тЄє(СИЇтюе prompt жЄїжЄЇтцЇ)сђѓhost runtime СИІТАїжЮбжЕ▒тіеС╗ЇС╗Ц [cua-driver SKILL](../cua-driver/SKILL.md) СИ║тЄєсђѓ\n","numLines":470,"startLine":1,"totalLines":470}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_3jkkR6yuftIIJTyUDh6cshx1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tname: cua-driver\n3\tdescription: Drive a native desktop app via the cua-driver CLI (default) or MCP server Рђћ snapshot its accessibility tree, click/type/scroll by element_index, verify via re-snapshot. Backend is auto-selected per platform: macOS uses the Swift `cua-driver` (mature), Linux/Windows use the Rust port `cua-driver-rs`. The CLI/MCP surface is identical across backends. Use when the user asks you to operate, drive, automate, or perform a GUI task in a real desktop application on the host (e.g. \"open a file in TextEdit\", \"click the Save button in Numbers\", \"fill the form in Notepad\").\n4\t---\n5\t\n6\t# cua-driver\n7\t\n8\tOrchestrates desktop app automation via `cua-driver`. Whenever a user\n9\tasks to drive a native app, follow the loop in this skill rather\n10\tthan calling tools ad-hoc Рђћ the snapshot-before-action invariant is not\n11\toptional and silently breaks if you skip it.\n12\t\n13\t## Backend selection\n14\t\n15\t| Host OS | Binary | Notes |\n16\t|---|---|---|\n17\t| macOS (arm64 / x86_64) | Swift `cua-driver` | mature, official, in `/Applications/CuaDriver.app` |\n18\t| Linux x86_64 | `cua-driver-rs` (Rust port) | feature-complete on Linux |\n19\t| Windows x86_64 | `cua-driver-rs` (Rust port) | installs via `install.ps1`, no admin required |\n20\t| Linux aarch64 | not supported by prebuilts | source build only |\n21\t\n22\tThe CLI subcommands and MCP tools described in this skill are the\n23\tsame across both backends. Anything that says \"macOS\" below applies\n24\tspecifically to the Swift backend; Linux/Windows-only callouts are\n25\tmarked. To install the right backend for the current host run\n26\t`scripts/install_cua_driver.py` from this project.\n27\t\n28\t## The no-foreground contract Рђћ read this first\n29\t\n30\t**The user's frontmost app MUST NOT change.** This is the whole\n31\treason cua-driver exists. Users pay for the right to keep typing in\n32\ttheir editor while an agent drives another app in the background.\n33\tViolate this rule and every other nice property the driver gives\n34\tyou (no cursor warp, no Space switch, no window raise) stops\n35\tmattering Рђћ you just shipped the Accessibility Inspector with extra\n36\tsteps.\n37\t\n38\tBefore running any shell command, ask: **\"does this raise,\n39\tactivate, foreground, or make-key any app?\"** If yes, don't run it.\n40\tEvery one of the commands below activates the target on macOS and\n41\tis therefore forbidden unless the user **explicitly** asked for\n42\tfrontmost state:\n43\t\n44\t- **Every form of the `open` CLI Рђћ `open -a <App>`, `open -b\n45\t  <bundle-id>`, `open <file>`, `open <path-to-App.app>`, `open\n46\t  <url>` Рђћ always activates.** macOS routes all forms through\n47\t  LaunchServices, which unhides and foregrounds the target\n48\t  regardless of whether you passed an app name, a bundle id, a\n49\t  document, a URL, or the bundle path itself. The activation\n50\t  happens even when the only intent was \"start the process.\"\n51\t  **Never use `open` for any app launch.** This includes launching\n52\t  a just-built .app from a local build dir (e.g. `open\n53\t  build/Build/Products/Debug/MyApp.app`) Рђћ resolve the\n54\t  `CFBundleIdentifier` from `Info.plist` and use `launch_app`\n55\t  with that id. See \"The narrow carve-out\" below for why\n56\t  `launch_app` is safe even when the app internally calls\n57\t  `NSApp.activate`.\n58\t- `osascript -e 'tell application \"X\" to activate'` Рђћ\n59\t  activates by design. Same for `... to open <file>`,\n60\t  `... to launch`, and anything with `activate` in the tell block.\n61\t- `osascript -e 'tell application \"System Events\" to ... frontmost'`\n62\t  in a mutating form (setting `frontmost` rather than reading it).\n63\t- AppleScript files that invoke `activate`, `launch`, or `open`\n64\t  against the target app.\n65\t- `cliclick` (moves the user's real cursor to the target coords\n66\t  before clicking Рђћ a focus-steal-equivalent even if the app's\n67\t  window state is unchanged).\n68\t- `CGEventPost` with `cghidEventTap` targeting a coordinate over\n69\t  a different app's window (warps the cursor, possibly activates\n70\t  on hit).\n71\t- `AppleScriptTask`, `NSAppleScript`, `Process` wrapping `osascript`\n72\t  that contains any of the above.\n73\t- `NSRunningApplication.activate(options:)` called from your own\n74\t  helper binary Рђћ same class.\n75\t- Dock clicks and any `open` invocation (see the first bullet Рђћ\n76\t  every form of `open` goes through LaunchServices which\n77\t  activates, full stop).\n78\t- **Keyboard shortcuts that semantically mean \"focus here\" Рђћ\n79\t  most notably Chrome / Safari / Arc's `РїўL` (focus omnibox) and\n80\t  Finder's `РїўРЄДG` (Go to Folder).** These aren't pure key events Рђћ\n81\t  the receiving app interprets \"user wants to type here\" as\n82\t  activation intent and raises its window to be key. Even when\n83\t  delivered to a backgrounded pid via `hotkey`, the downstream app\n84\t  pulls focus. **For omnibox navigation specifically**, the correct\n85\t  path is `launch_app({bundle_id: \"com.google.Chrome\", urls:\n86\t  [\"https://Рђд\"]})` Рђћ no omnibox dance, no `РїўL`, no focus-steal. Do\n87\t  NOT try `set_value` on the omnibox: Chrome's commit logic requires\n88\t  a \"user-typed\" signal that neither an AX value write nor\n89\t  `CGEvent.postToPid` keystrokes supply from a backgrounded pid Рђћ\n90\t  the URL lands in the field but Return fires as a no-op. See\n91\t  `WEB_APPS.md` Рєњ \"Navigate to a URL\" for the full pattern. The\n92\t  general principle: a shortcut that says \"put my cursor inside this\n93\t  app\" is a focus-steal; a shortcut that says \"do this thing\" (copy,\n94\t  save, quit) is fine.\n95\t- **Tab-switching shortcuts in browsers (`Рїў1..Рїў9`, `Рїў]`, `Рїў[`,\n96\t  `РїўРЄД[`, `РїўРЄД]`) are visibly disruptive even when delivered to a\n97\t  backgrounded pid.** The app's key handler processes the shortcut,\n98\t  the window re-renders the new tab's content, the user sees their\n99\t  tabs flipping. There is no AX-only workaround: page content (HTML,\n100\t  form state, `AXWebArea`) populates only for the focused tab;\n101\t  inspecting a background tab requires activating it, which is the\n102\t  visible flip. Observed with Dia; the same mechanic applies to every\n103\t  Chromium-family browser (Chrome, Arc, Brave, Edge).\n104\t\n105\t  **Prefer the windows-over-tabs pattern**: for each URL you need to\n106\t  drive backgrounded, use `launch_app({bundle_id, urls: [url]})` Рђћ\n107\t  browsers open each URL in a new **window**. Each window has its own\n108\t  `window_id`, its own AX tree, and can be inspected / interacted with\n109\t  via `element_index` without activating or switching anything. Tabs\n110\t  are a UX grouping for humans; cua-driver workflows should default to\n111\t  windows. See `WEB_APPS.md` Рєњ \"Tabs vs windows\" for the full pattern.\n112\t\n113\t  Tab-title enumeration (read-only) IS safe Рђћ walk a window's toolbar\n114\t  AX tree for `AXTab` / `AXRadioButton` children and read their\n115\t  `AXTitle`s. Tab switching (activating one) is not.\n116\t\n117\tReading frontmost state is fine (`osascript -e 'tell application\n118\t\"System Events\" to get name of first application process whose\n119\tfrontmost is true'`). Mutating it is not.\n120\t\n121\t**Corollary Рђћ the AXMenuBar rule.** `AXMenuBarItem` + AXPick\n122\tdispatches at the AX layer regardless of which app is frontmost,\n123\tbut macOS's on-screen menu bar always belongs to the frontmost\n124\tapp. If you drive a *backgrounded* app's menu bar, the AX call\n125\tsucceeds but the viewer sees the dispatch rendered over the\n126\t*frontmost* app's menu bar Рђћ confusing in any observed session and\n127\troutinely a silent no-op too, because action menu items go\n128\t`DISABLED` when their owning app isn't the key window. **So: only\n129\tuse menu-bar navigation when the target is already frontmost.** For\n130\tbackgrounded targets, read state via in-window AX (window title,\n131\ttoolbar `AXStaticText`) and dispatch via in-window `element_index`\n132\tor pixel clicks Рђћ both paths are frontmost-insensitive. Full\n133\trationale in \"Navigating native menu bars\" below.\n134\t\n135\t**\"Open \\<app\\>\" in user speech means launch, not activate.**\n136\t`cua-driver launch_app` is the one correct path for process\n137\tstartup Рђћ it's idempotent (no-op on a running app), returns the\n138\tpid, and has an internal `FocusRestoreGuard` that catches\n139\t`NSApp.activate(ignoringOtherApps:)` calls the target makes during\n140\t`application(_:open:)` and clobbers the frontmost back to what it\n141\twas before the launch. That guard is why `launch_app` with `urls`\n142\t(e.g. `{\"bundle_id\": \"com.colliderli.iina\", \"urls\": [\"~/video.mp4\"]}`)\n143\tis safe even for apps that normally foreground on media-load\n144\t(Chrome, Electron, media players).\n145\t\n146\t## Defaults Рђћ always prefer cua-driver over shell shims\n147\t\n148\t**Default transport is the `cua-driver` CLI** Рђћ `Bash` shelling out\n149\tto `cua-driver <tool-name> '<JSON-args>'`. MCP tools (prefix\n150\t`mcp__cua-driver__*`) only when the user explicitly asks for them.\n151\tCLI wins because it picks up rebuilds instantly, failures are\n152\teasier to diagnose, and there's no per-tool schema-load overhead.\n153\t\n154\tEvery reference to `click(...)`, `get_window_state(...)` etc. in this\n155\tskill means `cua-driver click '{...}'` Рђћ translate to MCP form only\n156\twhen MCP is requested.\n157\t\n158\t### Claude Code computer-use compatibility mode\n159\t\n160\tFor normal Claude Code use, keep the default CLI or `cua-driver` MCP server path above. If the user explicitly wants Claude Code's vision/computer-use-style flow, they can register:\n161\t\n162\t```bash\n163\tclaude mcp add --transport stdio cua-computer-use -- cua-driver mcp --claude-code-computer-use-compat\n164\t```\n165\t\n166\tObservation: Claude Code vision flows appear to treat a screenshot MCP tool as the image-grounding anchor. This compatibility mode keeps the normal CuaDriver tools and changes only `screenshot`. The compatibility `screenshot` requires `pid` and `window_id`, captures only that target window, and returns the window-local pixel coordinate frame. Start with `launch_app` or `list_windows`, then call `screenshot({pid, window_id})`; do not assume desktop coordinates or a full-screen capture.\n167\t\n168\tUse MCP for this Claude Code vision/computer-use-style path. Do not shell out to `cua-driver screenshot` as a substitute: CLI screenshots still work as CuaDriver calls, but they do not expose the `mcp__cua-computer-use__screenshot` tool name that Claude Code appears to use as the image-grounding cue.\n169\t\n170\tIntent Рєњ tool mapping. If you find yourself reaching for the right\n171\tcolumn, something has gone wrong Рђћ re-read \"The no-foreground\n172\tcontract\" above:\n173\t\n174\t| Intent | Use | Don't use |\n175\t|---|---|---|\n176\t| Open / launch an app | `launch_app({bundle_id})` or `launch_app({bundle_id, urls:[...]})` | `open -a`, `osascript 'tell app Рђд to launch/activate/open'` |\n177\t| Find a pid | `list_apps` or `launch_app`'s return | `pgrep`, `ps`, `osascript frontmost` |\n178\t| Enumerate an app's windows | `list_windows({pid})` Рђћ or read the `windows` array `launch_app` already returns | `osascript 'every window of app Рђд'` |\n179\t| Click / type / scroll / keys | `click`, `type_text`, `scroll`, `press_key`, `hotkey` | `osascript`, `cliclick`, raw `CGEvent`, `open <url>` |\n180\t| Drag / drag-and-drop / marquee select | `drag({pid, from_x, from_y, to_x, to_y})` (pixel-only Рђћ macOS AX has no semantic drag) | `cliclick dd:`, `osascript drag` |\n181\t| Screenshot | `screenshot` or the PNG in `get_window_state` | `screencapture` |\n182\t| Quit an app | ask the user first, then `hotkey({pid, keys:[\"cmd\",\"q\"]})` | `kill`, `killall`, `pkill` |\n183\t| Hand a file/URL to an app | `launch_app({bundle_id, urls:[<path>]})` | `open -a <App> <path>`, `open <url>` |\n184\t\n185\t### The narrow carve-out\n186\t\n187\tThe **only** legitimate use of `osascript -e 'tell app X to\n188\tactivate'` is when the user **explicitly** asked for frontmost\n189\tstate (\"bring Chrome to the front\", \"make it frontmost\", \"I want\n190\tto see X\"). Reaching for it because a tool call returned something\n191\tconfusing is wrong Рђћ that's the skill's classic foot-in-the-door\n192\tfailure mode and it steals focus every time.\n193\t\n194\tWhen a cua-driver call surprises you, diagnose cua-driver first:\n195\t\n196\t- **Tiny screenshot / empty `tree_markdown`?** Check\n197\t  `cua-driver get_config` Рєњ `capture_mode`. Default `\"som\"` returns\n198\t  both the AX tree and screenshot. `\"vision\"` omits the AX tree\n199\t  (PNG only), `\"ax\"` omits the PNG. If a snapshot lacks a tree,\n200\t  `capture_mode` is almost certainly `\"vision\"` Рђћ either reason\n201\t  purely from the PNG or flip to `\"som\"` / `\"ax\"` via `set_config`.\n202\t- **`has_screenshot: false`?** The window capture failed (transient\n203\t  race against a close, or the window has no backing store yet).\n204\t  Re-snapshot; if persistent, pick a different `window_id` via\n205\t  `list_windows`.\n206\t- **`Invalid element_index` / `No cached AX state`?** You either\n207\t  skipped `get_window_state` this turn or passed a different\n208\t  `window_id` than the one the snapshot cached against. The cache\n209\t  is keyed on `(pid, window_id)` Рђћ indices don't carry across\n210\t  windows of the same app. Re-snapshot with the same window_id\n211\t  you're about to click in.\n212\t- **Sparse Chromium AX tree?** Retry `get_window_state` once Рђћ the\n213\t  tree populates on second call.\n214\t\n215\tOnly after those are ruled out, and only if the user's action\n216\tgenuinely needs frontmost state, fall through to the activate\n217\tfallback. Always name the focus steal in your response (\"I'll\n218\tbriefly bring Chrome to the front because Рђд\").\n219\t\n220\t### Self-check pattern\n221\t\n222\tBefore every `Bash` call whose command line touches any macOS app\n223\t(launching, opening, clicking, typing, scripting, screenshotting),\n224\trun the self-check:\n225\t\n226\t1. **Does this command foreground the target?** If yes Рђћ stop and\n227\t   translate to the cua-driver equivalent from the mapping table.\n228\t2. **Does this command move the user's real cursor?** (`cliclick`,\n229\t   any `CGEventPost` at `cghidEventTap` over another app's window).\n230\t   If yes Рђћ stop; use `click({pid, x, y})` which routes per-pid\n231\t   via SkyLight and never warps the cursor.\n232\t3. **Does this command bypass cua-driver entirely?** (`osascript`\n233\t   mutating GUI state, AppleScript files, external helpers.) If\n234\t   yes Рђћ stop; find the cua-driver tool that does the intent.\n235\t\n236\tIf all three are \"no,\" the command is safe. If you can't answer,\n237\tdefault to stop and ask rather than proceed. A single `open -a`\n238\trun by accident kills the demo, the trust, and the user's in-flight\n239\teditor state.\n240\t\n241\t## Prerequisites Рђћ check before starting\n242\t\n243\t1. `cua-driver` is on `$PATH` (`which cua-driver`). If not, point the\n244\t   user at `scripts/install-local.sh` and stop.\n245\t2. Run `cua-driver check_permissions` (with the daemon up Рђћ see step 3).\n246\t   The default behavior also raises the system permission dialogs for\n247\t   any missing grants, so the user can grant on the spot. If either\n248\t   grant still reads `false` after that (user dismissed the dialog),\n249\t   tell them to open System Settings Рєњ Privacy & Security and grant\n250\t   Accessibility and Screen Recording to `CuaDriver.app`, then stop.\n251\t   Pass `'{\"prompt\":false}'` for a purely read-only status check that\n252\t   won't steal focus.\n253\t3. Start the daemon with `open -n -g -a CuaDriver --args serve` (the\n254\t   recommended form Рђћ goes through LaunchServices so TCC attributes\n255\t   the process to CuaDriver.app). `cua-driver serve &` also works;\n256\t   the CLI auto-relaunches through `open -n -g -a CuaDriver` when it\n257\t   detects a wrong-TCC context (any IDE-spawned shell: Claude Code,\n258\t   Cursor, VS Code, Conductor). Verify with `cua-driver status`.\n259\t\n260\t## Using cua-driver from the shell\n261\t\n262\tTool names are `snake_case`, management subcommands are\n263\t`kebab-case` Рђћ no ambiguity. Tools invoked as `cua-driver\n264\t<tool-name> '<JSON-args>'`. Management subcommands:\n265\t\n266\t- `open -n -g -a CuaDriver --args serve` Рђћ start persistent daemon\n267\t  (**required** for `element_index` workflows; without it each CLI\n268\t  invocation spawns a fresh process and the per-pid element cache\n269\t  dies between calls). `cua-driver serve &` also works Рђћ the CLI\n270\t  auto-relaunches via `open` when the shell's TCC context is wrong.\n271\t  Pass `--no-relaunch` / `CUA_DRIVER_NO_RELAUNCH=1` to opt out.\n272\t- `cua-driver stop` / `status`\n273\t- `cua-driver list-tools`, `describe <tool>`\n274\t- `cua-driver recording start|stop|status` Рђћ see `RECORDING.md`\n275\t\n276\tCanonical multi-step workflow:\n277\t\n278\t```\n279\topen -n -g -a CuaDriver --args serve\n280\tcua-driver launch_app '{\"bundle_id\":\"com.apple.calculator\"}'\n281\t# Рєњ {pid: 844, windows: [{window_id: 10725, ...}]}\n282\tcua-driver get_window_state '{\"pid\":844,\"window_id\":10725}'\n283\tcua-driver click '{\"pid\":844,\"window_id\":10725,\"element_index\":14}'\n284\tcua-driver stop\n285\t```\n286\t\n287\t## Agent cursor overlay\n288\t\n289\tVisual cursor overlay for demos and screen recordings. Default:\n290\tenabled. Toggle with `cua-driver set_agent_cursor_enabled\n291\t'{\"enabled\":true|false}'`. A triangle pointer Bezier-glides to each\n292\tclick target, ring-ripples on landing, idle-hides after ~1.5s.\n293\tMotion knobs: `set_agent_cursor_motion` takes any subset of\n294\t`start_handle`, `end_handle`, `arc_size`, `arc_flow`, `spring` Рђћ\n295\ttuneable at runtime, persisted to config.\n296\t\n297\tRequires an AppKit runloop, which `cua-driver serve` / `mcp`\n298\tbootstraps. One-shot CLI invocations skip the overlay entirely.\n299\t\n300\t## The core invariant Рђћ snapshot before AND after every action\n301\t\n302\t**Every action MUST be bracketed by `get_window_state(pid, window_id)`**:\n303\t\n304\t- **Before** Рђћ the pre-action snapshot resolves the `element_index`\n305\t  you're about to use. Indices from previous turns are stale; the\n306\t  server replaces the element index map on every snapshot, keyed\n307\t  on `(pid, window_id)`. Indices from turn N don't resolve in turn\n308\t  N+1, and indices from window A don't resolve against window B of\n309\t  the same app. Skip this and element-indexed actions fail with\n310\t  `No cached AX state`.\n311\t- **After** Рђћ the post-action snapshot verifies the action actually\n312\t  landed. Without it you can't tell a silent no-op from a real\n313\t  effect. The AX tree change (new value, new window, disappeared\n314\t  menu, disabled button, etc.) is your evidence that the action\n315\t  fired. If nothing changed, the action probably failed silently Рђћ\n316\t  say so, don't assume success.\n317\t\n318\tThis applies to pixel clicks too Рђћ re-snapshot after to confirm the\n319\tclick landed on the intended target.\n320\t\n321\t### Why window selection is the caller's job now\n322\t\n323\t`get_app_state` used to pick a window for you via a max-area heuristic\n324\tthat returned the wrong surface on apps with large off-screen utility\n325\tpanels. Concrete reproducer: IINA's OpenSubtitles helper (600├Ќ432\n326\toff-screen) out-area'd the visible 320├Ќ240 player window, so\n327\t`get_app_state(pid)` screenshot'd the invisible panel and clicks landed\n328\tthere silently. The new `get_window_state(pid, window_id)` makes the\n329\tcaller name the window explicitly Рђћ the driver validates that the\n330\twindow belongs to the pid and is on the current Space, then snapshots\n331\texactly what was asked for. Enumerate candidates via `list_windows` or\n332\tread the `windows` array `launch_app` already returns.\n333\t\n334\t## Behavior matrix\n335\t\n336\tTwo orthogonal axes shape what the agent can do.\n337\t\n338\t**capture_mode Рєњ addressing mode**\n339\t\n340\t| `capture_mode` | `get_window_state` returns | Use for actions |\n341\t|---|---|---|\n342\t| **`som`** (default) | tree + screenshot | `element_index` preferred; pixel fallback |\n343\t| **`ax`** | tree only (no PNG) | `element_index` only |\n344\t| **`vision`** | PNG only (no tree) | pixel only Рђћ see [SCREENSHOT.md](./SCREENSHOT.md) |\n345\t\n346\t`vision` was renamed from `screenshot` Рђћ the old name still decodes\n347\tas a deprecated alias, so an on-disk `\"capture_mode\": \"screenshot\"`\n348\tkeeps working. Default is `som` so element_index clicks work the\n349\tfirst time a user calls `get_window_state`; the other modes are\n350\topt-in when the caller specifically doesn't want one half of the\n351\twork. Note the tool named `screenshot` is separate (raw PNG, no AX\n352\twalk) and unrelated to the capture mode.\n353\t\n354\tWhen a snapshot looks wrong (tiny screenshot / empty tree), check\n355\t`cua-driver get_config` for `capture_mode` before anything else.\n356\t\n357\tPure-vision mode has its own caveats Рђћ Claude Code's vision\n358\tpipeline downsamples dense text aggressively, so pixel grounding\n359\ttakes multiple correction cycles on text-heavy UIs. Read\n360\t[SCREENSHOT.md](./SCREENSHOT.md) before driving anything in that\n361\tmode; it documents the iterate/annotate/verify recipe plus the\n362\tJPEG-over-PNG finding.\n363\t\n364\t**Window state Рєњ what works**\n365\t\n366\t| state | `get_window_state` | `click`/`set_value` (AX) | `press_key` commit (Return/Space/Tab) | pixel click |\n367\t|---|---|---|---|---|\n368\t| frontmost | РюЁ | РюЁ | РюЁ | РюЁ |\n369\t| backgrounded / visible | РюЁ | РюЁ | РюЁ | РюЁ |\n370\t| **minimized** (Dock genie) | РюЁ | РюЁ (no deminiaturize Рђћ AX actions fire on the minimized window in place) | РЮї silent no-op / system beep Рђћ use `set_value` or click equivalent | РЮї no on-screen bounds |\n371\t| hidden (`hides=true` / `NSApp.hide`) | РюЁ | РюЁ | depends | РЮї |\n372\t| on another Space | Рџа№ИЈ AX tree often stripped to menu-bar-only on SwiftUI apps (System Settings) Рђћ AppKit apps usually fine. Response carries `off_space: true` + `window_space_ids` so you can detect it | РюЁ | РюЁ | РЮї window not in current-Space list |\n373\t\n374\t**Critical cell Рђћ minimized + keyboard commit.** The keystroke\n375\treaches the app but AX focus doesn't propagate to renderer focus on\n376\ta minimized window. Workarounds in order of preference:\n377\t`set_value` to write the field's entire value directly, or AX-click\n378\ta commit-equivalent button (Go, Submit, checkbox). Tell the user\n379\tthe window needs to un-minimize only as a last resort.\n380\t\n381\t## The canonical loop\n382\t\n383\t```\n384\tlaunch_app(target)\n385\t  Рєњ pick window_id from the returned `windows` array\n386\t    (or call list_windows(pid) separately)\n387\t  Рєњ get_window_state(pid, window_id)\n388\t    Рєњ [act]  # every action also takes (pid, window_id)\n389\t  Рєњ get_window_state(pid, window_id) Рєњ verify\n390\t```\n391\t\n392\t`launch_app` now returns a `windows` array alongside the pid, so the\n393\tcommon case collapses to two calls (`launch_app` Рєњ `get_window_state`)\n394\twithout a separate `list_windows` hop.\n395\t\n396\t### 1. Resolve target pid Рђћ always via `launch_app`\n397\t\n398\t**Always start with `launch_app`**, whether or not the target is already\n399\trunning. It's idempotent (relaunching returns the existing pid with no\n400\tside effects) and gives you the pid in one call Рђћ no `list_apps` hop.\n401\t\n402\t- `launch_app({bundle_id: \"com.apple.finder\"})` Рђћ preferred, unambiguous.\n403\t- `launch_app({name: \"Calculator\"})` Рђћ when bundle_id isn't known.\n404\t\n405\t`launch_app` is a **hidden-launch primitive by design** Рђћ that's the\n406\tentire point of cua-driver: agents drive apps in the background while\n407\tthe user keeps typing in their real foreground app. The target's\n408\twindow is initialized (AX tree fully populated, clickable via\n409\t`element_index`, the pid appears in `list_apps`) but not drawn on\n410\tscreen. The driver never activates or unhides apps on its own; that\n411\twould violate the no-foreground contract the whole driver exists to\n412\tprotect.\n413\t\n414\tIf the user explicitly wants the window visible (usually for a demo\n415\tor recording), they unhide it themselves Рђћ Dock click, Cmd-Tab, or\n416\tSpotlight. Do not reach for `open` / `osascript activate` as a\n417\tshortcut to make the window visible; those paths break the backgrounded\n418\tinvariant on every call, not just the call that \"needed\" the\n419\tforeground. Say out loud what the user needs to do (\"click the\n420\tTodo app in your Dock to bring it forward\") and let them do it.\n421\t\n422\tNever shell out to **any** form of `open` (including `open\n423\t<path-to-App.app>` for a just-built binary Рђћ resolve the bundle id\n424\tfrom `Info.plist` and use `launch_app` with that), `osascript 'tell\n425\tapp Рђд to launch/open'`, or similar. Those paths activate the target,\n426\tbypass the driver's focus-restore guard, and require a Bash\n427\tpermission prompt the agent loop shouldn't be burning on app launch.\n428\tSee \"Prefer cua-driver tools over shell shims\" above for the full\n429\tintent Рєњ tool mapping.\n430\t\n431\t`list_apps` is for app-level discovery (answering \"what's installed /\n432\trunning / frontmost?\") Рђћ not part of the core action loop. Skip it in\n433\tthe loop. For **window-level** questions Рђћ \"does this app have a\n434\tvisible window?\", \"which Space is this window on?\", \"which of this\n435\tpid's windows is the main one?\" Рђћ call `list_windows` instead; the\n436\tapp record doesn't carry window state on purpose. In the common\n437\tsingle-window case you can skip `list_windows` entirely and read the\n438\t`windows` array that `launch_app` already returned.\n439\t\n440\t### 2. Snapshot and act by element_index\n441\t\n442\tCall `get_window_state({pid, window_id})` with the `window_id` from\n443\t`launch_app`'s `windows` array (or a fresh `list_windows({pid})` if\n444\tyou're interacting with a long-lived process). The default `som`\n445\tcapture_mode returns **both the AX tree and screenshot**, so the\n446\tcanonical loop works immediately without any config change. The rest\n447\tof this section walks through `som` mode. If you're in `vision` mode\n448\t(PNG only, no AX tree), flip back: `cua-driver set_config '{\"key\":\n449\t\"capture_mode\", \"value\": \"som\"}'`.\n450\t\n451\tIn `som` mode (the default) the response carries:\n452\t\n453\t- `tree_markdown` Рђћ every actionable element tagged `[N]`. That `N`\n454\t  is the `element_index`. The tree can be very large (Finder is\n455\t  ~1600 elements, ~190 KB); when it exceeds token limits the MCP\n456\t  harness saves it to a file and returns the path. Use `Bash` +\n457\t  `jq -r '.tree_markdown'` + `grep` to pull the section you need.\n458\t- `screenshot_file_path` Рђћ absolute path to the saved screenshot when\n459\t  `screenshot_out_file` was passed. Absent otherwise.\n460\t- `screenshot_width` / `_height` / `_scale_factor` Рђћ dimensions of the\n461\t  captured image. Present whenever a screenshot was taken.\n462\t**Getting the screenshot as a file (CLI and context-constrained agents):**\n463\t\n464\t```bash\n465\t# write to file Рђћ stdout stays readable (AX tree / summary only, no base64)\n466\tcua-driver get_window_state '{\"pid\":N,\"window_id\":W,\"screenshot_out_file\":\"/tmp/shot.jpg\"}'\n467\t\n468\t# CLI --screenshot-out-file flag is equivalent and works for all capture modes\n469\tcua-driver get_window_state '{\"pid\":N,\"window_id\":W}' --screenshot-out-file /tmp/shot.jpg\n470\t```\n471\t\n472\tPass `screenshot_out_file` when using `get_window_state` via CLI or from an\n473\tagent whose context window can't absorb ~31 KB of inline base64 (e.g.\n474\tOpenCode with a local Ollama model). The MCP image content block is omitted\n475\tfrom the response when this param is set Рђћ the model receives only the AX\n476\ttree and `screenshot_file_path`, then reads the image from disk.\n477\t\n478\t**Reason over both the tree AND the screenshot Рђћ they're\n479\tcomplementary, not redundant.** In `som` mode every\n480\tturn's `get_window_state` gives you both halves and you should pull\n481\tsignal from each:\n482\t\n483\t- The **AX tree** tells you *what's clickable* Рђћ roles, labels,\n484\t  `element_index` handles, advertised actions, parent-child\n485\t  structure. This is the ground truth for dispatching.\n486\t- The **screenshot** tells you *which one* Рђћ the tree often has\n487\t  many buttons with similar or empty labels (\"Delete\", \"OK\",\n488\t  anonymous UUID-labeled buttons, five `AXStaticText = \" \"`), and\n489\t  visual context disambiguates. Captions, colors, layout relationships\n490\t  visible in pixels often don't show up in the AX tree at all\n491\t  (especially in Chromium / Electron / web content).\n492\t\n493\tCanonical pattern: look at the screenshot to decide \"the blue\n494\tSubscribe button on the top-right of the video card\", then walk the\n495\ttree to find the matching `AXButton` and dispatch by its\n496\t`element_index`. Don't try to do it from just the tree Рђћ you'll\n497\tpick the wrong element when labels repeat. Don't try to do it from\n498\tjust the screenshot Рђћ you lose the reliable AX-action path and the\n499\tsafe backgrounded-dispatch.\n500\t\n501\tReach for pixel coordinates only when the target is a canvas /\n502\tvideo / WebGL / custom-drawn surface that isn't in the AX tree\n503\t(see Pixel-coordinate clicks below).\n504\t\n505\tThe `actions=[...]` list on each element is **advisory**, not\n506\tauthoritative. cua-driver does not pre-flight check against it Рђћ\n507\t`click({pid, element_index})` always attempts `AXPress` (or the\n508\taction you pass) and surfaces whatever the target returns. Many\n509\tapps accept `AXPress` on elements that don't advertise it Рђћ Chrome's\n510\tomnibox suggestion `AXMenuItem` is a live example. **Try the click\n511\tfirst** Рђћ pivot only on the returned AX error code.\n512\t\n513\tDispatch table (every row assumes a `(pid, window_id)` pair from the\n514\tlast `get_window_state`; `window_id` is required alongside\n515\t`element_index`, ignored on pixel-only forms unless you want to\n516\tanchor the conversion against a specific window):\n517\t\n518\t| Intent | Tool | Notes |\n519\t|---|---|---|\n520\t| List an app's windows | `list_windows({pid})` | returns `window_id`, `title`, `bounds`, `z_index`, `is_on_screen`, `on_current_space`. Already included in `launch_app`'s response Рђћ only call this for long-lived pids |\n521\t| Snapshot a window | `get_window_state({pid, window_id})` | returns `tree_markdown` + `screenshot_*`; populates the `(pid, window_id)` element_index cache |\n522\t| Left click | `click({pid, window_id, element_index})` | default `action: \"press\"`. Pixel form: `click({pid, x, y})` (window_id optional Рђћ when supplied, pinpoints the anchor window) Рђћ `modifier: [\"cmd\"]` |\n523\t| Double-click / open | `double_click({pid, window_id, element_index})` | AXOpen when advertised (Finder items, openable rows); else stamped pixel double-click at the element's center. Pixel form: `double_click({pid, x, y})` Рђћ primer-gated recipe lands on backgrounded Chromium web content (YouTube fullscreen, Finder open-on-dbl). `click({..., count: 2})` still works and routes through the same recipe; `double_click` is the intent-first spelling |\n524\t| Right click / context menu | `right_click({pid, window_id, element_index})` or `click({pid, window_id, element_index, action: \"show_menu\"})` | Chromium web-content coerces pixel right-click to left Рђћ see `WEB_APPS.md` |\n525\t| Type at cursor | `type_text({pid, text, window_id, element_index})` | `AXSelectedText` write; focuses first |\n526\t| Set whole field value | `set_value({pid, window_id, element_index, value})` | sliders, steppers, text fields; **use for keyboard-commit workarounds on minimized windows** |\n527\t| Scroll | `scroll({pid, direction, amount, by, window_id, element_index})` | synthesizes PageUp/PageDown/arrows via SLEventPostToPid |\n528\t| Focus + send key | `press_key({pid, key, window_id, element_index, modifiers})` | element_index sets AXFocused, then posts key |\n529\t| Send key to pid | `press_key({pid, key, modifiers})` | no focus change; key goes to pid's current focus |\n530\t| Modifier combo | `hotkey({pid, keys})` | e.g. `[\"cmd\",\"c\"]`; posted per-pid, not HID tap |\n531\t| Unicode keystrokes | `type_text({pid, text, delay_ms})` | AX write with automatic CGEvent fallback; reaches Chromium/Electron inputs |\n532\t\n533\t**All keyboard/text primitives require `pid`.** There is no\n534\tfrontmost-routed variant Рђћ every key goes to the named target via\n535\t`CGEvent.postToPid`, so the driver cannot leak keystrokes into the\n536\tuser's foreground app.\n537\t\n538\t**Why `element_index` is the primary path:** works on hidden /\n539\toccluded / off-Space windows, no focus steal, stable across\n540\trebuilds, labels tell you what you're clicking. Reach for pixel\n541\tcoordinates only when AX can't.\n542\t\n543\t### Pixel-coordinate clicks\n544\t\n545\tThe pixel path (`click({pid, x, y})`) is for surfaces the AX tree\n546\tdoesn't reach Рђћ canvases, video players, WebGL, custom-drawn controls.\n547\tCoords are **window-local screenshot pixels** (same space as the PNG\n548\t`get_window_state` returns). Top-left origin, y-down. The driver\n549\thandles screen-point conversion internally. Passing `window_id`\n550\talongside `x, y` is optional but recommended Рђћ it pins the\n551\tcoordinate conversion to the window whose screenshot produced the\n552\tpixel, rather than the driver's heuristic choice.\n553\t\n554\t#### Reading coordinates from the PNG\n555\t\n556\tPNGs returned by `get_window_state` are capped at **1568 px\n557\tlong-side by default** (`max_image_dimension` config), matching\n558\tAnthropic's multimodal-vision downsampling limit. That means the\n559\timage the model reasons over and the image the click tool's\n560\tcoordinate system lives in are the **same resolution** Рђћ just look\n561\tat the PNG, pick a pixel, click at that pixel. No scaling math.\n562\t\n563\tThis is the default because the mismatch between \"rendered\n564\tthumbnail\" and \"native PNG\" was a recurring coord-estimation\n565\tfootgun. If you opt out (explicit `max_image_dimension=0` for\n566\tpixel-perfect verification flows), the old rule applies: don't\n567\teyeball coords from whatever your client renders Рђћ it may be\n568\t2-4├Ќ smaller than the PNG on disk, and a 2% error in thumbnail\n569\tspace becomes ~80 px in the real image. Use the crosshair recipe\n570\tbelow against the full-resolution file in that case.\n571\t\n572\t1. `get_window_state({pid, window_id})` returns an image capped\n573\t   at 1568 long-side (default) plus its dimensions\n574\t   (`screenshot_width` / `screenshot_height`). Write the bytes to\n575\t   disk with `--screenshot-out-file <path>` in any capture mode Рђћ works\n576\t   identically in `vision` (where it's the only way) and `som`\n577\t   (where it sidesteps the jq + base64 dance on the spliced\n578\t   `screenshot_png_b64` field).\n579\t2. You are a multimodal model Рђћ look at the PNG. Since the PNG\n580\t   matches what you see, pick the target pixel directly. No\n581\t   fractional math needed.\n582\t3. When precision matters (small targets, dense UIs), draw a\n583\t   crosshair on the image (do **not** crop Рђћ cropping loses the\n584\t   coordinate system and requires error-prone offset math) and\n585\t   show it before clicking:\n586\t\n587\t```python\n588\tfrom PIL import Image, ImageDraw\n589\timg = Image.open('/tmp/shot.png')\n590\tdraw = ImageDraw.Draw(img)\n591\tx, y = <your_coordinate>\n592\tr = 18\n593\tdraw.ellipse([x-r, y-r, x+r, y+r], outline='red', width=4)\n594\tdraw.line([x-30, y, x+30, y], fill='red', width=3)\n595\tdraw.line([x, y-30, x, y+30], fill='red', width=3)\n596\timg.save('/tmp/shot_annotated.png')\n597\t```\n598\t\n599\t4. Only dispatch the click after the user (or your own re-read of\n600\t   the annotated image) confirms the crosshair is on target.\n601\t\n602\t#### Addressing variants\n603\t\n604\t- `click({pid, x, y})` Рђћ single left-click.\n605\t- `click({pid, x, y, count: 2})` Рђћ double-click.\n606\t- `click({pid, x, y, modifier: [\"cmd\"]})` Рђћ cmd-click. Accepts any\n607\t  subset of `cmd/shift/option/ctrl`.\n608\t- `right_click({pid, x, y})` Рђћ also takes `modifier`.\n609\t\n610\tThe pixel path animates the agent cursor overlay but never warps\n611\tthe real cursor. If the pid has no on-screen window the call errors\n612\twith `pid X has no on-screen window` Рђћ you need a visible window to\n613\tanchor the conversion.\n614\t\n615\t#### How the pixel click is dispatched\n616\t\n617\tThe recipe is the backgrounded \"noraise\" sequence: yabai's\n618\tfocus-without-raise SLPS event records followed by an off-screen\n619\tuser-activation primer and the real click, all stamped via\n620\t`SLEventPostToPid`. The target app becomes AppKit-active for event\n621\trouting but its window does **not** rise to the front of the\n622\tz-stack, and macOS's \"switch to Space with windows for app\" follow\n623\tis suppressed. Full mechanics in\n624\t`Sources/CuaDriverCore/Input/MouseInput.swift` (`clickViaAuthSignedPost`)\n625\tand the companion `FocusWithoutRaise.swift`.\n626\t\n627\t#### Known limits\n628\t\n629\t- **Chromium `<video>` play/pause**: pixel click is often rejected\n630\t  by HTML5's click-to-play handler on some builds. Use keyboard\n631\t  instead: `press_key({pid, key: \"k\"})` (YouTube) or\n632\t  `press_key({pid, key: \"space\"})` (generic). Keyboard events\n633\t  travel through a different auth envelope.\n634\t- **Pixel right-click on Chromium web content** coerces to a\n635\t  left-click Рђћ a known Chromium renderer-IPC limitation that affects\n636\t  every non-HID-tap synthesis path. For context menus on\n637\t  AX-addressable elements (links, buttons, toolbar items), use\n638\t  `right_click({pid, element_index})` instead.\n639\t\n640\t### Canvases, viewports, games (Blender, Unity, GHOST, Qt, wxWidgets)\n641\t\n642\tApps whose main surface is an OpenGL / Metal / Qt / wxWidgets\n643\tviewport expose **no useful AX tree** Рђћ the whole surface is one\n644\topaque `AXGroup` or `AXWindow` from AX's perspective. Per-pid event\n645\tpaths (`SLEventPostToPid`, `CGEvent.postToPid`) are filtered by the\n646\tviewport's own event-source check and silently dropped Рђћ the event\n647\tloop wants \"real HID origin\".\n648\t\n649\tThe working pattern:\n650\t\n651\t1. Bring the target frontmost (a brief `osascript activate` is\n652\t   acceptable here Рђћ this is the carve-out the skill's osascript\n653\t   gate allows).\n654\t2. `CGEvent.post(tap: .cghidEventTap)` with a leading `mouseMoved`\n655\t   event (~30 ms before the click). `cua-driver click` when the\n656\t   target is frontmost automatically takes this path.\n657\t3. Accept that the real cursor visibly moves Рђћ `cghidEventTap` is\n658\t   the system HID stream, the cursor warps to the click point.\n659\t\n660\tThere is no backgrounded path that reaches these apps today.\n661\t\n662\t## Navigating native menu bars (AXMenuBar)\n663\t\n664\t**Only drive the menu bar when the target app is frontmost.** This\n665\tis the single most-misused cua-driver capability. If the target is\n666\tbackgrounded, don't reach for `AXMenuBarItem` + AXPick Рђћ use\n667\tin-window `element_index` or pixel clicks instead. Two reasons, one\n668\tfunctional and one perceptual:\n669\t\n670\t- **Functional:** menu items that touch document/playback/editor\n671\t  state go `DISABLED` when their owning app isn't the key window\n672\t  (Preview rotate, IINA speed change, most editor commands). AXPick\n673\t  + AXPress will dispatch successfully from the driver's side but\n674\t  no-op at the target Рђћ you get a silent false-pass.\n675\t- **Perceptual (matters for demos, screen recordings, and anything\n676\t  the user watches live):** macOS's screen-rendered menu bar\n677\t  always belongs to the *frontmost* app. AXPick on a backgrounded\n678\t  app's `AXMenuBarItem` dispatches to that app's per-process menu at\n679\t  the AX layer, but any visible menu render happens over the\n680\t  frontmost app's menu bar Рђћ the viewer sees an IINA submenu\n681\t  flashing on top of Chrome's menus, which reads as \"the agent\n682\t  clicked the wrong app.\" The AX call was correct; the frame the\n683\t  user sees is not. For recorded or observed sessions, this is an\n684\t  integrity bug even though it's not a correctness bug.\n685\t\n686\t**Good decision rule:** if the target is not already frontmost, do\n687\tnot use `AXMenuBarItem` at all. For *reading* in-window state,\n688\tsnapshot the window AX tree Рђћ most apps expose the same state via\n689\tan in-window `AXStaticText`, title bar, or toolbar. For *dispatching*\n690\tactions, use in-window `element_index` (buttons, toolbar items) or\n691\tpixel clicks on in-window controls Рђћ both dispatch via AppKit's\n692\twindow-under-pointer hit-test and are **not** frontmost-gated.\n693\t\n694\tWhen the target IS frontmost, the menu-bar flow below is fine and\n695\tthe canonical path for menus.\n696\t\n697\t### The two-snapshot pattern (target frontmost only)\n698\t\n699\tMenu contents are a two-snapshot flow. Closed AXMenu subtrees are\n700\tdeliberately skipped during snapshot Рђћ otherwise every app's File /\n701\tEdit / View hierarchy plus every Recent Items macOS has ever seen\n702\twould inflate the tree 10-100x. But once a menu is *open*, its\n703\tAXMenuItem children do receive `element_index` values so you can\n704\tclick them normally.\n705\t\n706\t1. Find the `[N] AXMenuBarItem \"<Menu Name>\"` in the tree.\n707\t2. `click({pid, element_index: N, action: \"pick\"})` Рђћ menu bar items\n708\t   implement `AXPick` (\"open my submenu\"), not `AXPress`. Using the\n709\t   default action on an AXMenuBarItem is a no-op.\n710\t3. Re-snapshot. The expanded menu's items now appear under the bar\n711\t   item as `[M] AXMenuItem \"<Item Name>\"`.\n712\t4. Click the target item Рђћ most items respond to `AXPress` (default\n713\t   action). Submenus nest under the item and are walked the same way.\n714\t5. Re-snapshot and verify.\n715\t\n716\tIf you ever need to back out without selecting, `press_key({pid, key:\n717\t\"escape\"})` closes the open menu. Leaving a menu expanded between\n718\tturns poisons subsequent snapshots for that pid.\n719\t\n720\t### Commands gated on the target being frontmost\n721\t\n722\tSome menu items and global shortcuts (Preview's Tools Рєњ Rotate\n723\tRight, РїўR; anything in the View menu that manipulates the current\n724\tdocument; most editor commands) are **disabled unless the target\n725\tapp is the key / frontmost window**. You'll see it in the AX tree\n726\tas `DISABLED` on the menu item even though the user's intent is\n727\tobviously valid.\n728\t\n729\tBefore activating, confirm you're in this narrow case Рђћ the menu\n730\titem still reads `DISABLED` after a fresh snapshot AND the action\n731\tthe user requested genuinely requires frontmost (Preview rotate,\n732\tView menu document manipulation, editor commands). If either\n733\tcheck fails, don't activate.\n734\t\n735\tWhen both checks pass, the driver has no `activate` tool\n736\t(deliberately Рђћ the whole point is backgroundable control), so\n737\tthis is the one legitimate `osascript` fallback:\n738\t\n739\t```\n740\tosascript -e 'tell application \"<App Name>\" to activate'\n741\t```\n742\t\n743\tThen re-snapshot Рђћ the menu item loses its `DISABLED` tag Рђћ and\n744\t`click({action: \"pick\"})` the item. Alternatively, a `hotkey`\n745\tcall delivered to the now-frontmost app works for the shortcut\n746\tform (`РїўR`, `Рїў+`, etc.).\n747\t\n748\t**Always name the focus steal in your response** so the user isn't\n749\tsurprised Рђћ \"Briefly activating Preview to enable Tools Рєњ Rotate\n750\tRight\" or similar. Don't silently steal focus. You don't need to\n751\trestore the previous frontmost afterwards unless the user asks Рђћ\n752\tthey can cmd-tab back.\n753\t\n754\t## Web-rendered apps (browsers, Electron, Tauri)\n755\t\n756\tFor Chrome / Edge / Brave / Arc / Safari, Electron apps (Slack,\n757\tVSCode, Notion, Discord), and Tauri apps Рђћ see **`WEB_APPS.md`**.\n758\t\n759\tCovers: sparse AX tree population (retry-once pattern for Chromium),\n760\tURL navigation via omnibox suggestions, the `set_value` workaround\n761\tfor keyboard commits on **minimized** windows (Return silently\n762\tno-ops Рђћ symptom is a macOS system beep; use `set_value` or click a\n763\tclickable equivalent), scrolling via synthetic PageUp/Down keystrokes,\n764\tin-page clicks, and typing into web inputs.\n765\t\n766\tChromium web content specifically also coerces `right_click` back to\n767\tleft Рђћ use `element_index` for AX-addressable targets and accept the\n768\tlimit otherwise.\n769\t\n770\t### Browser JS primitives Рђћ `page` tool and `get_window_state(javascript=)`\n771\t\n772\tWhen the AX tree doesn't expose the data you need (common in\n773\tChromium/Electron Рђћ the tree is sparse for web content), use the\n774\t`page` tool or the `javascript` param on `get_window_state` to query\n775\tthe DOM directly via Apple Events. Requires \"Allow JavaScript from\n776\tApple Events\" to be enabled Рђћ see `WEB_APPS.md` for the setup path.\n777\t\n778\t**Three actions on the `page` tool:**\n779\t\n780\t- `page({pid, window_id, action: \"get_text\"})` Рђћ returns\n781\t  `document.body.innerText`. Fastest way to read page content, prices,\n782\t  article text, or any raw text the AX tree truncates or omits.\n783\t\n784\t- `page({pid, window_id, action: \"query_dom\", css_selector: \"a[href]\",\n785\t  attributes: [\"href\"]})` Рђћ runs `querySelectorAll` and returns each\n786\t  match's tag, text, and requested attributes as a JSON array. Use for\n787\t  table rows, link hrefs, data attributes, structured page data.\n788\t\n789\t- `page({pid, window_id, action: \"execute_javascript\", javascript:\n790\t  \"...\"})` Рђћ raw JS. Wrap in an IIFE with try-catch. Don't use this for\n791\t  elements already indexed by `get_window_state` Рђћ `click` and\n792\t  `set_value` are more reliable there.\n793\t\n794\t**Co-located read Рђћ `get_window_state` with `javascript`:**\n795\t\n796\t```\n797\tget_window_state({pid, window_id, javascript: \"document.title\"})\n798\t```\n799\t\n800\tRuns the JS and appends the result as a `## JavaScript result` section\n801\talongside the AX snapshot Рђћ one round-trip instead of two. Use this\n802\twhen you need both the element tree (for subsequent clicks) and some\n803\tpage data in the same turn.\n804\t\n805\t**Decision rule Рђћ AX vs JS:**\n806\t\n807\t| Need | Use |\n808\t|---|---|\n809\t| Click / type into an element | `get_window_state` Рєњ `click` / `set_value` (AX, works backgrounded) |\n810\t| Read text the AX tree drops | `page(get_text)` or `get_window_state(javascript=)` |\n811\t| Scrape structured data (tables, hrefs) | `page(query_dom)` |\n812\t| Trigger JS events / mutations | `page(execute_javascript)` |\n813\t\n814\tSupported backends:\n815\t\n816\t| App type | How | Context |\n817\t|---|---|---|\n818\t| Chrome / Brave / Edge | Apple Events `execute javascript` | Full DOM РюЁ |\n819\t| Safari | Apple Events `do JavaScript` | Full DOM РюЁ |\n820\t| Electron (VS Code, CursorРђд) | SIGUSR1 Рєњ V8 inspector Рєњ CDP | Main process only: `process`, `Buffer` Рђћ no `document`, no `require` in sandboxed apps |\n821\t| Electron (with `--remote-debugging-port`) | CDP page target | Full DOM РюЁ |\n822\t\n823\t**Electron sandbox note:** SIGUSR1 connects to the Node.js *main* process.\n824\tSandboxed Electron apps (VS Code, Cursor) strip `require` and Electron\n825\tAPIs there. Useful for: `process.env`, `process.versions`, `process.cwd()`,\n826\t`process.pid`. For full DOM/renderer access, launch the app with\n827\t`--remote-debugging-port=9222` Рђћ cua-driver will detect and prefer the\n828\tpage target automatically.\n829\t\n830\tArc returns no values; Firefox has no JS-via-AppleEvents support Рђћ see\n831\t`WEB_APPS.md` for the full matrix.\n832\t\n833\t### 3. Re-snapshot and verify Рђћ mandatory\n834\t\n835\t**Always** call `get_window_state({pid, window_id})` after the action.\n836\tThis isn't optional verification Рђћ it's the second half of the\n837\tsnapshot invariant.\n838\t\n839\tCheck the AX tree diff: a changed value, a new element, a new\n840\twindow, or the disappearance of the thing you just clicked (menus\n841\tcollapse after selection, buttons may become disabled, etc.). If\n842\tnothing changed, the action likely failed silently Рђћ **tell the\n843\tuser what you attempted and what you observed**, don't paper over\n844\twith \"done\" language. Agents that skip this step report success on\n845\tsilently-dropped actions Рђћ the single most common failure mode.\n846\t\n847\t## Recording trajectories\n848\t\n849\tSession-scoped action recording + replay, for demos, regressions, and\n850\ttraining data. Only invoke when the user explicitly asks to record a\n851\tsession Рђћ the skill does not auto-enable this. CLI surface:\n852\t`cua-driver recording start|stop|status`; raw tool: `set_recording`.\n853\t\n854\tSee **`RECORDING.md`** for the full flow: enable/disable, turn folder\n855\tcontents, replay via `replay_trajectory`, and the element_index\n856\tdoesn't-survive-across-sessions caveat.\n857\t\n858\t## Common error patterns\n859\t\n860\t| Error text | Meaning | Fix |\n861\t|---|---|---|\n862\t| `No cached AX state for pid X window_id W` | You either skipped `get_window_state` this turn, or passed a different `window_id` to the click than the one the snapshot cached against | Call `get_window_state({pid: X, window_id: W})` first Рђћ the same window_id you intend to click in |\n863\t| `Invalid element_index N for pid X window_id W` | Index is stale or out of range | Re-run `get_window_state` with the same window_id, pick a fresh index from the new tree |\n864\t| `window_id W belongs to pid P, not Рђд` | Passed a window_id that's owned by a different process | Use `list_windows({pid: X})` to enumerate this pid's own windows |\n865\t| `AX action AXPress failed with code Рђд` | Element doesn't support AXPress | Try `show_menu`, `confirm`, `cancel`, or `pick` |\n866\t| macOS system-alert beep on `press_key` with no visible change | Target window is minimized; Return / Space / Tab commits don't establish real renderer focus on minimized windows | AX-click a clickable equivalent (Go button, Submit button, checkbox) instead of pressing the key; see \"Keyboard commits on minimized windows\" under the Browser section |\n867\t| `Accessibility permission not granted` | TCC not granted | Stop; tell user to grant in System Settings |\n868\t| `Screen Recording permission not granted` | TCC not granted for capture | Affects `screenshot` and `get_window_state` (which always captures). Grant in System Settings Рђћ the driver can't operate without it |\n869\t\n870\t## Things to avoid\n871\t\n872\t- **Never** reuse an `element_index` across a re-snapshot of the same pid.\n873\t- **Never** translate screenshot pixels into a click Рђћ the screenshot\n874\t  is for visual disambiguation, not coordinates. Use the\n875\t  `element_index`.\n876\t- **Prefer AX over pixels.** `click({pid, x, y})` works for\n877\t  canvas / WebView regions, but it lands blindly and skips the\n878\t  agent-cursor overlay. Exhaust AX paths (menu bars, cmd-k palettes,\n879\t  toolbar items, keyboard shortcuts) before dropping to coordinates.\n880\t- **Never** drive destructive actions (delete files, close unsaved\n881\t  documents, send messages, submit forms) without explicit user\n882\t  intent for that specific destructive step.\n883\t- **Never** launch apps autonomously; confirm with the user first\n884\t  unless their original request clearly implies the launch.\n885\t\n886\t## Example end-to-end task\n887\t\n888\t**User:** \"Open the Downloads folder in Finder.\"\n889\t\n890\t1. `launch_app({bundle_id: \"com.apple.finder\", urls: [\"~/Downloads\"]})`\n891\t   Рєњ `{pid: 844, windows: [{window_id: 6123, title: \"Downloads\", ...}]}`.\n892\t   Idempotent launch; plus Finder opens a hidden window rooted at\n893\t   `~/Downloads` via `application(_:open:)` Рђћ zero activation, no\n894\t   focus steal. The `windows` array lets you skip a `list_windows` hop.\n895\t2. `get_window_state({pid: 844, window_id: 6123})` Рєњ verify an\n896\t   `AXWindow` whose title contains \"Downloads\" is present with a\n897\t   populated AX subtree (sidebar, list view, files).\n898\t3. Done.\n899\t\n900\tIf the user instead asks to navigate *within* an already-open Finder\n901\twindow, use the menu-bar flow from the \"Navigating native menu bars\"\n902\tsection above (click Go Рєњ pick a menu item Рєњ re-snapshot Рєњ click it).\n903\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9ae2b347-5aa4-4079-9d46-d9fc7aba3cef","uuid":"c21ca76e-b792-4f90-8e70-adb48f43a27d","timestamp":"2026-05-21T20:28:39.009Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/zhiwei/projects/computer-use/.claude/skills/cua-driver/SKILL.md","content":"---\nname: cua-driver\ndescription: Drive a native desktop app via the cua-driver CLI (default) or MCP server Рђћ snapshot its accessibility tree, click/type/scroll by element_index, verify via re-snapshot. Backend is auto-selected per platform: macOS uses the Swift `cua-driver` (mature), Linux/Windows use the Rust port `cua-driver-rs`. The CLI/MCP surface is identical across backends. Use when the user asks you to operate, drive, automate, or perform a GUI task in a real desktop application on the host (e.g. \"open a file in TextEdit\", \"click the Save button in Numbers\", \"fill the form in Notepad\").\n---\n\n# cua-driver\n\nOrchestrates desktop app automation via `cua-driver`. Whenever a user\nasks to drive a native app, follow the loop in this skill rather\nthan calling tools ad-hoc Рђћ the snapshot-before-action invariant is not\noptional and silently breaks if you skip it.\n\n## Backend selection\n\n| Host OS | Binary | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| macOS (arm64 / x86_64) | Swift `cua-driver` | mature, official, in `/Applications/CuaDriver.app` |\n| Linux x86_64 | `cua-driver-rs` (Rust port) | feature-complete on Linux |\n| Windows x86_64 | `cua-driver-rs` (Rust port) | installs via `install.ps1`, no admin required |\n| Linux aarch64 | not supported by prebuilts | source build only |\n\nThe CLI subcommands and MCP tools described in this skill are the\nsame across both backends. Anything that says \"macOS\" below applies\nspecifically to the Swift backend; Linux/Windows-only callouts are\nmarked. To install the right backend for the current host run\n`scripts/install_cua_driver.py` from this project.\n\n## The no-foreground contract Рђћ read this first\n\n**The user's frontmost app MUST NOT change.** This is the whole\nreason cua-driver exists. Users pay for the right to keep typing in\ntheir editor while an agent drives another app in the background.\nViolate this rule and every other nice property the driver gives\nyou (no cursor warp, no Space switch, no window raise) stops\nmattering Рђћ you just shipped the Accessibility Inspector with extra\nsteps.\n\nBefore running any shell command, ask: **\"does this raise,\nactivate, foreground, or make-key any app?\"** If yes, don't run it.\nEvery one of the commands below activates the target on macOS and\nis therefore forbidden unless the user **explicitly** asked for\nfrontmost state:\n\n- **Every form of the `open` CLI Рђћ `open -a <App>`, `open -b\n  <bundle-id>`, `open <file>`, `open <path-to-App.app>`, `open\n  <url>` Рђћ always activates.** macOS routes all forms through\n  LaunchServices, which unhides and foregrounds the target\n  regardless of whether you passed an app name, a bundle id, a\n  document, a URL, or the bundle path itself. The activation\n  happens even when the only intent was \"start the process.\"\n  **Never use `open` for any app launch.** This includes launching\n  a just-built .app from a local build dir (e.g. `open\n  build/Build/Products/Debug/MyApp.app`) Рђћ resolve the\n  `CFBundleIdentifier` from `Info.plist` and use `launch_app`\n  with that id. See \"The narrow carve-out\" below for why\n  `launch_app` is safe even when the app internally calls\n  `NSApp.activate`.\n- `osascript -e 'tell application \"X\" to activate'` Рђћ\n  activates by design. Same for `... to open <file>`,\n  `... to launch`, and anything with `activate` in the tell block.\n- `osascript -e 'tell application \"System Events\" to ... frontmost'`\n  in a mutating form (setting `frontmost` rather than reading it).\n- AppleScript files that invoke `activate`, `launch`, or `open`\n  against the target app.\n- `cliclick` (moves the user's real cursor to the target coords\n  before clicking Рђћ a focus-steal-equivalent even if the app's\n  window state is unchanged).\n- `CGEventPost` with `cghidEventTap` targeting a coordinate over\n  a different app's window (warps the cursor, possibly activates\n  on hit).\n- `AppleScriptTask`, `NSAppleScript`, `Process` wrapping `osascript`\n  that contains any of the above.\n- `NSRunningApplication.activate(options:)` called from your own\n  helper binary Рђћ same class.\n- Dock clicks and any `open` invocation (see the first bullet Рђћ\n  every form of `open` goes through LaunchServices which\n  activates, full stop).\n- **Keyboard shortcuts that semantically mean \"focus here\" Рђћ\n  most notably Chrome / Safari / Arc's `РїўL` (focus omnibox) and\n  Finder's `РїўРЄДG` (Go to Folder).** These aren't pure key events Рђћ\n  the receiving app interprets \"user wants to type here\" as\n  activation intent and raises its window to be key. Even when\n  delivered to a backgrounded pid via `hotkey`, the downstream app\n  pulls focus. **For omnibox navigation specifically**, the correct\n  path is `launch_app({bundle_id: \"com.google.Chrome\", urls:\n  [\"https://Рђд\"]})` Рђћ no omnibox dance, no `РїўL`, no focus-steal. Do\n  NOT try `set_value` on the omnibox: Chrome's commit logic requires\n  a \"user-typed\" signal that neither an AX value write nor\n  `CGEvent.postToPid` keystrokes supply from a backgrounded pid Рђћ\n  the URL lands in the field but Return fires as a no-op. See\n  `WEB_APPS.md` Рєњ \"Navigate to a URL\" for the full pattern. The\n  general principle: a shortcut that says \"put my cursor inside this\n  app\" is a focus-steal; a shortcut that says \"do this thing\" (copy,\n  save, quit) is fine.\n- **Tab-switching shortcuts in browsers (`Рїў1..Рїў9`, `Рїў]`, `Рїў[`,\n  `РїўРЄД[`, `РїўРЄД]`) are visibly disruptive even when delivered to a\n  backgrounded pid.** The app's key handler processes the shortcut,\n  the window re-renders the new tab's content, the user sees their\n  tabs flipping. There is no AX-only workaround: page content (HTML,\n  form state, `AXWebArea`) populates only for the focused tab;\n  inspecting a background tab requires activating it, which is the\n  visible flip. Observed with Dia; the same mechanic applies to every\n  Chromium-family browser (Chrome, Arc, Brave, Edge).\n\n  **Prefer the windows-over-tabs pattern**: for each URL you need to\n  drive backgrounded, use `launch_app({bundle_id, urls: [url]})` Рђћ\n  browsers open each URL in a new **window**. Each window has its own\n  `window_id`, its own AX tree, and can be inspected / interacted with\n  via `element_index` without activating or switching anything. Tabs\n  are a UX grouping for humans; cua-driver workflows should default to\n  windows. See `WEB_APPS.md` Рєњ \"Tabs vs windows\" for the full pattern.\n\n  Tab-title enumeration (read-only) IS safe Рђћ walk a window's toolbar\n  AX tree for `AXTab` / `AXRadioButton` children and read their\n  `AXTitle`s. Tab switching (activating one) is not.\n\nReading frontmost state is fine (`osascript -e 'tell application\n\"System Events\" to get name of first application process whose\nfrontmost is true'`). Mutating it is not.\n\n**Corollary Рђћ the AXMenuBar rule.** `AXMenuBarItem` + AXPick\ndispatches at the AX layer regardless of which app is frontmost,\nbut macOS's on-screen menu bar always belongs to the frontmost\napp. If you drive a *backgrounded* app's menu bar, the AX call\nsucceeds but the viewer sees the dispatch rendered over the\n*frontmost* app's menu bar Рђћ confusing in any observed session and\nroutinely a silent no-op too, because action menu items go\n`DISABLED` when their owning app isn't the key window. **So: only\nuse menu-bar navigation when the target is already frontmost.** For\nbackgrounded targets, read state via in-window AX (window title,\ntoolbar `AXStaticText`) and dispatch via in-window `element_index`\nor pixel clicks Рђћ both paths are frontmost-insensitive. Full\nrationale in \"Navigating native menu bars\" below.\n\n**\"Open \\<app\\>\" in user speech means launch, not activate.**\n`cua-driver launch_app` is the one correct path for process\nstartup Рђћ it's idempotent (no-op on a running app), returns the\npid, and has an internal `FocusRestoreGuard` that catches\n`NSApp.activate(ignoringOtherApps:)` calls the target makes during\n`application(_:open:)` and clobbers the frontmost back to what it\nwas before the launch. That guard is why `launch_app` with `urls`\n(e.g. `{\"bundle_id\": \"com.colliderli.iina\", \"urls\": [\"~/video.mp4\"]}`)\nis safe even for apps that normally foreground on media-load\n(Chrome, Electron, media players).\n\n## Defaults Рђћ always prefer cua-driver over shell shims\n\n**Default transport is the `cua-driver` CLI** Рђћ `Bash` shelling out\nto `cua-driver <tool-name> '<JSON-args>'`. MCP tools (prefix\n`mcp__cua-driver__*`) only when the user explicitly asks for them.\nCLI wins because it picks up rebuilds instantly, failures are\neasier to diagnose, and there's no per-tool schema-load overhead.\n\nEvery reference to `click(...)`, `get_window_state(...)` etc. in this\nskill means `cua-driver click '{...}'` Рђћ translate to MCP form only\nwhen MCP is requested.\n\n### Claude Code computer-use compatibility mode\n\nFor normal Claude Code use, keep the default CLI or `cua-driver` MCP server path above. If the user explicitly wants Claude Code's vision/computer-use-style flow, they can register:\n\n```bash\nclaude mcp add --transport stdio cua-computer-use -- cua-driver mcp --claude-code-computer-use-compat\n```\n\nObservation: Claude Code vision flows appear to treat a screenshot MCP tool as the image-grounding anchor. This compatibility mode keeps the normal CuaDriver tools and changes only `screenshot`. The compatibility `screenshot` requires `pid` and `window_id`, captures only that target window, and returns the window-local pixel coordinate frame. Start with `launch_app` or `list_windows`, then call `screenshot({pid, window_id})`; do not assume desktop coordinates or a full-screen capture.\n\nUse MCP for this Claude Code vision/computer-use-style path. Do not shell out to `cua-driver screenshot` as a substitute: CLI screenshots still work as CuaDriver calls, but they do not expose the `mcp__cua-computer-use__screenshot` tool name that Claude Code appears to use as the image-grounding cue.\n\nIntent Рєњ tool mapping. If you find yourself reaching for the right\ncolumn, something has gone wrong Рђћ re-read \"The no-foreground\ncontract\" above:\n\n| Intent | Use | Don't use |\n|---|---|---|\n| Open / launch an app | `launch_app({bundle_id})` or `launch_app({bundle_id, urls:[...]})` | `open -a`, `osascript 'tell app Рђд to launch/activate/open'` |\n| Find a pid | `list_apps` or `launch_app`'s return | `pgrep`, `ps`, `osascript frontmost` |\n| Enumerate an app's windows | `list_windows({pid})` Рђћ or read the `windows` array `launch_app` already returns | `osascript 'every window of app Рђд'` |\n| Click / type / scroll / keys | `click`, `type_text`, `scroll`, `press_key`, `hotkey` | `osascript`, `cliclick`, raw `CGEvent`, `open <url>` |\n| Drag / drag-and-drop / marquee select | `drag({pid, from_x, from_y, to_x, to_y})` (pixel-only Рђћ macOS AX has no semantic drag) | `cliclick dd:`, `osascript drag` |\n| Screenshot | `screenshot` or the PNG in `get_window_state` | `screencapture` |\n| Quit an app | ask the user first, then `hotkey({pid, keys:[\"cmd\",\"q\"]})` | `kill`, `killall`, `pkill` |\n| Hand a file/URL to an app | `launch_app({bundle_id, urls:[<path>]})` | `open -a <App> <path>`, `open <url>` |\n\n### The narrow carve-out\n\nThe **only** legitimate use of `osascript -e 'tell app X to\nactivate'` is when the user **explicitly** asked for frontmost\nstate (\"bring Chrome to the front\", \"make it frontmost\", \"I want\nto see X\"). Reaching for it because a tool call returned something\nconfusing is wrong Рђћ that's the skill's classic foot-in-the-door\nfailure mode and it steals focus every time.\n\nWhen a cua-driver call surprises you, diagnose cua-driver first:\n\n- **Tiny screenshot / empty `tree_markdown`?** Check\n  `cua-driver get_config` Рєњ `capture_mode`. Default `\"som\"` returns\n  both the AX tree and screenshot. `\"vision\"` omits the AX tree\n  (PNG only), `\"ax\"` omits the PNG. If a snapshot lacks a tree,\n  `capture_mode` is almost certainly `\"vision\"` Рђћ either reason\n  purely from the PNG or flip to `\"som\"` / `\"ax\"` via `set_config`.\n- **`has_screenshot: false`?** The window capture failed (transient\n  race against a close, or the window has no backing store yet).\n  Re-snapshot; if persistent, pick a different `window_id` via\n  `list_windows`.\n- **`Invalid element_index` / `No cached AX state`?** You either\n  skipped `get_window_state` this turn or passed a different\n  `window_id` than the one the snapshot cached against. The cache\n  is keyed on `(pid, window_id)` Рђћ indices don't carry across\n  windows of the same app. Re-snapshot with the same window_id\n  you're about to click in.\n- **Sparse Chromium AX tree?** Retry `get_window_state` once Рђћ the\n  tree populates on second call.\n\nOnly after those are ruled out, and only if the user's action\ngenuinely needs frontmost state, fall through to the activate\nfallback. Always name the focus steal in your response (\"I'll\nbriefly bring Chrome to the front because Рђд\").\n\n### Self-check pattern\n\nBefore every `Bash` call whose command line touches any macOS app\n(launching, opening, clicking, typing, scripting, screenshotting),\nrun the self-check:\n\n1. **Does this command foreground the target?** If yes Рђћ stop and\n   translate to the cua-driver equivalent from the mapping table.\n2. **Does this command move the user's real cursor?** (`cliclick`,\n   any `CGEventPost` at `cghidEventTap` over another app's window).\n   If yes Рђћ stop; use `click({pid, x, y})` which routes per-pid\n   via SkyLight and never warps the cursor.\n3. **Does this command bypass cua-driver entirely?** (`osascript`\n   mutating GUI state, AppleScript files, external helpers.) If\n   yes Рђћ stop; find the cua-driver tool that does the intent.\n\nIf all three are \"no,\" the command is safe. If you can't answer,\ndefault to stop and ask rather than proceed. A single `open -a`\nrun by accident kills the demo, the trust, and the user's in-flight\neditor state.\n\n## Prerequisites Рђћ check before starting\n\n1. `cua-driver` is on `$PATH` (`which cua-driver`). If not, point the\n   user at `scripts/install-local.sh` and stop.\n2. Run `cua-driver check_permissions` (with the daemon up Рђћ see step 3).\n   The default behavior also raises the system permission dialogs for\n   any missing grants, so the user can grant on the spot. If either\n   grant still reads `false` after that (user dismissed the dialog),\n   tell them to open System Settings Рєњ Privacy & Security and grant\n   Accessibility and Screen Recording to `CuaDriver.app`, then stop.\n   Pass `'{\"prompt\":false}'` for a purely read-only status check that\n   won't steal focus.\n3. Start the daemon with `open -n -g -a CuaDriver --args serve` (the\n   recommended form Рђћ goes through LaunchServices so TCC attributes\n   the process to CuaDriver.app). `cua-driver serve &` also works;\n   the CLI auto-relaunches through `open -n -g -a CuaDriver` when it\n   detects a wrong-TCC context (any IDE-spawned shell: Claude Code,\n   Cursor, VS Code, Conductor). Verify with `cua-driver status`.\n\n## Using cua-driver from the shell\n\nTool names are `snake_case`, management subcommands are\n`kebab-case` Рђћ no ambiguity. Tools invoked as `cua-driver\n<tool-name> '<JSON-args>'`. Management subcommands:\n\n- `open -n -g -a CuaDriver --args serve` Рђћ start persistent daemon\n  (**required** for `element_index` workflows; without it each CLI\n  invocation spawns a fresh process and the per-pid element cache\n  dies between calls). `cua-driver serve &` also works Рђћ the CLI\n  auto-relaunches via `open` when the shell's TCC context is wrong.\n  Pass `--no-relaunch` / `CUA_DRIVER_NO_RELAUNCH=1` to opt out.\n- `cua-driver stop` / `status`\n- `cua-driver list-tools`, `describe <tool>`\n- `cua-driver recording start|stop|status` Рђћ see `RECORDING.md`\n\nCanonical multi-step workflow:\n\n```\nopen -n -g -a CuaDriver --args serve\ncua-driver launch_app '{\"bundle_id\":\"com.apple.calculator\"}'\n# Рєњ {pid: 844, windows: [{window_id: 10725, ...}]}\ncua-driver get_window_state '{\"pid\":844,\"window_id\":10725}'\ncua-driver click '{\"pid\":844,\"window_id\":10725,\"element_index\":14}'\ncua-driver stop\n```\n\n## Agent cursor overlay\n\nVisual cursor overlay for demos and screen recordings. Default:\nenabled. Toggle with `cua-driver set_agent_cursor_enabled\n'{\"enabled\":true|false}'`. A triangle pointer Bezier-glides to each\nclick target, ring-ripples on landing, idle-hides after ~1.5s.\nMotion knobs: `set_agent_cursor_motion` takes any subset of\n`start_handle`, `end_handle`, `arc_size`, `arc_flow`, `spring` Рђћ\ntuneable at runtime, persisted to config.\n\nRequires an AppKit runloop, which `cua-driver serve` / `mcp`\nbootstraps. One-shot CLI invocations skip the overlay entirely.\n\n## The core invariant Рђћ snapshot before AND after every action\n\n**Every action MUST be bracketed by `get_window_state(pid, window_id)`**:\n\n- **Before** Рђћ the pre-action snapshot resolves the `element_index`\n  you're about to use. Indices from previous turns are stale; the\n  server replaces the element index map on every snapshot, keyed\n  on `(pid, window_id)`. Indices from turn N don't resolve in turn\n  N+1, and indices from window A don't resolve against window B of\n  the same app. Skip this and element-indexed actions fail with\n  `No cached AX state`.\n- **After** Рђћ the post-action snapshot verifies the action actually\n  landed. Without it you can't tell a silent no-op from a real\n  effect. The AX tree change (new value, new window, disappeared\n  menu, disabled button, etc.) is your evidence that the action\n  fired. If nothing changed, the action probably failed silently Рђћ\n  say so, don't assume success.\n\nThis applies to pixel clicks too Рђћ re-snapshot after to confirm the\nclick landed on the intended target.\n\n### Why window selection is the caller's job now\n\n`get_app_state` used to pick a window for you via a max-area heuristic\nthat returned the wrong surface on apps with large off-screen utility\npanels. Concrete reproducer: IINA's OpenSubtitles helper (600├Ќ432\noff-screen) out-area'd the visible 320├Ќ240 player window, so\n`get_app_state(pid)` screenshot'd the invisible panel and clicks landed\nthere silently. The new `get_window_state(pid, window_id)` makes the\ncaller name the window explicitly Рђћ the driver validates that the\nwindow belongs to the pid and is on the current Space, then snapshots\nexactly what was asked for. Enumerate candidates via `list_windows` or\nread the `windows` array `launch_app` already returns.\n\n## Behavior matrix\n\nTwo orthogonal axes shape what the agent can do.\n\n**capture_mode Рєњ addressing mode**\n\n| `capture_mode` | `get_window_state` returns | Use for actions |\n|---|---|---|\n| **`som`** (default) | tree + screenshot | `element_index` preferred; pixel fallback |\n| **`ax`** | tree only (no PNG) | `element_index` only |\n| **`vision`** | PNG only (no tree) | pixel only Рђћ see [SCREENSHOT.md](./SCREENSHOT.md) |\n\n`vision` was renamed from `screenshot` Рђћ the old name still decodes\nas a deprecated alias, so an on-disk `\"capture_mode\": \"screenshot\"`\nkeeps working. Default is `som` so element_index clicks work the\nfirst time a user calls `get_window_state`; the other modes are\nopt-in when the caller specifically doesn't want one half of the\nwork. Note the tool named `screenshot` is separate (raw PNG, no AX\nwalk) and unrelated to the capture mode.\n\nWhen a snapshot looks wrong (tiny screenshot / empty tree), check\n`cua-driver get_config` for `capture_mode` before anything else.\n\nPure-vision mode has its own caveats Рђћ Claude Code's vision\npipeline downsamples dense text aggressively, so pixel grounding\ntakes multiple correction cycles on text-heavy UIs. Read\n[SCREENSHOT.md](./SCREENSHOT.md) before driving anything in that\nmode; it documents the iterate/annotate/verify recipe plus the\nJPEG-over-PNG finding.\n\n**Window state Рєњ what works**\n\n| state | `get_window_state` | `click`/`set_value` (AX) | `press_key` commit (Return/Space/Tab) | pixel click |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| frontmost | РюЁ | РюЁ | РюЁ | РюЁ |\n| backgrounded / visible | РюЁ | РюЁ | РюЁ | РюЁ |\n| **minimized** (Dock genie) | РюЁ | РюЁ (no deminiaturize Рђћ AX actions fire on the minimized window in place) | РЮї silent no-op / system beep Рђћ use `set_value` or click equivalent | РЮї no on-screen bounds |\n| hidden (`hides=true` / `NSApp.hide`) | РюЁ | РюЁ | depends | РЮї |\n| on another Space | Рџа№ИЈ AX tree often stripped to menu-bar-only on SwiftUI apps (System Settings) Рђћ AppKit apps usually fine. Response carries `off_space: true` + `window_space_ids` so you can detect it | РюЁ | РюЁ | РЮї window not in current-Space list |\n\n**Critical cell Рђћ minimized + keyboard commit.** The keystroke\nreaches the app but AX focus doesn't propagate to renderer focus on\na minimized window. Workarounds in order of preference:\n`set_value` to write the field's entire value directly, or AX-click\na commit-equivalent button (Go, Submit, checkbox). Tell the user\nthe window needs to un-minimize only as a last resort.\n\n## The canonical loop\n\n```\nlaunch_app(target)\n  Рєњ pick window_id from the returned `windows` array\n    (or call list_windows(pid) separately)\n  Рєњ get_window_state(pid, window_id)\n    Рєњ [act]  # every action also takes (pid, window_id)\n  Рєњ get_window_state(pid, window_id) Рєњ verify\n```\n\n`launch_app` now returns a `windows` array alongside the pid, so the\ncommon case collapses to two calls (`launch_app` Рєњ `get_window_state`)\nwithout a separate `list_windows` hop.\n\n### 1. Resolve target pid Рђћ always via `launch_app`\n\n**Always start with `launch_app`**, whether or not the target is already\nrunning. It's idempotent (relaunching returns the existing pid with no\nside effects) and gives you the pid in one call Рђћ no `list_apps` hop.\n\n- `launch_app({bundle_id: \"com.apple.finder\"})` Рђћ preferred, unambiguous.\n- `launch_app({name: \"Calculator\"})` Рђћ when bundle_id isn't known.\n\n`launch_app` is a **hidden-launch primitive by design** Рђћ that's the\nentire point of cua-driver: agents drive apps in the background while\nthe user keeps typing in their real foreground app. The target's\nwindow is initialized (AX tree fully populated, clickable via\n`element_index`, the pid appears in `list_apps`) but not drawn on\nscreen. The driver never activates or unhides apps on its own; that\nwould violate the no-foreground contract the whole driver exists to\nprotect.\n\nIf the user explicitly wants the window visible (usually for a demo\nor recording), they unhide it themselves Рђћ Dock click, Cmd-Tab, or\nSpotlight. Do not reach for `open` / `osascript activate` as a\nshortcut to make the window visible; those paths break the backgrounded\ninvariant on every call, not just the call that \"needed\" the\nforeground. Say out loud what the user needs to do (\"click the\nTodo app in your Dock to bring it forward\") and let them do it.\n\nNever shell out to **any** form of `open` (including `open\n<path-to-App.app>` for a just-built binary Рђћ resolve the bundle id\nfrom `Info.plist` and use `launch_app` with that), `osascript 'tell\napp Рђд to launch/open'`, or similar. Those paths activate the target,\nbypass the driver's focus-restore guard, and require a Bash\npermission prompt the agent loop shouldn't be burning on app launch.\nSee \"Prefer cua-driver tools over shell shims\" above for the full\nintent Рєњ tool mapping.\n\n`list_apps` is for app-level discovery (answering \"what's installed /\nrunning / frontmost?\") Рђћ not part of the core action loop. Skip it in\nthe loop. For **window-level** questions Рђћ \"does this app have a\nvisible window?\", \"which Space is this window on?\", \"which of this\npid's windows is the main one?\" Рђћ call `list_windows` instead; the\napp record doesn't carry window state on purpose. In the common\nsingle-window case you can skip `list_windows` entirely and read the\n`windows` array that `launch_app` already returned.\n\n### 2. Snapshot and act by element_index\n\nCall `get_window_state({pid, window_id})` with the `window_id` from\n`launch_app`'s `windows` array (or a fresh `list_windows({pid})` if\nyou're interacting with a long-lived process). The default `som`\ncapture_mode returns **both the AX tree and screenshot**, so the\ncanonical loop works immediately without any config change. The rest\nof this section walks through `som` mode. If you're in `vision` mode\n(PNG only, no AX tree), flip back: `cua-driver set_config '{\"key\":\n\"capture_mode\", \"value\": \"som\"}'`.\n\nIn `som` mode (the default) the response carries:\n\n- `tree_markdown` Рђћ every actionable element tagged `[N]`. That `N`\n  is the `element_index`. The tree can be very large (Finder is\n  ~1600 elements, ~190 KB); when it exceeds token limits the MCP\n  harness saves it to a file and returns the path. Use `Bash` +\n  `jq -r '.tree_markdown'` + `grep` to pull the section you need.\n- `screenshot_file_path` Рђћ absolute path to the saved screenshot when\n  `screenshot_out_file` was passed. Absent otherwise.\n- `screenshot_width` / `_height` / `_scale_factor` Рђћ dimensions of the\n  captured image. Present whenever a screenshot was taken.\n**Getting the screenshot as a file (CLI and context-constrained agents):**\n\n```bash\n# write to file Рђћ stdout stays readable (AX tree / summary only, no base64)\ncua-driver get_window_state '{\"pid\":N,\"window_id\":W,\"screenshot_out_file\":\"/tmp/shot.jpg\"}'\n\n# CLI --screenshot-out-file flag is equivalent and works for all capture modes\ncua-driver get_window_state '{\"pid\":N,\"window_id\":W}' --screenshot-out-file /tmp/shot.jpg\n```\n\nPass `screenshot_out_file` when using `get_window_state` via CLI or from an\nagent whose context window can't absorb ~31 KB of inline base64 (e.g.\nOpenCode with a local Ollama model). The MCP image content block is omitted\nfrom the response when this param is set Рђћ the model receives only the AX\ntree and `screenshot_file_path`, then reads the image from disk.\n\n**Reason over both the tree AND the screenshot Рђћ they're\ncomplementary, not redundant.** In `som` mode every\nturn's `get_window_state` gives you both halves and you should pull\nsignal from each:\n\n- The **AX tree** tells you *what's clickable* Рђћ roles, labels,\n  `element_index` handles, advertised actions, parent-child\n  structure. This is the ground truth for dispatching.\n- The **screenshot** tells you *which one* Рђћ the tree often has\n  many buttons with similar or empty labels (\"Delete\", \"OK\",\n  anonymous UUID-labeled buttons, five `AXStaticText = \" \"`), and\n  visual context disambiguates. Captions, colors, layout relationships\n  visible in pixels often don't show up in the AX tree at all\n  (especially in Chromium / Electron / web content).\n\nCanonical pattern: look at the screenshot to decide \"the blue\nSubscribe button on the top-right of the video card\", then walk the\ntree to find the matching `AXButton` and dispatch by its\n`element_index`. Don't try to do it from just the tree Рђћ you'll\npick the wrong element when labels repeat. Don't try to do it from\njust the screenshot Рђћ you lose the reliable AX-action path and the\nsafe backgrounded-dispatch.\n\nReach for pixel coordinates only when the target is a canvas /\nvideo / WebGL / custom-drawn surface that isn't in the AX tree\n(see Pixel-coordinate clicks below).\n\nThe `actions=[...]` list on each element is **advisory**, not\nauthoritative. cua-driver does not pre-flight check against it Рђћ\n`click({pid, element_index})` always attempts `AXPress` (or the\naction you pass) and surfaces whatever the target returns. Many\napps accept `AXPress` on elements that don't advertise it Рђћ Chrome's\nomnibox suggestion `AXMenuItem` is a live example. **Try the click\nfirst** Рђћ pivot only on the returned AX error code.\n\nDispatch table (every row assumes a `(pid, window_id)` pair from the\nlast `get_window_state`; `window_id` is required alongside\n`element_index`, ignored on pixel-only forms unless you want to\nanchor the conversion against a specific window):\n\n| Intent | Tool | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| List an app's windows | `list_windows({pid})` | returns `window_id`, `title`, `bounds`, `z_index`, `is_on_screen`, `on_current_space`. Already included in `launch_app`'s response Рђћ only call this for long-lived pids |\n| Snapshot a window | `get_window_state({pid, window_id})` | returns `tree_markdown` + `screenshot_*`; populates the `(pid, window_id)` element_index cache |\n| Left click | `click({pid, window_id, element_index})` | default `action: \"press\"`. Pixel form: `click({pid, x, y})` (window_id optional Рђћ when supplied, pinpoints the anchor window) Рђћ `modifier: [\"cmd\"]` |\n| Double-click / open | `double_click({pid, window_id, element_index})` | AXOpen when advertised (Finder items, openable rows); else stamped pixel double-click at the element's center. Pixel form: `double_click({pid, x, y})` Рђћ primer-gated recipe lands on backgrounded Chromium web content (YouTube fullscreen, Finder open-on-dbl). `click({..., count: 2})` still works and routes through the same recipe; `double_click` is the intent-first spelling |\n| Right click / context menu | `right_click({pid, window_id, element_index})` or `click({pid, window_id, element_index, action: \"show_menu\"})` | Chromium web-content coerces pixel right-click to left Рђћ see `WEB_APPS.md` |\n| Type at cursor | `type_text({pid, text, window_id, element_index})` | `AXSelectedText` write; focuses first |\n| Set whole field value | `set_value({pid, window_id, element_index, value})` | sliders, steppers, text fields; **use for keyboard-commit workarounds on minimized windows** |\n| Scroll | `scroll({pid, direction, amount, by, window_id, element_index})` | synthesizes PageUp/PageDown/arrows via SLEventPostToPid |\n| Focus + send key | `press_key({pid, key, window_id, element_index, modifiers})` | element_index sets AXFocused, then posts key |\n| Send key to pid | `press_key({pid, key, modifiers})` | no focus change; key goes to pid's current focus |\n| Modifier combo | `hotkey({pid, keys})` | e.g. `[\"cmd\",\"c\"]`; posted per-pid, not HID tap |\n| Unicode keystrokes | `type_text({pid, text, delay_ms})` | AX write with automatic CGEvent fallback; reaches Chromium/Electron inputs |\n\n**All keyboard/text primitives require `pid`.** There is no\nfrontmost-routed variant Рђћ every key goes to the named target via\n`CGEvent.postToPid`, so the driver cannot leak keystrokes into the\nuser's foreground app.\n\n**Why `element_index` is the primary path:** works on hidden /\noccluded / off-Space windows, no focus steal, stable across\nrebuilds, labels tell you what you're clicking. Reach for pixel\ncoordinates only when AX can't.\n\n### Pixel-coordinate clicks\n\nThe pixel path (`click({pid, x, y})`) is for surfaces the AX tree\ndoesn't reach Рђћ canvases, video players, WebGL, custom-drawn controls.\nCoords are **window-local screenshot pixels** (same space as the PNG\n`get_window_state` returns). Top-left origin, y-down. The driver\nhandles screen-point conversion internally. Passing `window_id`\nalongside `x, y` is optional but recommended Рђћ it pins the\ncoordinate conversion to the window whose screenshot produced the\npixel, rather than the driver's heuristic choice.\n\n#### Reading coordinates from the PNG\n\nPNGs returned by `get_window_state` are capped at **1568 px\nlong-side by default** (`max_image_dimension` config), matching\nAnthropic's multimodal-vision downsampling limit. That means the\nimage the model reasons over and the image the click tool's\ncoordinate system lives in are the **same resolution** Рђћ just look\nat the PNG, pick a pixel, click at that pixel. No scaling math.\n\nThis is the default because the mismatch between \"rendered\nthumbnail\" and \"native PNG\" was a recurring coord-estimation\nfootgun. If you opt out (explicit `max_image_dimension=0` for\npixel-perfect verification flows), the old rule applies: don't\neyeball coords from whatever your client renders Рђћ it may be\n2-4├Ќ smaller than the PNG on disk, and a 2% error in thumbnail\nspace becomes ~80 px in the real image. Use the crosshair recipe\nbelow against the full-resolution file in that case.\n\n1. `get_window_state({pid, window_id})` returns an image capped\n   at 1568 long-side (default) plus its dimensions\n   (`screenshot_width` / `screenshot_height`). Write the bytes to\n   disk with `--screenshot-out-file <path>` in any capture mode Рђћ works\n   identically in `vision` (where it's the only way) and `som`\n   (where it sidesteps the jq + base64 dance on the spliced\n   `screenshot_png_b64` field).\n2. You are a multimodal model Рђћ look at the PNG. Since the PNG\n   matches what you see, pick the target pixel directly. No\n   fractional math needed.\n3. When precision matters (small targets, dense UIs), draw a\n   crosshair on the image (do **not** crop Рђћ cropping loses the\n   coordinate system and requires error-prone offset math) and\n   show it before clicking:\n\n```python\nfrom PIL import Image, ImageDraw\nimg = Image.open('/tmp/shot.png')\ndraw = ImageDraw.Draw(img)\nx, y = <your_coordinate>\nr = 18\ndraw.ellipse([x-r, y-r, x+r, y+r], outline='red', width=4)\ndraw.line([x-30, y, x+30, y], fill='red', width=3)\ndraw.line([x, y-30, x, y+30], fill='red', width=3)\nimg.save('/tmp/shot_annotated.png')\n```\n\n4. Only dispatch the click after the user (or your own re-read of\n   the annotated image) confirms the crosshair is on target.\n\n#### Addressing variants\n\n- `click({pid, x, y})` Рђћ single left-click.\n- `click({pid, x, y, count: 2})` Рђћ double-click.\n- `click({pid, x, y, modifier: [\"cmd\"]})` Рђћ cmd-click. Accepts any\n  subset of `cmd/shift/option/ctrl`.\n- `right_click({pid, x, y})` Рђћ also takes `modifier`.\n\nThe pixel path animates the agent cursor overlay but never warps\nthe real cursor. If the pid has no on-screen window the call errors\nwith `pid X has no on-screen window` Рђћ you need a visible window to\nanchor the conversion.\n\n#### How the pixel click is dispatched\n\nThe recipe is the backgrounded \"noraise\" sequence: yabai's\nfocus-without-raise SLPS event records followed by an off-screen\nuser-activation primer and the real click, all stamped via\n`SLEventPostToPid`. The target app becomes AppKit-active for event\nrouting but its window does **not** rise to the front of the\nz-stack, and macOS's \"switch to Space with windows for app\" follow\nis suppressed. Full mechanics in\n`Sources/CuaDriverCore/Input/MouseInput.swift` (`clickViaAuthSignedPost`)\nand the companion `FocusWithoutRaise.swift`.\n\n#### Known limits\n\n- **Chromium `<video>` play/pause**: pixel click is often rejected\n  by HTML5's click-to-play handler on some builds. Use keyboard\n  instead: `press_key({pid, key: \"k\"})` (YouTube) or\n  `press_key({pid, key: \"space\"})` (generic). Keyboard events\n  travel through a different auth envelope.\n- **Pixel right-click on Chromium web content** coerces to a\n  left-click Рђћ a known Chromium renderer-IPC limitation that affects\n  every non-HID-tap synthesis path. For context menus on\n  AX-addressable elements (links, buttons, toolbar items), use\n  `right_click({pid, element_index})` instead.\n\n### Canvases, viewports, games (Blender, Unity, GHOST, Qt, wxWidgets)\n\nApps whose main surface is an OpenGL / Metal / Qt / wxWidgets\nviewport expose **no useful AX tree** Рђћ the whole surface is one\nopaque `AXGroup` or `AXWindow` from AX's perspective. Per-pid event\npaths (`SLEventPostToPid`, `CGEvent.postToPid`) are filtered by the\nviewport's own event-source check and silently dropped Рђћ the event\nloop wants \"real HID origin\".\n\nThe working pattern:\n\n1. Bring the target frontmost (a brief `osascript activate` is\n   acceptable here Рђћ this is the carve-out the skill's osascript\n   gate allows).\n2. `CGEvent.post(tap: .cghidEventTap)` with a leading `mouseMoved`\n   event (~30 ms before the click). `cua-driver click` when the\n   target is frontmost automatically takes this path.\n3. Accept that the real cursor visibly moves Рђћ `cghidEventTap` is\n   the system HID stream, the cursor warps to the click point.\n\nThere is no backgrounded path that reaches these apps today.\n\n## Navigating native menu bars (AXMenuBar)\n\n**Only drive the menu bar when the target app is frontmost.** This\nis the single most-misused cua-driver capability. If the target is\nbackgrounded, don't reach for `AXMenuBarItem` + AXPick Рђћ use\nin-window `element_index` or pixel clicks instead. Two reasons, one\nfunctional and one perceptual:\n\n- **Functional:** menu items that touch document/playback/editor\n  state go `DISABLED` when their owning app isn't the key window\n  (Preview rotate, IINA speed change, most editor commands). AXPick\n  + AXPress will dispatch successfully from the driver's side but\n  no-op at the target Рђћ you get a silent false-pass.\n- **Perceptual (matters for demos, screen recordings, and anything\n  the user watches live):** macOS's screen-rendered menu bar\n  always belongs to the *frontmost* app. AXPick on a backgrounded\n  app's `AXMenuBarItem` dispatches to that app's per-process menu at\n  the AX layer, but any visible menu render happens over the\n  frontmost app's menu bar Рђћ the viewer sees an IINA submenu\n  flashing on top of Chrome's menus, which reads as \"the agent\n  clicked the wrong app.\" The AX call was correct; the frame the\n  user sees is not. For recorded or observed sessions, this is an\n  integrity bug even though it's not a correctness bug.\n\n**Good decision rule:** if the target is not already frontmost, do\nnot use `AXMenuBarItem` at all. For *reading* in-window state,\nsnapshot the window AX tree Рђћ most apps expose the same state via\nan in-window `AXStaticText`, title bar, or toolbar. For *dispatching*\nactions, use in-window `element_index` (buttons, toolbar items) or\npixel clicks on in-window controls Рђћ both dispatch via AppKit's\nwindow-under-pointer hit-test and are **not** frontmost-gated.\n\nWhen the target IS frontmost, the menu-bar flow below is fine and\nthe canonical path for menus.\n\n### The two-snapshot pattern (target frontmost only)\n\nMenu contents are a two-snapshot flow. Closed AXMenu subtrees are\ndeliberately skipped during snapshot Рђћ otherwise every app's File /\nEdit / View hierarchy plus every Recent Items macOS has ever seen\nwould inflate the tree 10-100x. But once a menu is *open*, its\nAXMenuItem children do receive `element_index` values so you can\nclick them normally.\n\n1. Find the `[N] AXMenuBarItem \"<Menu Name>\"` in the tree.\n2. `click({pid, element_index: N, action: \"pick\"})` Рђћ menu bar items\n   implement `AXPick` (\"open my submenu\"), not `AXPress`. Using the\n   default action on an AXMenuBarItem is a no-op.\n3. Re-snapshot. The expanded menu's items now appear under the bar\n   item as `[M] AXMenuItem \"<Item Name>\"`.\n4. Click the target item Рђћ most items respond to `AXPress` (default\n   action). Submenus nest under the item and are walked the same way.\n5. Re-snapshot and verify.\n\nIf you ever need to back out without selecting, `press_key({pid, key:\n\"escape\"})` closes the open menu. Leaving a menu expanded between\nturns poisons subsequent snapshots for that pid.\n\n### Commands gated on the target being frontmost\n\nSome menu items and global shortcuts (Preview's Tools Рєњ Rotate\nRight, РїўR; anything in the View menu that manipulates the current\ndocument; most editor commands) are **disabled unless the target\napp is the key / frontmost window**. You'll see it in the AX tree\nas `DISABLED` on the menu item even though the user's intent is\nobviously valid.\n\nBefore activating, confirm you're in this narrow case Рђћ the menu\nitem still reads `DISABLED` after a fresh snapshot AND the action\nthe user requested genuinely requires frontmost (Preview rotate,\nView menu document manipulation, editor commands). If either\ncheck fails, don't activate.\n\nWhen both checks pass, the driver has no `activate` tool\n(deliberately Рђћ the whole point is backgroundable control), so\nthis is the one legitimate `osascript` fallback:\n\n```\nosascript -e 'tell application \"<App Name>\" to activate'\n```\n\nThen re-snapshot Рђћ the menu item loses its `DISABLED` tag Рђћ and\n`click({action: \"pick\"})` the item. Alternatively, a `hotkey`\ncall delivered to the now-frontmost app works for the shortcut\nform (`РїўR`, `Рїў+`, etc.).\n\n**Always name the focus steal in your response** so the user isn't\nsurprised Рђћ \"Briefly activating Preview to enable Tools Рєњ Rotate\nRight\" or similar. Don't silently steal focus. You don't need to\nrestore the previous frontmost afterwards unless the user asks Рђћ\nthey can cmd-tab back.\n\n## Web-rendered apps (browsers, Electron, Tauri)\n\nFor Chrome / Edge / Brave / Arc / Safari, Electron apps (Slack,\nVSCode, Notion, Discord), and Tauri apps Рђћ see **`WEB_APPS.md`**.\n\nCovers: sparse AX tree population (retry-once pattern for Chromium),\nURL navigation via omnibox suggestions, the `set_value` workaround\nfor keyboard commits on **minimized** windows (Return silently\nno-ops Рђћ symptom is a macOS system beep; use `set_value` or click a\nclickable equivalent), scrolling via synthetic PageUp/Down keystrokes,\nin-page clicks, and typing into web inputs.\n\nChromium web content specifically also coerces `right_click` back to\nleft Рђћ use `element_index` for AX-addressable targets and accept the\nlimit otherwise.\n\n### Browser JS primitives Рђћ `page` tool and `get_window_state(javascript=)`\n\nWhen the AX tree doesn't expose the data you need (common in\nChromium/Electron Рђћ the tree is sparse for web content), use the\n`page` tool or the `javascript` param on `get_window_state` to query\nthe DOM directly via Apple Events. Requires \"Allow JavaScript from\nApple Events\" to be enabled Рђћ see `WEB_APPS.md` for the setup path.\n\n**Three actions on the `page` tool:**\n\n- `page({pid, window_id, action: \"get_text\"})` Рђћ returns\n  `document.body.innerText`. Fastest way to read page content, prices,\n  article text, or any raw text the AX tree truncates or omits.\n\n- `page({pid, window_id, action: \"query_dom\", css_selector: \"a[href]\",\n  attributes: [\"href\"]})` Рђћ runs `querySelectorAll` and returns each\n  match's tag, text, and requested attributes as a JSON array. Use for\n  table rows, link hrefs, data attributes, structured page data.\n\n- `page({pid, window_id, action: \"execute_javascript\", javascript:\n  \"...\"})` Рђћ raw JS. Wrap in an IIFE with try-catch. Don't use this for\n  elements already indexed by `get_window_state` Рђћ `click` and\n  `set_value` are more reliable there.\n\n**Co-located read Рђћ `get_window_state` with `javascript`:**\n\n```\nget_window_state({pid, window_id, javascript: \"document.title\"})\n```\n\nRuns the JS and appends the result as a `## JavaScript result` section\nalongside the AX snapshot Рђћ one round-trip instead of two. Use this\nwhen you need both the element tree (for subsequent clicks) and some\npage data in the same turn.\n\n**Decision rule Рђћ AX vs JS:**\n\n| Need | Use |\n|---|---|\n| Click / type into an element | `get_window_state` Рєњ `click` / `set_value` (AX, works backgrounded) |\n| Read text the AX tree drops | `page(get_text)` or `get_window_state(javascript=)` |\n| Scrape structured data (tables, hrefs) | `page(query_dom)` |\n| Trigger JS events / mutations | `page(execute_javascript)` |\n\nSupported backends:\n\n| App type | How | Context |\n|---|---|---|\n| Chrome / Brave / Edge | Apple Events `execute javascript` | Full DOM РюЁ |\n| Safari | Apple Events `do JavaScript` | Full DOM РюЁ |\n| Electron (VS Code, CursorРђд) | SIGUSR1 Рєњ V8 inspector Рєњ CDP | Main process only: `process`, `Buffer` Рђћ no `document`, no `require` in sandboxed apps |\n| Electron (with `--remote-debugging-port`) | CDP page target | Full DOM РюЁ |\n\n**Electron sandbox note:** SIGUSR1 connects to the Node.js *main* process.\nSandboxed Electron apps (VS Code, Cursor) strip `require` and Electron\nAPIs there. Useful for: `process.env`, `process.versions`, `process.cwd()`,\n`process.pid`. For full DOM/renderer access, launch the app with\n`--remote-debugging-port=9222` Рђћ cua-driver will detect and prefer the\npage target automatically.\n\nArc returns no values; Firefox has no JS-via-AppleEvents support Рђћ see\n`WEB_APPS.md` for the full matrix.\n\n### 3. Re-snapshot and verify Рђћ mandatory\n\n**Always** call `get_window_state({pid, window_id})` after the action.\nThis isn't optional verification Рђћ it's the second half of the\nsnapshot invariant.\n\nCheck the AX tree diff: a changed value, a new element, a new\nwindow, or the disappearance of the thing you just clicked (menus\ncollapse after selection, buttons may become disabled, etc.). If\nnothing changed, the action likely failed silently Рђћ **tell the\nuser what you attempted and what you observed**, don't paper over\nwith \"done\" language. Agents that skip this step report success on\nsilently-dropped actions Рђћ the single most common failure mode.\n\n## Recording trajectories\n\nSession-scoped action recording + replay, for demos, regressions, and\ntraining data. Only invoke when the user explicitly asks to record a\nsession Рђћ the skill does not auto-enable this. CLI surface:\n`cua-driver recording start|stop|status`; raw tool: `set_recording`.\n\nSee **`RECORDING.md`** for the full flow: enable/disable, turn folder\ncontents, replay via `replay_trajectory`, and the element_index\ndoesn't-survive-across-sessions caveat.\n\n## Common error patterns\n\n| Error text | Meaning | Fix |\n|---|---|---|\n| `No cached AX state for pid X window_id W` | You either skipped `get_window_state` this turn, or passed a different `window_id` to the click than the one the snapshot cached against | Call `get_window_state({pid: X, window_id: W})` first Рђћ the same window_id you intend to click in |\n| `Invalid element_index N for pid X window_id W` | Index is stale or out of range | Re-run `get_window_state` with the same window_id, pick a fresh index from the new tree |\n| `window_id W belongs to pid P, not Рђд` | Passed a window_id that's owned by a different process | Use `list_windows({pid: X})` to enumerate this pid's own windows |\n| `AX action AXPress failed with code Рђд` | Element doesn't support AXPress | Try `show_menu`, `confirm`, `cancel`, or `pick` |\n| macOS system-alert beep on `press_key` with no visible change | Target window is minimized; Return / Space / Tab commits don't establish real renderer focus on minimized windows | AX-click a clickable equivalent (Go button, Submit button, checkbox) instead of pressing the key; see \"Keyboard commits on minimized windows\" under the Browser section |\n| `Accessibility permission not granted` | TCC not granted | Stop; tell user to grant in System Settings |\n| `Screen Recording permission not granted` | TCC not granted for capture | Affects `screenshot` and `get_window_state` (which always captures). Grant in System Settings Рђћ the driver can't operate without it |\n\n## Things to avoid\n\n- **Never** reuse an `element_index` across a re-snapshot of the same pid.\n- **Never** translate screenshot pixels into a click Рђћ the screenshot\n  is for visual disambiguation, not coordinates. Use the\n  `element_index`.\n- **Prefer AX over pixels.** `click({pid, x, y})` works for\n  canvas / WebView regions, but it lands blindly and skips the\n  agent-cursor overlay. Exhaust AX paths (menu bars, cmd-k palettes,\n  toolbar items, keyboard shortcuts) before dropping to coordinates.\n- **Never** drive destructive actions (delete files, close unsaved\n  documents, send messages, submit forms) without explicit user\n  intent for that specific destructive step.\n- **Never** launch apps autonomously; confirm with the user first\n  unless their original request clearly implies the launch.\n\n## Example end-to-end task\n\n**User:** \"Open the Downloads folder in Finder.\"\n\n1. `launch_app({bundle_id: \"com.apple.finder\", urls: [\"~/Downloads\"]})`\n   Рєњ `{pid: 844, windows: [{window_id: 6123, title: \"Downloads\", ...}]}`.\n   Idempotent launch; plus Finder opens a hidden window rooted at\n   `~/Downloads` via `application(_:open:)` Рђћ zero activation, no\n   focus steal. The `windows` array lets you skip a `list_windows` hop.\n2. `get_window_state({pid: 844, window_id: 6123})` Рєњ verify an\n   `AXWindow` whose title contains \"Downloads\" is present with a\n   populated AX subtree (sidebar, list view, files).\n3. Done.\n\nIf the user instead asks to navigate *within* an already-open Finder\nwindow, use the menu-bar flow from the \"Navigating native menu bars\"\nsection above (click Go Рєњ pick a menu item Рєњ re-snapshot Рєњ click it).\n","numLines":903,"startLine":1,"totalLines":903}}}
